dateSent.title: dateSent
dateSent.description: The date/time at which the message was sent.

paymentStatus.title: paymentStatus
paymentStatus.description: The status of payment; whether the invoice has been paid or not.

isPlanForApartment.title: isPlanForApartment
isPlanForApartment.description: Indicates some accommodation that this floor plan describes.

countryOfOrigin.title: countryOfOrigin
countryOfOrigin.description:
The country of origin of something, including products as well as creative  works such as movie and TV content.

In the case of TV and movie, this would be the country of the principle offices of the production company or individual responsible for the movie. For other kinds of [[CreativeWork]] it is difficult to provide fully general guidance, and properties such as [[contentLocation]] and [[locationCreated]] may be more applicable.

In the case of products, the country of origin of the product. The exact interpretation of this may vary by context and product type, and cannot be fully enumerated here.

permittedUsage.title: permittedUsage
permittedUsage.description: Indications regarding the permitted usage of the accommodation.

scheduledTime.title: scheduledTime
scheduledTime.description: The time the object is scheduled to.

itinerary.title: itinerary
itinerary.description: Destination(s) ( [[Place]] ) that make up a trip. For a trip where destination order is important use [[ItemList]] to specify that order (see examples).

uploadDate.title: uploadDate
uploadDate.description: Date (including time if available) when this media object was uploaded to this site.

floorLimit.title: floorLimit
floorLimit.description: A floor limit is the amount of money above which credit card transactions must be authorized.

addressCountry.title: addressCountry
addressCountry.description: The country. For example, USA. You can also provide the two-letter [ISO 3166-1 alpha-2 country code](http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/ISO_3166-1).

broadcastSignalModulation.title: broadcastSignalModulation
broadcastSignalModulation.description: The modulation (e.g. FM, AM, etc) used by a particular broadcast service.

issn.title: issn
issn.description: The International Standard Serial Number (ISSN) that identifies this serial publication. You can repeat this property to identify different formats of, or the linking ISSN (ISSN-L) for, this serial publication.

cvdNumVentUse.title: cvdNumVentUse
cvdNumVentUse.description: numventuse - MECHANICAL VENTILATORS IN USE: Total number of ventilators in use.

isVariantOf.title: isVariantOf
isVariantOf.description: Indicates the kind of product that this is a variant of. In the case of [[ProductModel]], this is a pointer (from a ProductModel) to a base product from which this product is a variant. It is safe to infer that the variant inherits all product features from the base model, unless defined locally. This is not transitive. In the case of a [[ProductGroup]], the group description also serves as a template, representing a set of Products that vary on explicitly defined, specific dimensions only (so it defines both a set of variants, as well as which values distinguish amongst those variants). When used with [[ProductGroup]], this property can apply to any [[Product]] included in the group.

proprietaryName.title: proprietaryName
proprietaryName.description: Proprietary name given to the diet plan, typically by its originator or creator.

seatRow.title: seatRow
seatRow.description: The row location of the reserved seat (e.g., B).

error.title: error
error.description: For failed actions, more information on the cause of the failure.

supply.title: supply
supply.description: A sub-property of instrument. A supply consumed when performing instructions or a direction.

cvdNumICUBedsOcc.title: cvdNumICUBedsOcc
cvdNumICUBedsOcc.description: numicubedsocc - ICU BED OCCUPANCY: Total number of staffed inpatient ICU beds that are occupied.

replacer.title: replacer
replacer.description: A sub property of object. The object that replaces.

taxID.title: taxID
taxID.description: The Tax / Fiscal ID of the organization or person, e.g. the TIN in the US or the CIF/NIF in Spain.

doseSchedule.title: doseSchedule
doseSchedule.description: A dosing schedule for the drug for a given population, either observed, recommended, or maximum dose based on the type used.

restPeriods.title: restPeriods
restPeriods.description: How often one should break from the activity.

softwareAddOn.title: softwareAddOn
softwareAddOn.description: Additional content for a software application.

inChIKey.title: inChIKey
inChIKey.description: InChIKey is a hashed version of the full InChI (using the SHA-256 algorithm).

cvdNumC19OFMechVentPats.title: cvdNumC19OFMechVentPats
cvdNumC19OFMechVentPats.description: numc19ofmechventpats - ED/OVERFLOW and VENTILATED: Patients with suspected or confirmed COVID-19 who are in the ED or any overflow location awaiting an inpatient bed and on a mechanical ventilator.

greater.title: greater
greater.description: This ordering relation for qualitative values indicates that the subject is greater than the object.

articleSection.title: articleSection
articleSection.description: Articles may belong to one or more 'sections' in a magazine or newspaper, such as Sports, Lifestyle, etc.

diagnosis.title: diagnosis
diagnosis.description: One or more alternative conditions considered in the differential diagnosis process as output of a diagnosis process.

encodingFormat.title: encodingFormat
encodingFormat.description:
Media type typically expressed using a MIME format (see [IANA site](http://www.iana.org/assignments/media-types/media-types.xhtml) and [MDN reference](https://developer.mozilla.org/en-US/docs/Web/HTTP/Basics_of_HTTP/MIME_types)), e.g. application/zip for a SoftwareApplication binary, audio/mpeg for .mp3 etc.

In cases where a [[CreativeWork]] has several media type representations, [[encoding]] can be used to indicate each [[MediaObject]] alongside particular [[encodingFormat]] information.

Unregistered or niche encoding and file formats can be indicated instead via the most appropriate URL, e.g. defining Web page or a Wikipedia/Wikidata entry.

datePublished.title: datePublished
datePublished.description: Date of first publication or broadcast. For example the date a [[CreativeWork]] was broadcast or a [[Certification]] was issued.

hasBroadcastChannel.title: hasBroadcastChannel
hasBroadcastChannel.description: A broadcast channel of a broadcast service.

producer.title: producer
producer.description: The person or organization who produced the work (e.g. music album, movie, TV/radio series etc.).

validUntil.title: validUntil
validUntil.description: The date when the item is no longer valid.

amountOfThisGood.title: amountOfThisGood
amountOfThisGood.description: The quantity of the goods included in the offer.

inverseOf.title: inverseOf
inverseOf.description: Relates a property to a property that is its inverse. Inverse properties relate the same pairs of items to each other, but in reversed direction. For example, the 'alumni' and 'alumniOf' properties are inverseOf each other. Some properties don't have explicit inverses; in these situations RDFa and JSON-LD syntax for reverse properties can be used.

participant.title: participant
participant.description: Other co-agents that participated in the action indirectly. E.g. John wrote a book with *Steve*.

skills.title: skills
skills.description: A statement of knowledge, skill, ability, task or any other assertion expressing a competency that is desired or required to fulfill this role or to work in this occupation.

ethicsPolicy.title: ethicsPolicy
ethicsPolicy.description: Statement about ethics policy, e.g. of a [[NewsMediaOrganization]] regarding journalistic and publishing practices, or of a [[Restaurant]], a page describing food source policies. In the case of a [[NewsMediaOrganization]], an ethicsPolicy is typically a statement describing the personal, organizational, and corporate standards of behavior expected by the organization.

associatedMedia.title: associatedMedia
associatedMedia.description: A media object that encodes this CreativeWork. This property is a synonym for encoding.

constraintProperty.title: constraintProperty
constraintProperty.description: Indicates a property used as a constraint. For example, in the definition of a [[StatisticalVariable]]. The value is a property, either from within Schema.org or from other compatible (e.g. RDF) systems such as DataCommons.org or Wikidata.org.

signDetected.title: signDetected
signDetected.description: A sign detected by the test.

valueReference.title: valueReference
valueReference.description: A secondary value that provides additional information on the original value, e.g. a reference temperature or a type of measurement.

monthsOfExperience.title: monthsOfExperience
monthsOfExperience.description: Indicates the minimal number of months of experience required for a position.

programPrerequisites.title: programPrerequisites
programPrerequisites.description: Prerequisites for enrolling in the program.

honorificPrefix.title: honorificPrefix
honorificPrefix.description: An honorific prefix preceding a Person's name such as Dr/Mrs/Mr.

rsvpResponse.title: rsvpResponse
rsvpResponse.description: The response (yes, no, maybe) to the RSVP.

unnamedSourcesPolicy.title: unnamedSourcesPolicy
unnamedSourcesPolicy.description: For an [[Organization]] (typically a [[NewsMediaOrganization]]), a statement about policy on use of unnamed sources and the decision process required.

genre.title: genre
genre.description: Genre of the creative work, broadcast channel or group.

polygon.title: polygon
polygon.description: A polygon is the area enclosed by a point-to-point path for which the starting and ending points are the same. A polygon is expressed as a series of four or more space delimited points where the first and final points are identical.

downloadUrl.title: downloadUrl
downloadUrl.description: If the file can be downloaded, URL to download the binary.

priceComponent.title: priceComponent
priceComponent.description: This property links to all [[UnitPriceSpecification]] nodes that apply in parallel for the [[CompoundPriceSpecification]] node.

returnPolicySeasonalOverride.title: returnPolicySeasonalOverride
returnPolicySeasonalOverride.description: Seasonal override of a return policy.

defaultValue.title: defaultValue
defaultValue.description: The default value of the input.  For properties that expect a literal, the default is a literal value, for properties that expect an object, it's an ID reference to one of the current values.

transFatContent.title: transFatContent
transFatContent.description: The number of grams of trans fat.

warranty.title: warranty
warranty.description: The warranty promise(s) included in the offer.

interactionStatistic.title: interactionStatistic
interactionStatistic.description: The number of interactions for the CreativeWork using the WebSite or SoftwareApplication. The most specific child type of InteractionCounter should be used.

parentItem.title: parentItem
parentItem.description: The parent of a question, answer or item in general. Typically used for Q/A discussion threads e.g. a chain of comments with the first comment being an [[Article]] or other [[CreativeWork]]. See also [[comment]] which points from something to a comment about it.

codeValue.title: codeValue
codeValue.description: A short textual code that uniquely identifies the value.

broadcastDisplayName.title: broadcastDisplayName
broadcastDisplayName.description: The name displayed in the channel guide. For many US affiliates, it is the network name.

legislationIdentifier.title: legislationIdentifier
legislationIdentifier.description: An identifier for the legislation. This can be either a string-based identifier, like the CELEX at EU level or the NOR in France, or a web-based, URL/URI identifier, like an ELI (European Legislation Identifier) or an URN-Lex.

syllabusSections.title: syllabusSections
syllabusSections.description: Indicates (typically several) Syllabus entities that lay out what each section of the overall course will cover.

isFamilyFriendly.title: isFamilyFriendly
isFamilyFriendly.description: Indicates whether this content is family friendly.

discountCode.title: discountCode
discountCode.description: Code used to redeem a discount.

acquiredFrom.title: acquiredFrom
acquiredFrom.description: The organization or person from which the product was acquired.

endorsee.title: endorsee
endorsee.description: A sub property of participant. The person/organization being supported.

broadcastSubChannel.title: broadcastSubChannel
broadcastSubChannel.description: The subchannel used for the broadcast.

archivedAt.title: archivedAt
archivedAt.description: Indicates a page or other link involved in archival of a [[CreativeWork]]. In the case of [[MediaReview]], the items in a [[MediaReviewItem]] may often become inaccessible, but be archived by archival, journalistic, activist, or law enforcement organizations. In such cases, the referenced page may not directly publish the content.

stageAsNumber.title: stageAsNumber
stageAsNumber.description: The stage represented as a number, e.g. 3.

hasMenuItem.title: hasMenuItem
hasMenuItem.description: A food or drink item contained in a menu or menu section.

worksFor.title: worksFor
worksFor.description: Organizations that the person works for.

trailer.title: trailer
trailer.description: The trailer of a movie or TV/radio series, season, episode, etc.

algorithm.title: algorithm
algorithm.description: The algorithm or rules to follow to compute the score.

repeatCount.title: repeatCount
repeatCount.description: Defines the number of times a recurring [[Event]] will take place.

accessibilityFeature.title: accessibilityFeature
accessibilityFeature.description: Content features of the resource, such as accessible media, alternatives and supported enhancements for accessibility. Values should be drawn from the [approved vocabulary](https://www.w3.org/2021/a11y-discov-vocab/latest/#accessibilityFeature-vocabulary).

breadcrumb.title: breadcrumb
breadcrumb.description: A set of links that can help a user understand and navigate a website hierarchy.

seatSection.title: seatSection
seatSection.description: The section location of the reserved seat (e.g. Orchestra).

hasTierBenefit.title: hasTierBenefit
hasTierBenefit.description: A member benefit for a particular tier of a loyalty program.

jobStartDate.title: jobStartDate
jobStartDate.description: The date on which a successful applicant for this job would be expected to start work. Choose a specific date in the future or use the jobImmediateStart property to indicate the position is to be filled as soon as possible.

tributary.title: tributary
tributary.description: The anatomical or organ system that the vein flows into; a larger structure that the vein connects to.

returnPolicyCountry.title: returnPolicyCountry
returnPolicyCountry.description: The country where the product has to be sent to for returns, for example "Ireland" using the [[name]] property of [[Country]]. You can also provide the two-letter [ISO 3166-1 alpha-2 country code](http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/ISO_3166-1). Note that this can be different from the country where the product was originally shipped from or sent to.

nerveMotor.title: nerveMotor
nerveMotor.description: The neurological pathway extension that involves muscle control.

cvdNumC19Died.title: cvdNumC19Died
cvdNumC19Died.description: numc19died - DEATHS: Patients with suspected or confirmed COVID-19 who died in the hospital, ED, or any overflow location.

eligibleRegion.title: eligibleRegion
eligibleRegion.description: The ISO 3166-1 (ISO 3166-1 alpha-2) or ISO 3166-2 code, the place, or the GeoShape for the geo-political region(s) for which the offer or delivery charge specification is valid.\n\nSee also [[ineligibleRegion]].

episode.title: episode
episode.description: An episode of a TV, radio or game media within a series or season.

quarantineGuidelines.title: quarantineGuidelines
quarantineGuidelines.description: Guidelines about quarantine rules, e.g. in the context of a pandemic.

seriousAdverseOutcome.title: seriousAdverseOutcome
seriousAdverseOutcome.description: A possible serious complication and/or serious side effect of this therapy. Serious adverse outcomes include those that are life-threatening; result in death, disability, or permanent damage; require hospitalization or prolong existing hospitalization; cause congenital anomalies or birth defects; or jeopardize the patient and may require medical or surgical intervention to prevent one of the outcomes in this definition.

landlord.title: landlord
landlord.description: A sub property of participant. The owner of the real estate property.

priceCurrency.title: priceCurrency
priceCurrency.description: The currency of the price, or a price component when attached to [[PriceSpecification]] and its subtypes.\n\nUse standard formats: [ISO 4217 currency format](http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/ISO_4217), e.g. "USD"; [Ticker symbol](https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/List_of_cryptocurrencies) for cryptocurrencies, e.g. "BTC"; well known names for [Local Exchange Trading Systems](https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Local_exchange_trading_system) (LETS) and other currency types, e.g. "Ithaca HOUR".

audience.title: audience
audience.description: An intended audience, i.e. a group for whom something was created.

jobTitle.title: jobTitle
jobTitle.description: The job title of the person (for example, Financial Manager).

contentLocation.title: contentLocation
contentLocation.description: The location depicted or described in the content. For example, the location in a photograph or painting.

jurisdiction.title: jurisdiction
jurisdiction.description: Indicates a legal jurisdiction, e.g. of some legislation, or where some government service is based.

composer.title: composer
composer.description: The person or organization who wrote a composition, or who is the composer of a work performed at some event.

duration.title: duration
duration.description: The duration of the item (movie, audio recording, event, etc.) in [ISO 8601 duration format](http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/ISO_8601).

maxPrice.title: maxPrice
maxPrice.description: The highest price if the price is a range.

object.title: object
object.description: The object upon which the action is carried out, whose state is kept intact or changed. Also known as the semantic roles patient, affected or undergoer (which change their state) or theme (which doesn't). E.g. John read *a book*.

knowsAbout.title: knowsAbout
knowsAbout.description: Of a [[Person]], and less typically of an [[Organization]], to indicate a topic that is known about - suggesting possible expertise but not implying it. We do not distinguish skill levels here, or relate this to educational content, events, objectives or [[JobPosting]] descriptions.

contentType.title: contentType
contentType.description: The supported content type(s) for an EntryPoint response.

dropoffLocation.title: dropoffLocation
dropoffLocation.description: Where a rental car can be dropped off.

subEvent.title: subEvent
subEvent.description: An Event that is part of this event. For example, a conference event includes many presentations, each of which is a subEvent of the conference.

catalogNumber.title: catalogNumber
catalogNumber.description: The catalog number for the release.

nonprofitStatus.title: nonprofitStatus
nonprofitStatus.description: nonprofitStatus indicates the legal status of a non-profit organization in its primary place of business.

acceptsReservations.title: acceptsReservations
acceptsReservations.description: Indicates whether a FoodEstablishment accepts reservations. Values can be Boolean, an URL at which reservations can be made or (for backwards compatibility) the strings ```Yes``` or ```No```.

legalName.title: legalName
legalName.description: The official name of the organization, e.g. the registered company name.

suggestedAnswer.title: suggestedAnswer
suggestedAnswer.description: An answer (possibly one of several, possibly incorrect) to a Question, e.g. on a Question/Answer site.

artEdition.title: artEdition
artEdition.description: The number of copies when multiple copies of a piece of artwork are produced - e.g. for a limited edition of 20 prints, 'artEdition' refers to the total number of copies (in this example "20").

catalog.title: catalog
catalog.description: A data catalog which contains this dataset.

estimatedSalary.title: estimatedSalary
estimatedSalary.description: An estimated salary for a job posting or occupation, based on a variety of variables including, but not limited to industry, job title, and location. Estimated salaries  are often computed by outside organizations rather than the hiring organization, who may not have committed to the estimated value.

collectionSize.title: collectionSize
collectionSize.description: The number of items in the [[Collection]].

broadcastTimezone.title: broadcastTimezone
broadcastTimezone.description: The timezone in [ISO 8601 format](http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/ISO_8601) for which the service bases its broadcasts.

sensoryRequirement.title: sensoryRequirement
sensoryRequirement.description: A description of any sensory requirements and levels necessary to function on the job, including hearing and vision. Defined terms such as those in O*net may be used, but note that there is no way to specify the level of ability as well as its nature when using a defined term.

containedIn.title: containedIn
containedIn.description: The basic containment relation between a place and one that contains it.

healthPlanMarketingUrl.title: healthPlanMarketingUrl
healthPlanMarketingUrl.description: The URL that goes directly to the plan brochure for the specific standard plan or plan variation.

pathophysiology.title: pathophysiology
pathophysiology.description: Changes in the normal mechanical, physical, and biochemical functions that are associated with this activity or condition.

sizeGroup.title: sizeGroup
sizeGroup.description: The size group (also known as "size type") for a product's size. Size groups are common in the fashion industry to define size segments and suggested audiences for wearable products. Multiple values can be combined, for example "men's big and tall", "petite maternity" or "regular".

auditDate.title: auditDate
auditDate.description: Date when a certification was last audited. See also  [gs1:certificationAuditDate](https://www.gs1.org/voc/certificationAuditDate).

actionPlatform.title: actionPlatform
actionPlatform.description: The high level platform(s) where the Action can be performed for the given URL. To specify a specific application or operating system instance, use actionApplication.

tissueSample.title: tissueSample
tissueSample.description: The type of tissue sample required for the test.

epidemiology.title: epidemiology
epidemiology.description: The characteristics of associated patients, such as age, gender, race etc.

maintainer.title: maintainer
maintainer.description: A maintainer of a [[Dataset]], software package ([[SoftwareApplication]]), or other [[Project]]. A maintainer is a [[Person]] or [[Organization]] that manages contributions to, and/or publication of, some (typically complex) artifact. It is common for distributions of software and data to be based on "upstream" sources. When [[maintainer]] is applied to a specific version of something e.g. a particular version or packaging of a [[Dataset]], it is always  possible that the upstream source has a different maintainer. The [[isBasedOn]] property can be used to indicate such relationships between datasets to make the different maintenance roles clear. Similarly in the case of software, a package may have dedicated maintainers working on integration into software distributions such as Ubuntu, as well as upstream maintainers of the underlying work.

recommendedIntake.title: recommendedIntake
recommendedIntake.description: Recommended intake of this supplement for a given population as defined by a specific recommending authority.

legislationDate.title: legislationDate
legislationDate.description: The date of adoption or signature of the legislation. This is the date at which the text is officially aknowledged to be a legislation, even though it might not even be published or in force.

strengthUnit.title: strengthUnit
strengthUnit.description: The units of an active ingredient's strength, e.g. mg.

educationRequirements.title: educationRequirements
educationRequirements.description: Educational background needed for the position or Occupation.

incentives.title: incentives
incentives.description: Description of bonus and commission compensation aspects of the job.

recipeCategory.title: recipeCategory
recipeCategory.description: The category of the recipe—for example, appetizer, entree, etc.

readBy.title: readBy
readBy.description: A person who reads (performs) the audiobook.

drugUnit.title: drugUnit
drugUnit.description: The unit in which the drug is measured, e.g. '5 mg tablet'.

musicArrangement.title: musicArrangement
musicArrangement.description: An arrangement derived from the composition.

customerRemorseReturnLabelSource.title: customerRemorseReturnLabelSource
customerRemorseReturnLabelSource.description: The method (from an enumeration) by which the customer obtains a return shipping label for a product returned due to customer remorse.

molecularFormula.title: molecularFormula
molecularFormula.description: The empirical formula is the simplest whole number ratio of all the atoms in a molecule.

entertainmentBusiness.title: entertainmentBusiness
entertainmentBusiness.description: A sub property of location. The entertainment business where the action occurred.

medicineSystem.title: medicineSystem
medicineSystem.description: The system of medicine that includes this MedicalEntity, for example 'evidence-based', 'homeopathic', 'chiropractic', etc.

securityClearanceRequirement.title: securityClearanceRequirement
securityClearanceRequirement.description: A description of any security clearance requirements of the job.

predecessorOf.title: predecessorOf
predecessorOf.description: A pointer from a previous, often discontinued variant of the product to its newer variant.

dataFeedElement.title: dataFeedElement
dataFeedElement.description: An item within a data feed. Data feeds may have many elements.

representativeOfPage.title: representativeOfPage
representativeOfPage.description: Indicates whether this image is representative of the content of the page.

funder.title: funder
funder.description: A person or organization that supports (sponsors) something through some kind of financial contribution.

safetyConsideration.title: safetyConsideration
safetyConsideration.description: Any potential safety concern associated with the supplement. May include interactions with other drugs and foods, pregnancy, breastfeeding, known adverse reactions, and documented efficacy of the supplement.

taxonomicRange.title: taxonomicRange
taxonomicRange.description: The taxonomic grouping of the organism that expresses, encodes, or in some way related to the BioChemEntity.

additionalNumberOfGuests.title: additionalNumberOfGuests
additionalNumberOfGuests.description: If responding yes, the number of guests who will attend in addition to the invitee.

endorsers.title: endorsers
endorsers.description: People or organizations that endorse the plan.

greaterOrEqual.title: greaterOrEqual
greaterOrEqual.description: This ordering relation for qualitative values indicates that the subject is greater than or equal to the object.

accountOverdraftLimit.title: accountOverdraftLimit
accountOverdraftLimit.description: An overdraft is an extension of credit from a lending institution when an account reaches zero. An overdraft allows the individual to continue withdrawing money even if the account has no funds in it. Basically the bank allows people to borrow a set amount of money.

totalPrice.title: totalPrice
totalPrice.description:
The total price for the reservation or ticket, including applicable taxes, shipping, etc.

Usage guidelines:

* Use values from 0123456789 (Unicode 'DIGIT ZERO' (U+0030) to 'DIGIT NINE' (U+0039)) rather than superficially similar Unicode symbols.
* Use '.' (Unicode 'FULL STOP' (U+002E)) rather than ',' to indicate a decimal point. Avoid using these symbols as a readability separator.

energyEfficiencyScaleMin.title: energyEfficiencyScaleMin
energyEfficiencyScaleMin.description: Specifies the least energy efficient class on the regulated EU energy consumption scale for the product category a product belongs to. For example, energy consumption for televisions placed on the market after January 1, 2020 is scaled from D to A+++.

certificationRating.title: certificationRating
certificationRating.description: Rating of a certification instance (as defined by an independent certification body). Typically this rating can be used to rate the level to which the requirements of the certification instance are fulfilled. See also [gs1:certificationValue](https://www.gs1.org/voc/certificationValue).

releaseOf.title: releaseOf
releaseOf.description: The album this is a release of.

numberOfEpisodes.title: numberOfEpisodes
numberOfEpisodes.description: The number of episodes in this season or series.

taxonRank.title: taxonRank
taxonRank.description: The taxonomic rank of this taxon given preferably as a URI from a controlled vocabulary – typically the ranks from TDWG TaxonRank ontology or equivalent Wikidata URIs.

endDate.title: endDate
endDate.description: The end date and time of the item (in [ISO 8601 date format](http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/ISO_8601)).

playMode.title: playMode
playMode.description: Indicates whether this game is multi-player, co-op or single-player.  The game can be marked as multi-player, co-op and single-player at the same time.

leiCode.title: leiCode
leiCode.description: An organization identifier that uniquely identifies a legal entity as defined in ISO 17442.

byArtist.title: byArtist
byArtist.description: The artist that performed this album or recording.

numberOfBeds.title: numberOfBeds
numberOfBeds.description: The quantity of the given bed type available in the HotelRoom, Suite, House, or Apartment.

tickerSymbol.title: tickerSymbol
tickerSymbol.description: The exchange traded instrument associated with a Corporation object. The tickerSymbol is expressed as an exchange and an instrument name separated by a space character. For the exchange component of the tickerSymbol attribute, we recommend using the controlled vocabulary of Market Identifier Codes (MIC) specified in ISO 15022.

associatedArticle.title: associatedArticle
associatedArticle.description: A NewsArticle associated with the Media Object.

doesNotShip.title: doesNotShip
doesNotShip.description: Indicates when shipping to a particular [[shippingDestination]] is not available.

sizeSystem.title: sizeSystem
sizeSystem.description: The size system used to identify a product's size. Typically either a standard (for example, "GS1" or "ISO-EN13402"), country code (for example "US" or "JP"), or a measuring system (for example "Metric" or "Imperial").

foundingLocation.title: foundingLocation
foundingLocation.description: The place where the Organization was founded.

studyDesign.title: studyDesign
studyDesign.description: Specifics about the observational study design (enumerated).

exercisePlan.title: exercisePlan
exercisePlan.description: A sub property of instrument. The exercise plan used on this action.

executableLibraryName.title: executableLibraryName
executableLibraryName.description: Library file name, e.g., mscorlib.dll, system.web.dll.

spatialCoverage.title: spatialCoverage
spatialCoverage.description:
The spatialCoverage of a CreativeWork indicates the place(s) which are the focus of the content. It is a subproperty of
      contentLocation intended primarily for more technical and detailed materials. For example with a Dataset, it indicates
      areas that the dataset describes: a dataset of New York weather would have spatialCoverage which was the place: the state of New York.

warning.title: warning
warning.description: Any FDA or other warnings about the drug (text or URL).

broadcastFrequencyValue.title: broadcastFrequencyValue
broadcastFrequencyValue.description: The frequency in MHz for a particular broadcast.

applicantLocationRequirements.title: applicantLocationRequirements
applicantLocationRequirements.description: The location(s) applicants can apply from. This is usually used for telecommuting jobs where the applicant does not need to be in a physical office. Note: This should not be used for citizenship or work visa requirements.

estimatesRiskOf.title: estimatesRiskOf
estimatesRiskOf.description: The condition, complication, or symptom whose risk is being estimated.

recipeIngredient.title: recipeIngredient
recipeIngredient.description: A single ingredient used in the recipe, e.g. sugar, flour or garlic.

contactPoints.title: contactPoints
contactPoints.description: A contact point for a person or organization.

cvdFacilityCounty.title: cvdFacilityCounty
cvdFacilityCounty.description: Name of the County of the NHSN facility that this data record applies to. Use [[cvdFacilityId]] to identify the facility. To provide other details, [[healthcareReportingData]] can be used on a [[Hospital]] entry.

loser.title: loser
loser.description: A sub property of participant. The loser of the action.

touristType.title: touristType
touristType.description: Attraction suitable for type(s) of tourist. E.g. children, visitors from a particular country, etc.

lastReviewed.title: lastReviewed
lastReviewed.description: Date on which the content on this web page was last reviewed for accuracy and/or completeness.

preparation.title: preparation
preparation.description: Typical preparation that a patient must undergo before having the procedure performed.

numberOfPages.title: numberOfPages
numberOfPages.description: The number of pages in the book.

workload.title: workload
workload.description: Quantitative measure of the physiologic output of the exercise; also referred to as energy expenditure.

dateIssued.title: dateIssued
dateIssued.description: The date the ticket was issued.

gtin8.title: gtin8
gtin8.description: The GTIN-8 code of the product, or the product to which the offer refers. This code is also known as EAN/UCC-8 or 8-digit EAN. See [GS1 GTIN Summary](http://www.gs1.org/barcodes/technical/idkeys/gtin) for more details.

occupationalCategory.title: occupationalCategory
occupationalCategory.description:
A category describing the job, preferably using a term from a taxonomy such as [BLS O*NET-SOC](http://www.onetcenter.org/taxonomy.html), [ISCO-08](https://www.ilo.org/public/english/bureau/stat/isco/isco08/) or similar, with the property repeated for each applicable value. Ideally the taxonomy should be identified, and both the textual label and formal code for the category should be provided.\n
Note: for historical reasons, any textual label and formal code provided as a literal may be assumed to be from O*NET-SOC.

productionCompany.title: productionCompany
productionCompany.description: The production company or studio responsible for the item, e.g. series, video game, episode etc.

applicationSuite.title: applicationSuite
applicationSuite.description: The name of the application suite to which the application belongs (e.g. Excel belongs to Office).

affectedBy.title: affectedBy
affectedBy.description: Drugs that affect the test's results.

memberOf.title: memberOf
memberOf.description: An Organization (or ProgramMembership) to which this Person or Organization belongs.

accessMode.title: accessMode
accessMode.description: The human sensory perceptual system or cognitive faculty through which a person may process or perceive information. Values should be drawn from the [approved vocabulary](https://www.w3.org/2021/a11y-discov-vocab/latest/#accessMode-vocabulary).

measurementTechnique.title: measurementTechnique
measurementTechnique.description:
A technique, method or technology used in an [[Observation]], [[StatisticalVariable]] or [[Dataset]] (or [[DataDownload]], [[DataCatalog]]), corresponding to the method used for measuring the corresponding variable(s) (for datasets, described using [[variableMeasured]]; for [[Observation]], a [[StatisticalVariable]]). Often but not necessarily each [[variableMeasured]] will have an explicit representation as (or mapping to) an property such as those defined in Schema.org, or other RDF vocabularies and "knowledge graphs". In that case the subproperty of [[variableMeasured]] called [[measuredProperty]] is applicable.
    
The [[measurementTechnique]] property helps when extra clarification is needed about how a [[measuredProperty]] was measured. This is oriented towards scientific and scholarly dataset publication but may have broader applicability; it is not intended as a full representation of measurement, but can often serve as a high level summary for dataset discovery. 

For example, if [[variableMeasured]] is: molecule concentration, [[measurementTechnique]] could be: "mass spectrometry" or "nmr spectroscopy" or "colorimetry" or "immunofluorescence". If the [[variableMeasured]] is "depression rating", the [[measurementTechnique]] could be "Zung Scale" or "HAM-D" or "Beck Depression Inventory". 

If there are several [[variableMeasured]] properties recorded for some given data object, use a [[PropertyValue]] for each [[variableMeasured]] and attach the corresponding [[measurementTechnique]]. The value can also be from an enumeration, organized as a [[MeasurementMetholdEnumeration]].

loanPaymentAmount.title: loanPaymentAmount
loanPaymentAmount.description: The amount of money to pay in a single payment.

bccRecipient.title: bccRecipient
bccRecipient.description: A sub property of recipient. The recipient blind copied on a message.

interpretedAsClaim.title: interpretedAsClaim
interpretedAsClaim.description: Used to indicate a specific claim contained, implied, translated or refined from the content of a [[MediaObject]] or other [[CreativeWork]]. The interpreting party can be indicated using [[claimInterpreter]].

workExample.title: workExample
workExample.description: Example/instance/realization/derivation of the concept of this creative work. E.g. the paperback edition, first edition, or e-book.

subEvents.title: subEvents
subEvents.description: Events that are a part of this event. For example, a conference event includes many presentations, each subEvents of the conference.

category.title: category
category.description: A category for the item. Greater signs or slashes can be used to informally indicate a category hierarchy.

educationalUse.title: educationalUse
educationalUse.description: The purpose of a work in the context of education; for example, 'assignment', 'group work'.

distribution.title: distribution
distribution.description: A downloadable form of this dataset, at a specific location, in a specific format. This property can be repeated if different variations are available. There is no expectation that different downloadable distributions must contain exactly equivalent information (see also [DCAT](https://www.w3.org/TR/vocab-dcat-3/#Class:Distribution) on this point). Different distributions might include or exclude different subsets of the entire dataset, for example.

member.title: member
member.description: A member of an Organization or a ProgramMembership. Organizations can be members of organizations; ProgramMembership is typically for individuals.

permissionType.title: permissionType
permissionType.description: The type of permission granted the person, organization, or audience.

isrcCode.title: isrcCode
isrcCode.description: The International Standard Recording Code for the recording.

maximumAttendeeCapacity.title: maximumAttendeeCapacity
maximumAttendeeCapacity.description: The total number of individuals that may attend an event or venue.

validIn.title: validIn
validIn.description: The geographic area where the item is valid. Applies for example to a [[Permit]], a [[Certification]], or an [[EducationalOccupationalCredential]].

accelerationTime.title: accelerationTime
accelerationTime.description:
The time needed to accelerate the vehicle from a given start velocity to a given target velocity.

Typical unit code(s): SEC for seconds

* Note: There are unfortunately no standard unit codes for seconds/0..100 km/h or seconds/0..60 mph. Simply use "SEC" for seconds and indicate the velocities in the [[name]] of the [[QuantitativeValue]], or use [[valueReference]] with a [[QuantitativeValue]] of 0..60 mph or 0..100 km/h to specify the reference speeds.

hasHealthAspect.title: hasHealthAspect
hasHealthAspect.description: Indicates the aspect or aspects specifically addressed in some [[HealthTopicContent]]. For example, that the content is an overview, or that it talks about treatment, self-care, treatments or their side-effects.

unitCode.title: unitCode
unitCode.description: The unit of measurement given using the UN/CEFACT Common Code (3 characters) or a URL. Other codes than the UN/CEFACT Common Code may be used with a prefix followed by a colon.

gameEdition.title: gameEdition
gameEdition.description: The edition of a video game.

maps.title: maps
maps.description: A URL to a map of the place.

homeTeam.title: homeTeam
homeTeam.description: The home team in a sports event.

shippingRate.title: shippingRate
shippingRate.description: The shipping rate is the cost of shipping to the specified destination. Typically, the maxValue and currency values (of the [[MonetaryAmount]]) are most appropriate.

actionAccessibilityRequirement.title: actionAccessibilityRequirement
actionAccessibilityRequirement.description: A set of requirements that must be fulfilled in order to perform an Action. If more than one value is specified, fulfilling one set of requirements will allow the Action to be performed.

gtin.title: gtin
gtin.description:
A Global Trade Item Number ([GTIN](https://www.gs1.org/standards/id-keys/gtin)). GTINs identify trade items, including products and services, using numeric identification codes.

A correct [[gtin]] value should be a valid GTIN, which means that it should be an all-numeric string of either 8, 12, 13 or 14 digits, or a "GS1 Digital Link" URL based on such a string. The numeric component should also have a [valid GS1 check digit](https://www.gs1.org/services/check-digit-calculator) and meet the other rules for valid GTINs. See also [GS1's GTIN Summary](http://www.gs1.org/barcodes/technical/idkeys/gtin) and [Wikipedia](https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Global_Trade_Item_Number) for more details. Left-padding of the gtin values is not required or encouraged. The [[gtin]] property generalizes the earlier [[gtin8]], [[gtin12]], [[gtin13]], and [[gtin14]] properties.

The GS1 [digital link specifications](https://www.gs1.org/standards/Digital-Link/) expresses GTINs as URLs (URIs, IRIs, etc.).
Digital Links should be populated into the [[hasGS1DigitalLink]] attribute.

Note also that this is a definition for how to include GTINs in Schema.org data, and not a definition of GTINs in general - see the GS1 documentation for authoritative details.

cvdNumC19HospPats.title: cvdNumC19HospPats
cvdNumC19HospPats.description: numc19hosppats - HOSPITALIZED: Patients currently hospitalized in an inpatient care location who have suspected or confirmed COVID-19.

sourceOrganization.title: sourceOrganization
sourceOrganization.description: The Organization on whose behalf the creator was working.

geoWithin.title: geoWithin
geoWithin.description: Represents a relationship between two geometries (or the places they represent), relating a geometry to one that contains it, i.e. it is inside (i.e. within) its interior. As defined in [DE-9IM](https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/DE-9IM).

sugarContent.title: sugarContent
sugarContent.description: The number of grams of sugar.

contentUrl.title: contentUrl
contentUrl.description: Actual bytes of the media object, for example the image file or video file.

accountId.title: accountId
accountId.description: The identifier for the account the payment will be applied to.

lodgingUnitType.title: lodgingUnitType
lodgingUnitType.description: Textual description of the unit type (including suite vs. room, size of bed, etc.).

paymentMethod.title: paymentMethod
paymentMethod.description: The name of the credit card or other method of payment for the order.

weight.title: weight
weight.description: The weight of the product or person.

nonProprietaryName.title: nonProprietaryName
nonProprietaryName.description: The generic name of this drug or supplement.

softwareRequirements.title: softwareRequirements
softwareRequirements.description: Component dependency requirements for application. This includes runtime environments and shared libraries that are not included in the application distribution package, but required to run the application (examples: DirectX, Java or .NET runtime).

material.title: material
material.description: A material that something is made from, e.g. leather, wool, cotton, paper.

doseUnit.title: doseUnit
doseUnit.description: The unit of the dose, e.g. 'mg'.

propertyID.title: propertyID
propertyID.description:
A commonly used identifier for the characteristic represented by the property, e.g. a manufacturer or a standard code for a property. propertyID can be
(1) a prefixed string, mainly meant to be used with standards for product properties; (2) a site-specific, non-prefixed string (e.g. the primary key of the property or the vendor-specific ID of the property), or (3)
a URL indicating the type of the property, either pointing to an external vocabulary, or a Web resource that describes the property (e.g. a glossary entry).
Standards bodies should promote a standard prefix for the identifiers of properties from their standards.

sharedContent.title: sharedContent
sharedContent.description: A CreativeWork such as an image, video, or audio clip shared as part of this posting.

guideline.title: guideline
guideline.description: A medical guideline related to this entity.

actors.title: actors
actors.description: An actor, e.g. in TV, radio, movie, video games etc. Actors can be associated with individual items or with a series, episode, clip.

wheelbase.title: wheelbase
wheelbase.description: The distance between the centers of the front and rear wheels.\n\nTypical unit code(s): CMT for centimeters, MTR for meters, INH for inches, FOT for foot/feet.

validFrom.title: validFrom
validFrom.description: The date when the item becomes valid.

membershipPointsEarned.title: membershipPointsEarned
membershipPointsEarned.description: The number of membership points earned by the member. If necessary, the unitText can be used to express the units the points are issued in. (E.g. stars, miles, etc.)

maximumIntake.title: maximumIntake
maximumIntake.description: Recommended intake of this supplement for a given population as defined by a specific recommending authority.

certificationIdentification.title: certificationIdentification
certificationIdentification.description: Identifier of a certification instance (as registered with an independent certification body). Typically this identifier can be used to consult and verify the certification instance. See also [gs1:certificationIdentification](https://www.gs1.org/voc/certificationIdentification).

passengerPriorityStatus.title: passengerPriorityStatus
passengerPriorityStatus.description: The priority status assigned to a passenger for security or boarding (e.g. FastTrack or Priority).

creator.title: creator
creator.description: The creator/author of this CreativeWork. This is the same as the Author property for CreativeWork.

legalStatus.title: legalStatus
legalStatus.description: The drug or supplement's legal status, including any controlled substance schedules that apply.

itemListElement.title: itemListElement
itemListElement.description:
For itemListElement values, you can use simple strings (e.g. "Peter", "Paul", "Mary"), existing entities, or use ListItem.

Text values are best if the elements in the list are plain strings. Existing entities are best for a simple, unordered list of existing things in your data. ListItem is used with ordered lists when you want to provide additional context about the element in that list or when the same item might be in different places in different lists.

Note: The order of elements in your mark-up is not sufficient for indicating the order or elements.  Use ListItem with a 'position' property in such cases.

subOrganization.title: subOrganization
subOrganization.description: A relationship between two organizations where the first includes the second, e.g., as a subsidiary. See also: the more specific 'department' property.

bookingTime.title: bookingTime
bookingTime.description: The date and time the reservation was booked.

currenciesAccepted.title: currenciesAccepted
currenciesAccepted.description: The currency accepted.\n\nUse standard formats: [ISO 4217 currency format](http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/ISO_4217), e.g. "USD"; [Ticker symbol](https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/List_of_cryptocurrencies) for cryptocurrencies, e.g. "BTC"; well known names for [Local Exchange Trading Systems](https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Local_exchange_trading_system) (LETS) and other currency types, e.g. "Ithaca HOUR".

relatedLink.title: relatedLink
relatedLink.description: A link related to this web page, for example to other related web pages.

jobLocation.title: jobLocation
jobLocation.description: A (typically single) geographic location associated with the job position.

recipient.title: recipient
recipient.description: A sub property of participant. The participant who is at the receiving end of the action.

boardingPolicy.title: boardingPolicy
boardingPolicy.description: The type of boarding policy used by the airline (e.g. zone-based or group-based).

includedRiskFactor.title: includedRiskFactor
includedRiskFactor.description: A modifiable or non-modifiable risk factor included in the calculation, e.g. age, coexisting condition.

datePosted.title: datePosted
datePosted.description: Publication date of an online listing.

dietFeatures.title: dietFeatures
dietFeatures.description: Nutritional information specific to the dietary plan. May include dietary recommendations on what foods to avoid, what foods to consume, and specific alterations/deviations from the USDA or other regulatory body's approved dietary guidelines.

contactlessPayment.title: contactlessPayment
contactlessPayment.description: A secure method for consumers to purchase products or services via debit, credit or smartcards by using RFID or NFC technology.

inventoryLevel.title: inventoryLevel
inventoryLevel.description: The current approximate inventory level for the item or items.

masthead.title: masthead
masthead.description: For a [[NewsMediaOrganization]], a link to the masthead page or a page listing top editorial management.

hasTiers.title: hasTiers
hasTiers.description: The tiers of a member program.

unsaturatedFatContent.title: unsaturatedFatContent
unsaturatedFatContent.description: The number of grams of unsaturated fat.

serviceType.title: serviceType
serviceType.description: The type of service being offered, e.g. veterans' benefits, emergency relief, etc.

feesAndCommissionsSpecification.title: feesAndCommissionsSpecification
feesAndCommissionsSpecification.description: Description of fees, commissions, and other terms applied either to a class of financial product, or by a financial service organization.

numberOfCredits.title: numberOfCredits
numberOfCredits.description: The number of credits or units awarded by a Course or required to complete an EducationalOccupationalProgram.

valueName.title: valueName
valueName.description: Indicates the name of the PropertyValueSpecification to be used in URL templates and form encoding in a manner analogous to HTML's input@name.

targetProduct.title: targetProduct
targetProduct.description: Target Operating System / Product to which the code applies.  If applies to several versions, just the product name can be used.

availableLanguage.title: availableLanguage
availableLanguage.description: A language someone may use with or at the item, service or place. Please use one of the language codes from the [IETF BCP 47 standard](http://tools.ietf.org/html/bcp47). See also [[inLanguage]].

yield.title: yield
yield.description: The quantity that results by performing instructions. For example, a paper airplane, 10 personalized candles.

coach.title: coach
coach.description: A person that acts in a coaching role for a sports team.

owns.title: owns
owns.description: Products owned by the organization or person.

employerOverview.title: employerOverview
employerOverview.description: A description of the employer, career opportunities and work environment for this position.

workTranslation.title: workTranslation
workTranslation.description: A work that is a translation of the content of this work. E.g. 西遊記 has an English workTranslation “Journey to the West”, a German workTranslation “Monkeys Pilgerfahrt” and a Vietnamese  translation Tây du ký bình khảo.

identifyingExam.title: identifyingExam
identifyingExam.description: A physical examination that can identify this sign.

tocContinuation.title: tocContinuation
tocContinuation.description: A [[HyperTocEntry]] can have a [[tocContinuation]] indicated, which is another [[HyperTocEntry]] that would be the default next item to play or render.

itemCondition.title: itemCondition
itemCondition.description: A predefined value from OfferItemCondition specifying the condition of the product or service, or the products or services included in the offer. Also used for product return policies to specify the condition of products accepted for returns.

geoCovers.title: geoCovers
geoCovers.description: Represents a relationship between two geometries (or the places they represent), relating a covering geometry to a covered geometry. "Every point of b is a point of (the interior or boundary of) a". As defined in [DE-9IM](https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/DE-9IM).

claimReviewed.title: claimReviewed
claimReviewed.description: A short summary of the specific claims reviewed in a ClaimReview.

clincalPharmacology.title: clincalPharmacology
clincalPharmacology.description: Description of the absorption and elimination of drugs, including their concentration (pharmacokinetics, pK) and biological effects (pharmacodynamics, pD).

byMonthWeek.title: byMonthWeek
byMonthWeek.description: Defines the week(s) of the month on which a recurring Event takes place. Specified as an Integer between 1-5. For clarity, byMonthWeek is best used in conjunction with byDay to indicate concepts like the first and third Mondays of a month.

activeIngredient.title: activeIngredient
activeIngredient.description: An active ingredient, typically chemical compounds and/or biologic substances.

discusses.title: discusses
discusses.description: Specifies the CreativeWork associated with the UserComment.

pickupTime.title: pickupTime
pickupTime.description: When a taxi will pick up a passenger or a rental car can be picked up.

serviceLocation.title: serviceLocation
serviceLocation.description: The location (e.g. civic structure, local business, etc.) where a person can go to access the service.

businessDays.title: businessDays
businessDays.description: Days of the week when the merchant typically operates, indicated via opening hours markup.

dependencies.title: dependencies
dependencies.description: Prerequisites needed to fulfill steps in article.

hasCredential.title: hasCredential
hasCredential.description: A credential awarded to the Person or Organization.

totalTime.title: totalTime
totalTime.description: The total time required to perform instructions or a direction (including time to prepare the supplies), in [ISO 8601 duration format](http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/ISO_8601).

relatedStructure.title: relatedStructure
relatedStructure.description: Related anatomical structure(s) that are not part of the system but relate or connect to it, such as vascular bundles associated with an organ system.

steeringPosition.title: steeringPosition
steeringPosition.description: The position of the steering wheel or similar device (mostly for cars).

numberOfBedrooms.title: numberOfBedrooms
numberOfBedrooms.description: The total integer number of bedrooms in a some [[Accommodation]], [[ApartmentComplex]] or [[FloorPlan]].

departureGate.title: departureGate
departureGate.description: Identifier of the flight's departure gate.

code.title: code
code.description: A medical code for the entity, taken from a controlled vocabulary or ontology such as ICD-9, DiseasesDB, MeSH, SNOMED-CT, RxNorm, etc.

trailerWeight.title: trailerWeight
trailerWeight.description:
The permitted weight of a trailer attached to the vehicle.

Typical unit code(s): KGM for kilogram, LBR for pound
* Note 1: You can indicate additional information in the [[name]] of the [[QuantitativeValue]] node.
* Note 2: You may also link to a [[QualitativeValue]] node that provides additional information using [[valueReference]].
* Note 3: Note that you can use [[minValue]] and [[maxValue]] to indicate ranges.

givenName.title: givenName
givenName.description: Given name. In the U.S., the first name of a Person.

spatial.title: spatial
spatial.description:
The "spatial" property can be used in cases when more specific properties
(e.g. [[locationCreated]], [[spatialCoverage]], [[contentLocation]]) are not known to be appropriate.

healthCondition.title: healthCondition
healthCondition.description: Specifying the health condition(s) of a patient, medical study, or other target audience.

accommodationCategory.title: accommodationCategory
accommodationCategory.description: Category of an [[Accommodation]], following real estate conventions, e.g. RESO (see [PropertySubType](https://ddwiki.reso.org/display/DDW17/PropertySubType+Field), and [PropertyType](https://ddwiki.reso.org/display/DDW17/PropertyType+Field) fields  for suggested values).

orderItemStatus.title: orderItemStatus
orderItemStatus.description: The current status of the order item.

inLanguage.title: inLanguage
inLanguage.description: The language of the content or performance or used in an action. Please use one of the language codes from the [IETF BCP 47 standard](http://tools.ietf.org/html/bcp47). See also [[availableLanguage]].

downPayment.title: downPayment
downPayment.description: a type of payment made in cash during the onset of the purchase of an expensive good/service. The payment typically represents only a percentage of the full purchase price.

musicGroupMember.title: musicGroupMember
musicGroupMember.description: A member of a music group—for example, John, Paul, George, or Ringo.

relatedDrug.title: relatedDrug
relatedDrug.description: Any other drug related to this one, for example commonly-prescribed alternatives.

dateRead.title: dateRead
dateRead.description: The date/time at which the message has been read by the recipient if a single recipient exists.

musicCompositionForm.title: musicCompositionForm
musicCompositionForm.description: The type of composition (e.g. overture, sonata, symphony, etc.).

subReservation.title: subReservation
subReservation.description: The individual reservations included in the package. Typically a repeated property.

relatedAnatomy.title: relatedAnatomy
relatedAnatomy.description: Anatomical systems or structures that relate to the superficial anatomy.

populationType.title: populationType
populationType.description: Indicates the populationType common to all members of a [[StatisticalPopulation]] or all cases within the scope of a [[StatisticalVariable]].

negativeNotes.title: negativeNotes
negativeNotes.description:
Provides negative considerations regarding something, most typically in pro/con lists for reviews (alongside [[positiveNotes]]). For symmetry 

In the case of a [[Review]], the property describes the [[itemReviewed]] from the perspective of the review; in the case of a [[Product]], the product itself is being described. Since product descriptions 
tend to emphasise positive claims, it may be relatively unusual to find [[negativeNotes]] used in this way. Nevertheless for the sake of symmetry, [[negativeNotes]] can be used on [[Product]].

The property values can be expressed either as unstructured text (repeated as necessary), or if ordered, as a list (in which case the most negative is at the beginning of the list).

partOfOrder.title: partOfOrder
partOfOrder.description: The overall order the items in this delivery were included in.

exerciseCourse.title: exerciseCourse
exerciseCourse.description: A sub property of location. The course where this action was taken.

contactOption.title: contactOption
contactOption.description: An option available on this contact point (e.g. a toll-free number or support for hearing-impaired callers).

floorSize.title: floorSize
floorSize.description:
The size of the accommodation, e.g. in square meter or squarefoot.
Typical unit code(s): MTK for square meter, FTK for square foot, or YDK for square yard.

busNumber.title: busNumber
busNumber.description: The unique identifier for the bus.

encodings.title: encodings
encodings.description: A media object that encodes this CreativeWork.

wordCount.title: wordCount
wordCount.description: The number of words in the text of the Article.

valueMinLength.title: valueMinLength
valueMinLength.description: Specifies the minimum allowed range for number of characters in a literal value.

applicationContact.title: applicationContact
applicationContact.description: Contact details for further information relevant to this job posting.

hasDefinedTerm.title: hasDefinedTerm
hasDefinedTerm.description: A Defined Term contained in this term set.

performers.title: performers
performers.description: The main performer or performers of the event—for example, a presenter, musician, or actor.

sku.title: sku
sku.description: The Stock Keeping Unit (SKU), i.e. a merchant-specific identifier for a product or service, or the product to which the offer refers.

temporalCoverage.title: temporalCoverage
temporalCoverage.description:
The temporalCoverage of a CreativeWork indicates the period that the content applies to, i.e. that it describes, either as a DateTime or as a textual string indicating a time period in [ISO 8601 time interval format](https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/ISO_8601#Time_intervals). In
      the case of a Dataset it will typically indicate the relevant time period in a precise notation (e.g. for a 2011 census dataset, the year 2011 would be written "2011/2012"). Other forms of content, e.g. ScholarlyArticle, Book, TVSeries or TVEpisode, may indicate their temporalCoverage in broader terms - textually or via well-known URL.
      Written works such as books may sometimes have precise temporal coverage too, e.g. a work set in 1939 - 1945 can be indicated in ISO 8601 interval format format via "1939/1945".

Open-ended date ranges can be written with ".." in place of the end date. For example, "2015-11/.." indicates a range beginning in November 2015 and with no specified final date. This is tentative and might be updated in future when ISO 8601 is officially updated.

applicableLocation.title: applicableLocation
applicableLocation.description: The location in which the status applies.

contactType.title: contactType
contactType.description: A person or organization can have different contact points, for different purposes. For example, a sales contact point, a PR contact point and so on. This property is used to specify the kind of contact point.

insertion.title: insertion
insertion.description: The place of attachment of a muscle, or what the muscle moves.

cvdFacilityId.title: cvdFacilityId
cvdFacilityId.description: Identifier of the NHSN facility that this data record applies to. Use [[cvdFacilityCounty]] to indicate the county. To provide other details, [[healthcareReportingData]] can be used on a [[Hospital]] entry.

isSimilarTo.title: isSimilarTo
isSimilarTo.description: A pointer to another, functionally similar product (or multiple products).

associatedMediaReview.title: associatedMediaReview
associatedMediaReview.description: An associated [[MediaReview]], related by specific common content, topic or claim. The expectation is that this property would be most typically used in cases where a single activity is conducting both claim reviews and media reviews, in which case [[relatedMediaReview]] would commonly be used on a [[ClaimReview]], while [[relatedClaimReview]] would be used on [[MediaReview]].

branch.title: branch
branch.description: The branches that delineate from the nerve bundle. Not to be confused with [[branchOf]].

image.title: image
image.description: An image of the item. This can be a [[URL]] or a fully described [[ImageObject]].

artist.title: artist
artist.description:
The primary artist for a work
    	in a medium other than pencils or digital line art--for example, if the
    	primary artwork is done in watercolors or digital paints.

branchCode.title: branchCode
branchCode.description: A short textual code (also called "store code") that uniquely identifies a place of business. The code is typically assigned by the parentOrganization and used in structured URLs.\n\nFor example, in the URL http://www.starbucks.co.uk/store-locator/etc/detail/3047 the code "3047" is a branchCode for a particular branch.

mealService.title: mealService
mealService.description: Description of the meals that will be provided or available for purchase.

screenCount.title: screenCount
screenCount.description: The number of screens in the movie theater.

gameServer.title: gameServer
gameServer.description: The server on which  it is possible to play the game.

streetAddress.title: streetAddress
streetAddress.description: The street address. For example, 1600 Amphitheatre Pkwy.

hasMenuSection.title: hasMenuSection
hasMenuSection.description: A subgrouping of the menu (by dishes, course, serving time period, etc.).

associatedDisease.title: associatedDisease
associatedDisease.description: Disease associated to this BioChemEntity. Such disease can be a MedicalCondition or a URL. If you want to add an evidence supporting the association, please use PropertyValue.

enginePower.title: enginePower
enginePower.description:
The power of the vehicle's engine.
    Typical unit code(s): KWT for kilowatt, BHP for brake horsepower, N12 for metric horsepower (PS, with 1 PS = 735,49875 W)

* Note 1: There are many different ways of measuring an engine's power. For an overview, see  [http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Horsepower#Engine\_power\_test\_codes](http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Horsepower#Engine_power_test_codes).
* Note 2: You can link to information about how the given value has been determined using the [[valueReference]] property.
* Note 3: You can use [[minValue]] and [[maxValue]] to indicate ranges.

handlingTime.title: handlingTime
handlingTime.description: The typical delay between the receipt of the order and the goods either leaving the warehouse or being prepared for pickup, in case the delivery method is on site pickup. Typical properties: minValue, maxValue, unitCode (d for DAY).  This is by common convention assumed to mean business days (if a unitCode is used, coded as "d"), i.e. only counting days when the business normally operates.

item.title: item
item.description: An entity represented by an entry in a list or data feed (e.g. an 'artist' in a list of 'artists').

secondaryPrevention.title: secondaryPrevention
secondaryPrevention.description: A preventative therapy used to prevent reoccurrence of the medical condition after an initial episode of the condition.

loanMortgageMandateAmount.title: loanMortgageMandateAmount
loanMortgageMandateAmount.description: Amount of mortgage mandate that can be converted into a proper mortgage at a later stage.

riskFactor.title: riskFactor
riskFactor.description: A modifiable or non-modifiable factor that increases the risk of a patient contracting this condition, e.g. age,  coexisting condition.

isGift.title: isGift
isGift.description: Indicates whether the offer was accepted as a gift for someone other than the buyer.

productSupported.title: productSupported
productSupported.description: The product or service this support contact point is related to (such as product support for a particular product line). This can be a specific product or product line (e.g. "iPhone") or a general category of products or services (e.g. "smartphones").

gameAvailabilityType.title: gameAvailabilityType
gameAvailabilityType.description: Indicates the availability type of the game content associated with this action, such as whether it is a full version or a demo.

firstPerformance.title: firstPerformance
firstPerformance.description: The date and place the work was first performed.

legislationPassedBy.title: legislationPassedBy
legislationPassedBy.description: The person or organization that originally passed or made the law: typically parliament (for primary legislation) or government (for secondary legislation). This indicates the "legal author" of the law, as opposed to its physical author.

eligibleTransactionVolume.title: eligibleTransactionVolume
eligibleTransactionVolume.description: The transaction volume, in a monetary unit, for which the offer or price specification is valid, e.g. for indicating a minimal purchasing volume, to express free shipping above a certain order volume, or to limit the acceptance of credit cards to purchases to a certain minimal amount.

userInteractionCount.title: userInteractionCount
userInteractionCount.description: The number of interactions for the CreativeWork using the WebSite or SoftwareApplication.

vehicleIdentificationNumber.title: vehicleIdentificationNumber
vehicleIdentificationNumber.description: The Vehicle Identification Number (VIN) is a unique serial number used by the automotive industry to identify individual motor vehicles.

ownedThrough.title: ownedThrough
ownedThrough.description: The date and time of giving up ownership on the product.

numChildren.title: numChildren
numChildren.description: The number of children staying in the unit.

regionDrained.title: regionDrained
regionDrained.description: The anatomical or organ system drained by this vessel; generally refers to a specific part of an organ.

travelBans.title: travelBans
travelBans.description: Information about travel bans, e.g. in the context of a pandemic.

director.title: director
director.description: A director of e.g. TV, radio, movie, video gaming etc. content, or of an event. Directors can be associated with individual items or with a series, episode, clip.

significance.title: significance
significance.description: The significance associated with the superficial anatomy; as an example, how characteristics of the superficial anatomy can suggest underlying medical conditions or courses of treatment.

conditionsOfAccess.title: conditionsOfAccess
conditionsOfAccess.description: Conditions that affect the availability of, or method(s) of access to, an item. Typically used for real world items such as an [[ArchiveComponent]] held by an [[ArchiveOrganization]]. This property is not suitable for use as a general Web access control mechanism. It is expressed only in natural language.\n\nFor example "Available by appointment from the Reading Room" or "Accessible only from logged-in accounts ".

equal.title: equal
equal.description: This ordering relation for qualitative values indicates that the subject is equal to the object.

seeks.title: seeks
seeks.description: A pointer to products or services sought by the organization or person (demand).

addressLocality.title: addressLocality
addressLocality.description: The locality in which the street address is, and which is in the region. For example, Mountain View.

repetitions.title: repetitions
repetitions.description: Number of times one should repeat the activity.

costOrigin.title: costOrigin
costOrigin.description: Additional details to capture the origin of the cost data. For example, 'Medicare Part B'.

responsibilities.title: responsibilities
responsibilities.description: Responsibilities associated with this role or Occupation.

codeRepository.title: codeRepository
codeRepository.description: Link to the repository where the un-compiled, human readable code and related code is located (SVN, GitHub, CodePlex).

containsPlace.title: containsPlace
containsPlace.description: The basic containment relation between a place and another that it contains.

season.title: season
season.description: A season in a media series.

numberOfItems.title: numberOfItems
numberOfItems.description: The number of items in an ItemList. Note that some descriptions might not fully describe all items in a list (e.g., multi-page pagination); in such cases, the numberOfItems would be for the entire list.

sportsActivityLocation.title: sportsActivityLocation
sportsActivityLocation.description: A sub property of location. The sports activity location where this action occurred.

applicationCategory.title: applicationCategory
applicationCategory.description: Type of software application, e.g. 'Game, Multimedia'.

printColumn.title: printColumn
printColumn.description: The number of the column in which the NewsArticle appears in the print edition.

byMonth.title: byMonth
byMonth.description: Defines the month(s) of the year on which a recurring [[Event]] takes place. Specified as an [[Integer]] between 1-12. January is 1.

employmentType.title: employmentType
employmentType.description: Type of employment (e.g. full-time, part-time, contract, temporary, seasonal, internship).

study.title: study
study.description: A medical study or trial related to this entity.

serviceOutput.title: serviceOutput
serviceOutput.description: The tangible thing generated by the service, e.g. a passport, permit, etc.

structuralClass.title: structuralClass
structuralClass.description: The name given to how bone physically connects to each other.

costPerUnit.title: costPerUnit
costPerUnit.description: The cost per unit of the drug.

refundType.title: refundType
refundType.description: A refund type, from an enumerated list.

step.title: step
step.description: A single step item (as HowToStep, text, document, video, etc.) or a HowToSection.

usesHealthPlanIdStandard.title: usesHealthPlanIdStandard
usesHealthPlanIdStandard.description: The standard for interpreting the Plan ID. The preferred is "HIOS". See the Centers for Medicare & Medicaid Services for more details.

firstAppearance.title: firstAppearance
firstAppearance.description: Indicates the first known occurrence of a [[Claim]] in some [[CreativeWork]].

netWorth.title: netWorth
netWorth.description: The total financial value of the person as calculated by subtracting assets from liabilities.

namedPosition.title: namedPosition
namedPosition.description: A position played, performed or filled by a person or organization, as part of an organization. For example, an athlete in a SportsTeam might play in the position named 'Quarterback'.

geoOverlaps.title: geoOverlaps
geoOverlaps.description: Represents a relationship between two geometries (or the places they represent), relating a geometry to another that geospatially overlaps it, i.e. they have some but not all points in common. As defined in [DE-9IM](https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/DE-9IM).

runtimePlatform.title: runtimePlatform
runtimePlatform.description: Runtime platform or script interpreter dependencies (example: Java v1, Python 2.3, .NET Framework 3.0).

intensity.title: intensity
intensity.description: Quantitative measure gauging the degree of force involved in the exercise, for example, heartbeats per minute. May include the velocity of the movement.

engineDisplacement.title: engineDisplacement
engineDisplacement.description:
The volume swept by all of the pistons inside the cylinders of an internal combustion engine in a single movement. 

Typical unit code(s): CMQ for cubic centimeter, LTR for liters, INQ for cubic inches
* Note 1: You can link to information about how the given value has been determined using the [[valueReference]] property.
* Note 2: You can use [[minValue]] and [[maxValue]] to indicate ranges.

speakable.title: speakable
speakable.description:
Indicates sections of a Web page that are particularly 'speakable' in the sense of being highlighted as being especially appropriate for text-to-speech conversion. Other sections of a page may also be usefully spoken in particular circumstances; the 'speakable' property serves to indicate the parts most likely to be generally useful for speech.

The *speakable* property can be repeated an arbitrary number of times, with three kinds of possible 'content-locator' values:

1.) *id-value* URL references - uses *id-value* of an element in the page being annotated. The simplest use of *speakable* has (potentially relative) URL values, referencing identified sections of the document concerned.

2.) CSS Selectors - addresses content in the annotated page, e.g. via class attribute. Use the [[cssSelector]] property.

3.)  XPaths - addresses content via XPaths (assuming an XML view of the content). Use the [[xpath]] property.


For more sophisticated markup of speakable sections beyond simple ID references, either CSS selectors or XPath expressions to pick out document section(s) as speakable. For this
we define a supporting type, [[SpeakableSpecification]]  which is defined to be a possible value of the *speakable* property.

agent.title: agent
agent.description: The direct performer or driver of the action (animate or inanimate). E.g. *John* wrote a book.

requiredQuantity.title: requiredQuantity
requiredQuantity.description: The required quantity of the item(s).

cvdNumBeds.title: cvdNumBeds
cvdNumBeds.description: numbeds - HOSPITAL INPATIENT BEDS: Inpatient beds, including all staffed, licensed, and overflow (surge) beds used for inpatients.

reviewBody.title: reviewBody
reviewBody.description: The actual body of the review.

seatNumber.title: seatNumber
seatNumber.description: The location of the reserved seat (e.g., 27).

fatContent.title: fatContent
fatContent.description: The number of grams of fat.

countriesNotSupported.title: countriesNotSupported
countriesNotSupported.description: Countries for which the application is not supported. You can also provide the two-letter ISO 3166-1 alpha-2 country code.

temporal.title: temporal
temporal.description:
The "temporal" property can be used in cases where more specific properties
(e.g. [[temporalCoverage]], [[dateCreated]], [[dateModified]], [[datePublished]]) are not known to be appropriate.

underName.title: underName
underName.description: The person or organization the reservation or ticket is for.

roleName.title: roleName
roleName.description: A role played, performed or filled by a person or organization. For example, the team of creators for a comic book might fill the roles named 'inker', 'penciller', and 'letterer'; or an athlete in a SportsTeam might play in the position named 'Quarterback'.

cashBack.title: cashBack
cashBack.description: A cardholder benefit that pays the cardholder a small percentage of their net expenditures.

artform.title: artform
artform.description: e.g. Painting, Drawing, Sculpture, Print, Photograph, Assemblage, Collage, etc.

isPartOf.title: isPartOf
