isPartOf.description: Indicates an item or CreativeWork that this item, or CreativeWork (in some sense), is part of.

serviceArea.title: serviceArea
serviceArea.description: The geographic area where the service is provided.

commentTime.title: commentTime
commentTime.description: The time at which the UserComment was made.

activityFrequency.title: activityFrequency
activityFrequency.description: How often one should engage in the activity.

gameItem.title: gameItem
gameItem.description: An item is an object within the game world that can be collected by a player or, occasionally, a non-player character.

includesObject.title: includesObject
includesObject.description: This links to a node or nodes indicating the exact quantity of the products included in  an [[Offer]] or [[ProductCollection]].

availableTest.title: availableTest
availableTest.description: A diagnostic test or procedure offered by this lab.

hasGS1DigitalLink.title: hasGS1DigitalLink
hasGS1DigitalLink.description:
The GS1 digital link associated with the object. This URL should conform to the particular requirements of digital links. The link should only contain the Application Identifiers (AIs) that are relevant for the entity being annotated, for instance a [[Product]] or an [[Organization]], and for the correct granularity. In particular, for products:
  • A Digital Link that contains a serial number (AI 21) should only be present on instances of [[IndividualProduct]]
  • A Digital Link that contains a lot number (AI 10) should be annotated as [[SomeProduct]] if only products from that lot are sold, or [[IndividualProduct]] if there is only a specific product.
  • A Digital Link that contains a global model number (AI 8013) should be attached to a [[Product]] or a [[ProductModel]].
Other item types should be adapted similarly.

application.title: application
application.description: An application that can complete the request.

ingredients.title: ingredients
ingredients.description: A single ingredient used in the recipe, e.g. sugar, flour or garlic.

musicalKey.title: musicalKey
musicalKey.description: The key, mode, or scale this composition uses.

experienceInPlaceOfEducation.title: experienceInPlaceOfEducation
experienceInPlaceOfEducation.description: Indicates whether a [[JobPosting]] will accept experience (as indicated by [[OccupationalExperienceRequirements]]) in place of its formal educational qualifications (as indicated by [[educationRequirements]]). If true, indicates that satisfying one of these requirements is sufficient.

abridged.title: abridged
abridged.description: Indicates whether the book is an abridged edition.

accessibilityControl.title: accessibilityControl
accessibilityControl.description: Identifies input methods that are sufficient to fully control the described resource. Values should be drawn from the [approved vocabulary](https://www.w3.org/2021/a11y-discov-vocab/latest/#accessibilityControl-vocabulary).

ownedFrom.title: ownedFrom
ownedFrom.description: The date and time of obtaining the product.

httpMethod.title: httpMethod
httpMethod.description: An HTTP method that specifies the appropriate HTTP method for a request to an HTTP EntryPoint. Values are capitalized strings as used in HTTP.

vehicleSpecialUsage.title: vehicleSpecialUsage
vehicleSpecialUsage.description: Indicates whether the vehicle has been used for special purposes, like commercial rental, driving school, or as a taxi. The legislation in many countries requires this information to be revealed when offering a car for sale.

fuelCapacity.title: fuelCapacity
fuelCapacity.description: The capacity of the fuel tank or in the case of electric cars, the battery. If there are multiple components for storage, this should indicate the total of all storage of the same type.\n\nTypical unit code(s): LTR for liters, GLL of US gallons, GLI for UK / imperial gallons, AMH for ampere-hours (for electrical vehicles).

hasCertification.title: hasCertification
hasCertification.description: Certification information about a product, organization, service, place, or person.

longitude.title: longitude
longitude.description: The longitude of a location. For example ```-122.08585``` ([WGS 84](https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/World_Geodetic_System)).

question.title: question
question.description: A sub property of object. A question.

hasEnergyEfficiencyCategory.title: hasEnergyEfficiencyCategory
hasEnergyEfficiencyCategory.description: Defines the energy efficiency Category (which could be either a rating out of range of values or a yes/no certification) for a product according to an international energy efficiency standard.

lodgingUnitDescription.title: lodgingUnitDescription
lodgingUnitDescription.description: A full description of the lodging unit.

embeddedTextCaption.title: embeddedTextCaption
embeddedTextCaption.description: Represents textual captioning from a [[MediaObject]], e.g. text of a 'meme'.

significantLinks.title: significantLinks
significantLinks.description: The most significant URLs on the page. Typically, these are the non-navigation links that are clicked on the most.

orderDelivery.title: orderDelivery
orderDelivery.description: The delivery of the parcel related to this order or order item.

hasAdultConsideration.title: hasAdultConsideration
hasAdultConsideration.description: Used to tag an item to be intended or suitable for consumption or use by adults only.

musicReleaseFormat.title: musicReleaseFormat
musicReleaseFormat.description: Format of this release (the type of recording media used, i.e. compact disc, digital media, LP, etc.).

hasOccupation.title: hasOccupation
hasOccupation.description: The Person's occupation. For past professions, use Role for expressing dates.

termsPerYear.title: termsPerYear
termsPerYear.description: The number of times terms of study are offered per year. Semesters and quarters are common units for term. For example, if the student can only take 2 semesters for the program in one year, then termsPerYear should be 2.

recognizedBy.title: recognizedBy
recognizedBy.description: An organization that acknowledges the validity, value or utility of a credential. Note: recognition may include a process of quality assurance or accreditation.

linkRelationship.title: linkRelationship
linkRelationship.description: Indicates the relationship type of a Web link.

meetsEmissionStandard.title: meetsEmissionStandard
meetsEmissionStandard.description: Indicates that the vehicle meets the respective emission standard.

editor.title: editor
editor.description: Specifies the Person who edited the CreativeWork.

strengthValue.title: strengthValue
strengthValue.description: The value of an active ingredient's strength, e.g. 325.

highPrice.title: highPrice
highPrice.description:
The highest price of all offers available.

Usage guidelines:

* Use values from 0123456789 (Unicode 'DIGIT ZERO' (U+0030) to 'DIGIT NINE' (U+0039)) rather than superficially similar Unicode symbols.
* Use '.' (Unicode 'FULL STOP' (U+002E)) rather than ',' to indicate a decimal point. Avoid using these symbols as a readability separator.

healthPlanId.title: healthPlanId
healthPlanId.description: The 14-character, HIOS-generated Plan ID number. (Plan IDs must be unique, even across different markets.)

claimInterpreter.title: claimInterpreter
claimInterpreter.description: For a [[Claim]] interpreted from [[MediaObject]] content, the [[interpretedAsClaim]] property can be used to indicate a claim contained, implied or refined from the content of a [[MediaObject]].

isAccessoryOrSparePartFor.title: isAccessoryOrSparePartFor
isAccessoryOrSparePartFor.description: A pointer to another product (or multiple products) for which this product is an accessory or spare part.

hoursAvailable.title: hoursAvailable
hoursAvailable.description: The hours during which this service or contact is available.

hasMolecularFunction.title: hasMolecularFunction
hasMolecularFunction.description: Molecular function performed by this BioChemEntity; please use PropertyValue if you want to include any evidence.

familyName.title: familyName
familyName.description: Family name. In the U.S., the last name of a Person.

billingStart.title: billingStart
billingStart.description: Specifies after how much time this price (or price component) becomes valid and billing starts. Can be used, for example, to model a price increase after the first year of a subscription. The unit of measurement is specified by the unitCode property.

maxValue.title: maxValue
maxValue.description: The upper value of some characteristic or property.

programName.title: programName
programName.description: The program providing the membership. It is preferable to use [:program](https://schema.org/program) instead.

target.title: target
target.description: Indicates a target EntryPoint, or url, for an Action.

pregnancyWarning.title: pregnancyWarning
pregnancyWarning.description: Any precaution, guidance, contraindication, etc. related to this drug's use during pregnancy.

addOn.title: addOn
addOn.description: An additional offer that can only be obtained in combination with the first base offer (e.g. supplements and extensions that are available for a surcharge).

chemicalRole.title: chemicalRole
chemicalRole.description: A role played by the BioChemEntity within a chemical context.

departureAirport.title: departureAirport
departureAirport.description: The airport where the flight originates.

announcementLocation.title: announcementLocation
announcementLocation.description: Indicates a specific [[CivicStructure]] or [[LocalBusiness]] associated with the SpecialAnnouncement. For example, a specific testing facility or business with special opening hours. For a larger geographic region like a quarantine of an entire region, use [[spatialCoverage]].

cvdNumC19HOPats.title: cvdNumC19HOPats
cvdNumC19HOPats.description: numc19hopats - HOSPITAL ONSET: Patients hospitalized in an NHSN inpatient care location with onset of suspected or confirmed COVID-19 14 or more days after hospitalization.

experienceRequirements.title: experienceRequirements
experienceRequirements.description: Description of skills and experience needed for the position or Occupation.

bankAccountType.title: bankAccountType
bankAccountType.description: The type of a bank account.

creditedTo.title: creditedTo
creditedTo.description: The group the release is credited to if different than the byArtist. For example, Red and Blue is credited to "Stefani Germanotta Band", but by Lady Gaga.

pattern.title: pattern
pattern.description: A pattern that something has, for example 'polka dot', 'striped', 'Canadian flag'. Values are typically expressed as text, although links to controlled value schemes are also supported.

paymentDue.title: paymentDue
paymentDue.description: The date that payment is due.

gettingTestedInfo.title: gettingTestedInfo
gettingTestedInfo.description: Information about getting tested (for a [[MedicalCondition]]), e.g. in the context of a pandemic.

healthPlanCostSharing.title: healthPlanCostSharing
healthPlanCostSharing.description: The costs to the patient for services under this network or formulary.

bookingAgent.title: bookingAgent
bookingAgent.description: 'bookingAgent' is an out-dated term indicating a 'broker' that serves as a booking agent.

drugClass.title: drugClass
drugClass.description: The class of drug this belongs to (e.g., statins).

recordingOf.title: recordingOf
recordingOf.description: The composition this track is a recording of.

subTrip.title: subTrip
subTrip.description: Identifies a [[Trip]] that is a subTrip of this Trip.  For example Day 1, Day 2, etc. of a multi-day trip.

exceptDate.title: exceptDate
exceptDate.description:
Defines a [[Date]] or [[DateTime]] during which a scheduled [[Event]] will not take place. The property allows exceptions to
      a [[Schedule]] to be specified. If an exception is specified as a [[DateTime]] then only the event that would have started at that specific date and time
      should be excluded from the schedule. If an exception is specified as a [[Date]] then any event that is scheduled for that 24 hour period should be
      excluded from the schedule. This allows a whole day to be excluded from the schedule without having to itemise every scheduled event.

referenceQuantity.title: referenceQuantity
referenceQuantity.description: The reference quantity for which a certain price applies, e.g. 1 EUR per 4 kWh of electricity. This property is a replacement for unitOfMeasurement for the advanced cases where the price does not relate to a standard unit.

fiberContent.title: fiberContent
fiberContent.description: The number of grams of fiber.

billingIncrement.title: billingIncrement
billingIncrement.description: This property specifies the minimal quantity and rounding increment that will be the basis for the billing. The unit of measurement is specified by the unitCode property.

maximumEnrollment.title: maximumEnrollment
maximumEnrollment.description: The maximum number of students who may be enrolled in the program.

playerType.title: playerType
playerType.description: Player type required—for example, Flash or Silverlight.

directApply.title: directApply
directApply.description: Indicates whether an [[url]] that is associated with a [[JobPosting]] enables direct application for the job, via the posting website. A job posting is considered to have directApply of [[True]] if an application process for the specified job can be directly initiated via the url(s) given (noting that e.g. multiple internet domains might nevertheless be involved at an implementation level). A value of [[False]] is appropriate if there is no clear path to applying directly online for the specified job, navigating directly from the JobPosting url(s) supplied.

hasMerchantReturnPolicy.title: hasMerchantReturnPolicy
hasMerchantReturnPolicy.description: Specifies a MerchantReturnPolicy that may be applicable.

openingHours.title: openingHours
openingHours.description: The general opening hours for a business. Opening hours can be specified as a weekly time range, starting with days, then times per day. Multiple days can be listed with commas ',' separating each day. Day or time ranges are specified using a hyphen '-'. * Days are specified using the following two-letter combinations: ```Mo```, ```Tu```, ```We```, ```Th```, ```Fr```, ```Sa```, ```Su```. * Times are specified using 24:00 format. For example, 3pm is specified as ```15:00```, 10am as ```10:00```. * Here is an example: <time itemprop="openingHours" datetime="Tu,Th 16:00-20:00">Tuesdays and Thursdays 4-8pm</time>. * If a business is open 7 days a week, then it can be specified as <time itemprop="openingHours" datetime="Mo-Su">Monday through Sunday, all day</time>.

containsSeason.title: containsSeason
containsSeason.description: A season that is part of the media series.

arrivalPlatform.title: arrivalPlatform
arrivalPlatform.description: The platform where the train arrives.

jobLocationType.title: jobLocationType
jobLocationType.description: A description of the job location (e.g. TELECOMMUTE for telecommute jobs).

biologicalRole.title: biologicalRole
biologicalRole.description: A role played by the BioChemEntity within a biological context.

checkoutTime.title: checkoutTime
checkoutTime.description: The latest someone may check out of a lodging establishment.

learningResourceType.title: learningResourceType
learningResourceType.description: The predominant type or kind characterizing the learning resource. For example, 'presentation', 'handout'.

originalMediaContextDescription.title: originalMediaContextDescription
originalMediaContextDescription.description: Describes, in a [[MediaReview]] when dealing with [[DecontextualizedContent]], background information that can contribute to better interpretation of the [[MediaObject]].

borrower.title: borrower
borrower.description: A sub property of participant. The person that borrows the object being lent.

numberOfAirbags.title: numberOfAirbags
numberOfAirbags.description: The number or type of airbags in the vehicle.

endOffset.title: endOffset
endOffset.description: The end time of the clip expressed as the number of seconds from the beginning of the work.

costCategory.title: costCategory
costCategory.description: The category of cost, such as wholesale, retail, reimbursement cap, etc.

stage.title: stage
stage.description: The stage of the condition, if applicable.

numberOfEmployees.title: numberOfEmployees
numberOfEmployees.description: The number of employees in an organization, e.g. business.

isResizable.title: isResizable
isResizable.description: Whether the 3DModel allows resizing. For example, room layout applications often do not allow 3DModel elements to be resized to reflect reality.

follows.title: follows
follows.description: The most generic uni-directional social relation.

subStageSuffix.title: subStageSuffix
subStageSuffix.description: The substage, e.g. 'a' for Stage IIIa.

opens.title: opens
opens.description: The opening hour of the place or service on the given day(s) of the week.

acceptedOffer.title: acceptedOffer
acceptedOffer.description: The offer(s) -- e.g., product, quantity and price combinations -- included in the order.

dayOfWeek.title: dayOfWeek
dayOfWeek.description: The day of the week for which these opening hours are valid.

subTest.title: subTest
subTest.description: A component test of the panel.

offerCount.title: offerCount
offerCount.description: The number of offers for the product.

publicationType.title: publicationType
publicationType.description: The type of the medical article, taken from the US NLM MeSH publication type catalog. See also [MeSH documentation](http://www.nlm.nih.gov/mesh/pubtypes.html).

alumniOf.title: alumniOf
alumniOf.description: An organization that the person is an alumni of.

aggregateRating.title: aggregateRating
aggregateRating.description: The overall rating, based on a collection of reviews or ratings, of the item.

jobBenefits.title: jobBenefits
jobBenefits.description: Description of benefits associated with the job.

broadcastServiceTier.title: broadcastServiceTier
broadcastServiceTier.description: The type of service required to have access to the channel (e.g. Standard or Premium).

legislationJurisdiction.title: legislationJurisdiction
legislationJurisdiction.description: The jurisdiction from which the legislation originates.

mediaItemAppearance.title: mediaItemAppearance
mediaItemAppearance.description: In the context of a [[MediaReview]], indicates specific media item(s) that are grouped using a [[MediaReviewItem]].

priceValidUntil.title: priceValidUntil
priceValidUntil.description: The date after which the price is no longer available.

about.title: about
about.description: The subject matter of the content.

aspect.title: aspect
aspect.description: An aspect of medical practice that is considered on the page, such as 'diagnosis', 'treatment', 'causes', 'prognosis', 'etiology', 'epidemiology', etc.

legislationLegalForce.title: legislationLegalForce
legislationLegalForce.description: Whether the legislation is currently in force, not in force, or partially in force.

legislationResponsible.title: legislationResponsible
legislationResponsible.description: An individual or organization that has some kind of responsibility for the legislation. Typically the ministry who is/was in charge of elaborating the legislation, or the adressee for potential questions about the legislation once it is published.

starRating.title: starRating
starRating.description: An official rating for a lodging business or food establishment, e.g. from national associations or standards bodies. Use the author property to indicate the rating organization, e.g. as an Organization with name such as (e.g. HOTREC, DEHOGA, WHR, or Hotelstars).

deathPlace.title: deathPlace
deathPlace.description: The place where the person died.

map.title: map
map.description: A URL to a map of the place.

associatedPathophysiology.title: associatedPathophysiology
associatedPathophysiology.description: If applicable, a description of the pathophysiology associated with the anatomical system, including potential abnormal changes in the mechanical, physical, and biochemical functions of the system.

availability.title: availability
availability.description: The availability of this item—for example In stock, Out of stock, Pre-order, etc.

scheduleTimezone.title: scheduleTimezone
scheduleTimezone.description: Indicates the timezone for which the time(s) indicated in the [[Schedule]] are given. The value provided should be among those listed in the IANA Time Zone Database.

assembly.title: assembly
assembly.description: Library file name, e.g., mscorlib.dll, system.web.dll.

orderItemNumber.title: orderItemNumber
orderItemNumber.description: The identifier of the order item.

numberOfSeasons.title: numberOfSeasons
numberOfSeasons.description: The number of seasons in this series.

dateReceived.title: dateReceived
dateReceived.description: The date/time the message was received if a single recipient exists.

startTime.title: startTime
startTime.description: The startTime of something. For a reserved event or service (e.g. FoodEstablishmentReservation), the time that it is expected to start. For actions that span a period of time, when the action was performed. E.g. John wrote a book from *January* to December. For media, including audio and video, it's the time offset of the start of a clip within a larger file.\n\nNote that Event uses startDate/endDate instead of startTime/endTime, even when describing dates with times. This situation may be clarified in future revisions.

healthPlanCoinsuranceOption.title: healthPlanCoinsuranceOption
healthPlanCoinsuranceOption.description: Whether the coinsurance applies before or after deductible, etc. TODO: Is this a closed set?

rxcui.title: rxcui
rxcui.description: The RxCUI drug identifier from RXNORM.

publication.title: publication
publication.description: A publication event associated with the item.

availableThrough.title: availableThrough
availableThrough.description: After this date, the item will no longer be available for pickup.

proficiencyLevel.title: proficiencyLevel
proficiencyLevel.description: Proficiency needed for this content; expected values: 'Beginner', 'Expert'.

recognizingAuthority.title: recognizingAuthority
recognizingAuthority.description: If applicable, the organization that officially recognizes this entity as part of its endorsed system of medicine.

fuelConsumption.title: fuelConsumption
fuelConsumption.description:
The amount of fuel consumed for traveling a particular distance or temporal duration with the given vehicle (e.g. liters per 100 km).

* Note 1: There are unfortunately no standard unit codes for liters per 100 km.  Use [[unitText]] to indicate the unit of measurement, e.g. L/100 km.
* Note 2: There are two ways of indicating the fuel consumption, [[fuelConsumption]] (e.g. 8 liters per 100 km) and [[fuelEfficiency]] (e.g. 30 miles per gallon). They are reciprocal.
* Note 3: Often, the absolute value is useful only when related to driving speed ("at 80 km/h") or usage pattern ("city traffic"). You can use [[valueReference]] to link the value for the fuel consumption to another value.

hasMeasurement.title: hasMeasurement
hasMeasurement.description: A measurement of an item, For example, the inseam of pants, the wheel size of a bicycle, the gauge of a screw, or the carbon footprint measured for certification by an authority. Usually an exact measurement, but can also be a range of measurements for adjustable products, for example belts and ski bindings.

broadcastOfEvent.title: broadcastOfEvent
broadcastOfEvent.description: The event being broadcast such as a sporting event or awards ceremony.

copyrightYear.title: copyrightYear
copyrightYear.description: The year during which the claimed copyright for the CreativeWork was first asserted.

interactivityType.title: interactivityType
interactivityType.description: The predominant mode of learning supported by the learning resource. Acceptable values are 'active', 'expositive', or 'mixed'.

knowsLanguage.title: knowsLanguage
knowsLanguage.description: Of a [[Person]], and less typically of an [[Organization]], to indicate a known language. We do not distinguish skill levels or reading/writing/speaking/signing here. Use language codes from the [IETF BCP 47 standard](http://tools.ietf.org/html/bcp47).

departureBoatTerminal.title: departureBoatTerminal
departureBoatTerminal.description: The terminal or port from which the boat departs.

phoneticText.title: phoneticText
phoneticText.description: Representation of a text [[textValue]] using the specified [[speechToTextMarkup]]. For example the city name of Houston in IPA: /ˈhjuːstən/.

authenticator.title: authenticator
authenticator.description: The Organization responsible for authenticating the user's subscription. For example, many media apps require a cable/satellite provider to authenticate your subscription before playing media.

affiliation.title: affiliation
affiliation.description: An organization that this person is affiliated with. For example, a school/university, a club, or a team.

arrivalStation.title: arrivalStation
arrivalStation.description: The station where the train trip ends.

targetDescription.title: targetDescription
targetDescription.description: The description of a node in an established educational framework.

inChI.title: inChI
inChI.description: Non-proprietary identifier for molecular entity that can be used in printed and electronic data sources thus enabling easier linking of diverse data compilations.

hasMenu.title: hasMenu
hasMenu.description: Either the actual menu as a structured representation, as text, or a URL of the menu.

cvdNumICUBeds.title: cvdNumICUBeds
cvdNumICUBeds.description: numicubeds - ICU BEDS: Total number of staffed inpatient intensive care unit (ICU) beds.

currency.title: currency
currency.description: The currency in which the monetary amount is expressed.\n\nUse standard formats: [ISO 4217 currency format](http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/ISO_4217), e.g. "USD"; [Ticker symbol](https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/List_of_cryptocurrencies) for cryptocurrencies, e.g. "BTC"; well known names for [Local Exchange Trading Systems](https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Local_exchange_trading_system) (LETS) and other currency types, e.g. "Ithaca HOUR".

recommendationStrength.title: recommendationStrength
recommendationStrength.description: Strength of the guideline's recommendation (e.g. 'class I').

byDay.title: byDay
byDay.description: Defines the day(s) of the week on which a recurring [[Event]] takes place. May be specified using either [[DayOfWeek]], or alternatively [[Text]] conforming to iCal's syntax for byDay recurrence rules.

knownVehicleDamages.title: knownVehicleDamages
knownVehicleDamages.description: A textual description of known damages, both repaired and unrepaired.

value.title: value
value.description:
The value of a [[QuantitativeValue]] (including [[Observation]]) or property value node.

* For [[QuantitativeValue]] and [[MonetaryAmount]], the recommended type for values is 'Number'.
* For [[PropertyValue]], it can be 'Text', 'Number', 'Boolean', or 'StructuredValue'.
* Use values from 0123456789 (Unicode 'DIGIT ZERO' (U+0030) to 'DIGIT NINE' (U+0039)) rather than superficially similar Unicode symbols.
* Use '.' (Unicode 'FULL STOP' (U+002E)) rather than ',' to indicate a decimal point. Avoid using these symbols as a readability separator.

risks.title: risks
risks.description: Specific physiologic risks associated to the diet plan.

inker.title: inker
inker.description: The individual who traces over the pencil drawings in ink after pencils are complete.

seller.title: seller
seller.description: An entity which offers (sells / leases / lends / loans) the services / goods.  A seller may also be a provider.

geographicArea.title: geographicArea
geographicArea.description: The geographic area associated with the audience.

activityDuration.title: activityDuration
activityDuration.description: Length of time to engage in the activity.

exerciseType.title: exerciseType
exerciseType.description: Type(s) of exercise or activity, such as strength training, flexibility training, aerobics, cardiac rehabilitation, etc.

keywords.title: keywords
keywords.description: Keywords or tags used to describe some item. Multiple textual entries in a keywords list are typically delimited by commas, or by repeating the property.

naturalProgression.title: naturalProgression
naturalProgression.description: The expected progression of the condition if it is not treated and allowed to progress naturally.

businessFunction.title: businessFunction
businessFunction.description: The business function (e.g. sell, lease, repair, dispose) of the offer or component of a bundle (TypeAndQuantityNode). The default is http://purl.org/goodrelations/v1#Sell.

directors.title: directors
directors.description: A director of e.g. TV, radio, movie, video games etc. content. Directors can be associated with individual items or with a series, episode, clip.

reservedTicket.title: reservedTicket
reservedTicket.description: A ticket associated with the reservation.

evidenceOrigin.title: evidenceOrigin
evidenceOrigin.description: Source of the data used to formulate the guidance, e.g. RCT, consensus opinion, etc.

sodiumContent.title: sodiumContent
sodiumContent.description: The number of milligrams of sodium.

minPrice.title: minPrice
minPrice.description: The lowest price if the price is a range.

copyrightNotice.title: copyrightNotice
copyrightNotice.description: Text of a notice appropriate for describing the copyright aspects of this Creative Work, ideally indicating the owner of the copyright for the Work.

mapType.title: mapType
mapType.description: Indicates the kind of Map, from the MapCategoryType Enumeration.

drainsTo.title: drainsTo
drainsTo.description: The vasculature that the vein drains into.

endTime.title: endTime
endTime.description: The endTime of something. For a reserved event or service (e.g. FoodEstablishmentReservation), the time that it is expected to end. For actions that span a period of time, when the action was performed. E.g. John wrote a book from January to *December*. For media, including audio and video, it's the time offset of the end of a clip within a larger file.\n\nNote that Event uses startDate/endDate instead of startTime/endTime, even when describing dates with times. This situation may be clarified in future revisions.

messageAttachment.title: messageAttachment
messageAttachment.description: A CreativeWork attached to the message.

workPerformed.title: workPerformed
workPerformed.description: A work performed in some event, for example a play performed in a TheaterEvent.

measurementDenominator.title: measurementDenominator
measurementDenominator.description: Identifies the denominator variable when an observation represents a ratio or percentage.

artworkSurface.title: artworkSurface
artworkSurface.description: The supporting materials for the artwork, e.g. Canvas, Paper, Wood, Board, etc.

occupancy.title: occupancy
occupancy.description:
The allowed total occupancy for the accommodation in persons (including infants etc). For individual accommodations, this is not necessarily the legal maximum but defines the permitted usage as per the contractual agreement (e.g. a double room used by a single person).
Typical unit code(s): C62 for person.

eligibleDuration.title: eligibleDuration
eligibleDuration.description: The duration for which the given offer is valid.

expectedPrognosis.title: expectedPrognosis
expectedPrognosis.description: The likely outcome in either the short term or long term of the medical condition.

specialty.title: specialty
specialty.description: One of the domain specialities to which this web page's content applies.

petsAllowed.title: petsAllowed
petsAllowed.description: Indicates whether pets are allowed to enter the accommodation or lodging business. More detailed information can be put in a text value.

geoDisjoint.title: geoDisjoint
geoDisjoint.description: Represents spatial relations in which two geometries (or the places they represent) are topologically disjoint: "they have no point in common. They form a set of disconnected geometries." (A symmetric relationship, as defined in [DE-9IM](https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/DE-9IM).)

educationalProgramMode.title: educationalProgramMode
educationalProgramMode.description: Similar to courseMode, the medium or means of delivery of the program as a whole. The value may either be a text label (e.g. "online", "onsite" or "blended"; "synchronous" or "asynchronous"; "full-time" or "part-time") or a URL reference to a term from a controlled vocabulary (e.g. https://ceds.ed.gov/element/001311#Asynchronous ).

opponent.title: opponent
opponent.description: A sub property of participant. The opponent on this action.

purchaseDate.title: purchaseDate
purchaseDate.description: The date the item, e.g. vehicle, was purchased by the current owner.

currentExchangeRate.title: currentExchangeRate
currentExchangeRate.description: The current price of a currency.

nerve.title: nerve
nerve.description: The underlying innervation associated with the muscle.

clinicalPharmacology.title: clinicalPharmacology
clinicalPharmacology.description: Description of the absorption and elimination of drugs, including their concentration (pharmacokinetics, pK) and biological effects (pharmacodynamics, pD).

typicalCreditsPerTerm.title: typicalCreditsPerTerm
typicalCreditsPerTerm.description: The number of credits or units a full-time student would be expected to take in 1 term however 'term' is defined by the institution.

episodes.title: episodes
episodes.description: An episode of a TV/radio series or season.

targetPlatform.title: targetPlatform
targetPlatform.description: Type of app development: phone, Metro style, desktop, XBox, etc.

printSection.title: printSection
printSection.description: If this NewsArticle appears in print, this field indicates the print section in which the article appeared.

yearlyRevenue.title: yearlyRevenue
yearlyRevenue.description: The size of the business in annual revenue.

recordedAs.title: recordedAs
recordedAs.description: An audio recording of the work.

beforeMedia.title: beforeMedia
beforeMedia.description: A media object representing the circumstances before performing this direction.

paymentDueDate.title: paymentDueDate
paymentDueDate.description: The date that payment is due.

billingDuration.title: billingDuration
billingDuration.description: Specifies for how long this price (or price component) will be billed. Can be used, for example, to model the contractual duration of a subscription or payment plan. Type can be either a Duration or a Number (in which case the unit of measurement, for example month, is specified by the unitCode property).

loanRepaymentForm.title: loanRepaymentForm
loanRepaymentForm.description: A form of paying back money previously borrowed from a lender. Repayment usually takes the form of periodic payments that normally include part principal plus interest in each payment.

associatedAnatomy.title: associatedAnatomy
associatedAnatomy.description: The anatomy of the underlying organ system or structures associated with this entity.

spokenByCharacter.title: spokenByCharacter
spokenByCharacter.description: The (e.g. fictional) character, Person or Organization to whom the quotation is attributed within the containing CreativeWork.

foundingDate.title: foundingDate
foundingDate.description: The date that this organization was founded.

coursePrerequisites.title: coursePrerequisites
coursePrerequisites.description: Requirements for taking the Course. May be completion of another [[Course]] or a textual description like "permission of instructor". Requirements may be a pre-requisite competency, referenced using [[AlignmentObject]].

differentialDiagnosis.title: differentialDiagnosis
differentialDiagnosis.description: One of a set of differential diagnoses for the condition. Specifically, a closely-related or competing diagnosis typically considered later in the cognitive process whereby this medical condition is distinguished from others most likely responsible for a similar collection of signs and symptoms to reach the most parsimonious diagnosis or diagnoses in a patient.

measurementQualifier.title: measurementQualifier
measurementQualifier.description: Provides additional qualification to an observation. For example, a GDP observation measures the Nominal value.

version.title: version
version.description: The version of the CreativeWork embodied by a specified resource.

hasEnergyConsumptionDetails.title: hasEnergyConsumptionDetails
hasEnergyConsumptionDetails.description: Defines the energy efficiency Category (also known as "class" or "rating") for a product according to an international energy efficiency standard.

isAccessibleForFree.title: isAccessibleForFree
isAccessibleForFree.description: A flag to signal that the item, event, or place is accessible for free.

videoFormat.title: videoFormat
videoFormat.description: The type of screening or video broadcast used (e.g. IMAX, 3D, SD, HD, etc.).

fundedItem.title: fundedItem
fundedItem.description: Indicates something directly or indirectly funded or sponsored through a [[Grant]]. See also [[ownershipFundingInfo]].

departureBusStop.title: departureBusStop
departureBusStop.description: The stop or station from which the bus departs.

resultComment.title: resultComment
resultComment.description: A sub property of result. The Comment created or sent as a result of this action.

mentions.title: mentions
mentions.description: Indicates that the CreativeWork contains a reference to, but is not necessarily about a concept.

reservationStatus.title: reservationStatus
reservationStatus.description: The current status of the reservation.

partOfSeason.title: partOfSeason
partOfSeason.description: The season to which this episode belongs.

verificationFactCheckingPolicy.title: verificationFactCheckingPolicy
verificationFactCheckingPolicy.description: Disclosure about verification and fact-checking processes for a [[NewsMediaOrganization]] or other fact-checking [[Organization]].

athlete.title: athlete
athlete.description: A person that acts as performing member of a sports team; a player as opposed to a coach.

biomechnicalClass.title: biomechnicalClass
biomechnicalClass.description: The biomechanical properties of the bone.

comprisedOf.title: comprisedOf
comprisedOf.description: Specifying something physically contained by something else. Typically used here for the underlying anatomical structures, such as organs, that comprise the anatomical system.

cholesterolContent.title: cholesterolContent
cholesterolContent.description: The number of milligrams of cholesterol.

securityScreening.title: securityScreening
securityScreening.description: The type of security screening the passenger is subject to.

actionOption.title: actionOption
actionOption.description: A sub property of object. The options subject to this action.

exchangeRateSpread.title: exchangeRateSpread
exchangeRateSpread.description: The difference between the price at which a broker or other intermediary buys and sells foreign currency.

durationOfWarranty.title: durationOfWarranty
durationOfWarranty.description: The duration of the warranty promise. Common unitCode values are ANN for year, MON for months, or DAY for days.

studyLocation.title: studyLocation
studyLocation.description: The location in which the study is taking/took place.

mainEntity.title: mainEntity
mainEntity.description: Indicates the primary entity described in some page or other CreativeWork.

hospitalAffiliation.title: hospitalAffiliation
hospitalAffiliation.description: A hospital with which the physician or office is affiliated.

vatID.title: vatID
vatID.description: The Value-added Tax ID of the organization or person.

variableMeasured.title: variableMeasured
variableMeasured.description: The variableMeasured property can indicate (repeated as necessary) the  variables that are measured in some dataset, either described as text or as pairs of identifier and description using PropertyValue, or more explicitly as a [[StatisticalVariable]].

remainingAttendeeCapacity.title: remainingAttendeeCapacity
remainingAttendeeCapacity.description: The number of attendee places for an event that remain unallocated.

molecularWeight.title: molecularWeight
molecularWeight.description: This is the molecular weight of the entity being described, not of the parent. Units should be included in the form '<Number> <unit>', for example '12 amu' or as '<QuantitativeValue>.

letterer.title: letterer
letterer.description: The individual who adds lettering, including speech balloons and sound effects, to artwork.

causeOf.title: causeOf
causeOf.description: The condition, complication, symptom, sign, etc. caused.

eligibilityToWorkRequirement.title: eligibilityToWorkRequirement
eligibilityToWorkRequirement.description: The legal requirements such as citizenship, visa and other documentation required for an applicant to this job.

availableService.title: availableService
availableService.description: A medical service available from this provider.

cvdNumTotBeds.title: cvdNumTotBeds
cvdNumTotBeds.description: numtotbeds - ALL HOSPITAL BEDS: Total number of all inpatient and outpatient beds, including all staffed, ICU, licensed, and overflow (surge) beds used for inpatients or outpatients.

broadcastFrequency.title: broadcastFrequency
broadcastFrequency.description: The frequency used for over-the-air broadcasts. Numeric values or simple ranges, e.g. 87-99. In addition a shortcut idiom is supported for frequencies of AM and FM radio channels, e.g. "87 FM".

deliveryMethod.title: deliveryMethod
deliveryMethod.description: A sub property of instrument. The method of delivery.

sampleType.title: sampleType
sampleType.description: What type of code sample: full (compile ready) solution, code snippet, inline code, scripts, template.

departureStation.title: departureStation
departureStation.description: The station from which the train departs.

reportNumber.title: reportNumber
reportNumber.description: The number or other unique designator assigned to a Report by the publishing organization.

accessibilitySummary.title: accessibilitySummary
accessibilitySummary.description: A human-readable summary of specific accessibility features or deficiencies, consistent with the other accessibility metadata but expressing subtleties such as "short descriptions are present but long descriptions will be needed for non-visual users" or "short descriptions are present and no long descriptions are needed".

resultReview.title: resultReview
resultReview.description: A sub property of result. The review that resulted in the performing of the action.

targetName.title: targetName
targetName.description: The name of a node in an established educational framework.

isInvolvedInBiologicalProcess.title: isInvolvedInBiologicalProcess
isInvolvedInBiologicalProcess.description: Biological process this BioChemEntity is involved in; please use PropertyValue if you want to include any evidence.

translator.title: translator
translator.description: Organization or person who adapts a creative work to different languages, regional differences and technical requirements of a target market, or that translates during some event.

area.title: area
area.description: The area within which users can expect to reach the broadcast service.

actionStatus.title: actionStatus
actionStatus.description: Indicates the current disposition of the Action.

energyEfficiencyScaleMax.title: energyEfficiencyScaleMax
energyEfficiencyScaleMax.description: Specifies the most energy efficient class on the regulated EU energy consumption scale for the product category a product belongs to. For example, energy consumption for televisions placed on the market after January 1, 2020 is scaled from D to A+++.

gracePeriod.title: gracePeriod
gracePeriod.description: The period of time after any due date that the borrower has to fulfil its obligations before a default (failure to pay) is deemed to have occurred.

benefitsSummaryUrl.title: benefitsSummaryUrl
benefitsSummaryUrl.description: The URL that goes directly to the summary of benefits and coverage for the specific standard plan or plan variation.

caption.title: caption
caption.description: The caption for this object. For downloadable machine formats (closed caption, subtitles etc.) use MediaObject and indicate the [[encodingFormat]].

partOfEpisode.title: partOfEpisode
partOfEpisode.description: The episode to which this clip belongs.

numberOfLoanPayments.title: numberOfLoanPayments
numberOfLoanPayments.description: The number of payments contractually required at origination to repay the loan. For monthly paying loans this is the number of months from the contractual first payment date to the maturity date.

broadcaster.title: broadcaster
broadcaster.description: The organization owning or operating the broadcast service.

brand.title: brand
brand.description: The brand(s) associated with a product or service, or the brand(s) maintained by an organization or business person.

geoCrosses.title: geoCrosses
geoCrosses.description: Represents a relationship between two geometries (or the places they represent), relating a geometry to another that crosses it: "a crosses b: they have some but not all interior points in common, and the dimension of the intersection is less than that of at least one of them". As defined in [DE-9IM](https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/DE-9IM).

dateline.title: dateline
dateline.description:
A [dateline](https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Dateline) is a brief piece of text included in news articles that describes where and when the story was written or filed though the date is often omitted. Sometimes only a placename is provided.

Structured representations of dateline-related information can also be expressed more explicitly using [[locationCreated]] (which represents where a work was created, e.g. where a news report was written).  For location depicted or described in the content, use [[contentLocation]].

Dateline summaries are oriented more towards human readers than towards automated processing, and can vary substantially. Some examples: "BEIRUT, Lebanon, June 2.", "Paris, France", "December 19, 2017 11:43AM Reporting from Washington", "Beijing/Moscow", "QUEZON CITY, Philippines".

isAvailableGenerically.title: isAvailableGenerically
isAvailableGenerically.description: True if the drug is available in a generic form (regardless of name).

availableStrength.title: availableStrength
availableStrength.description: An available dosage strength for the drug.

releaseNotes.title: releaseNotes
releaseNotes.description: Description of what changed in this version.

pageStart.title: pageStart
pageStart.description: The page on which the work starts; for example "135" or "xiii".

winner.title: winner
winner.description: A sub property of participant. The winner of the action.

transmissionMethod.title: transmissionMethod
transmissionMethod.description: How the disease spreads, either as a route or vector, for example 'direct contact', 'Aedes aegypti', etc.

recordLabel.title: recordLabel
recordLabel.description: The label that issued the release.

positiveNotes.title: positiveNotes
positiveNotes.description:
Provides positive considerations regarding something, for example product highlights or (alongside [[negativeNotes]]) pro/con lists for reviews.

In the case of a [[Review]], the property describes the [[itemReviewed]] from the perspective of the review; in the case of a [[Product]], the product itself is being described.

The property values can be expressed either as unstructured text (repeated as necessary), or if ordered, as a list (in which case the most positive is at the beginning of the list).

mobileUrl.title: mobileUrl
mobileUrl.description:
The [[mobileUrl]] property is provided for specific situations in which data consumers need to determine whether one of several provided URLs is a dedicated 'mobile site'.

To discourage over-use, and reflecting intial usecases, the property is expected only on [[Product]] and [[Offer]], rather than [[Thing]]. The general trend in web technology is towards [responsive design](https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Responsive_web_design) in which content can be flexibly adapted to a wide range of browsing environments. Pages and sites referenced with the long-established [[url]] property should ideally also be usable on a wide variety of devices, including mobile phones. In most cases, it would be pointless and counter productive to attempt to update all [[url]] markup to use [[mobileUrl]] for more mobile-oriented pages. The property is intended for the case when items (primarily [[Product]] and [[Offer]]) have extra URLs hosted on an additional "mobile site" alongside the main one. It should not be taken as an endorsement of this publication style.

releasedEvent.title: releasedEvent
releasedEvent.description: The place and time the release was issued, expressed as a PublicationEvent.

educationalFramework.title: educationalFramework
educationalFramework.description: The framework to which the resource being described is aligned.

educationalLevel.title: educationalLevel
educationalLevel.description: The level in terms of progression through an educational or training context. Examples of educational levels include 'beginner', 'intermediate' or 'advanced', and formal sets of level indicators.

hasVariant.title: hasVariant
hasVariant.description: Indicates a [[Product]] that is a member of this [[ProductGroup]] (or [[ProductModel]]).

elevation.title: elevation
elevation.description: The elevation of a location ([WGS 84](https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/World_Geodetic_System)). Values may be of the form 'NUMBER UNIT\_OF\_MEASUREMENT' (e.g., '1,000 m', '3,200 ft') while numbers alone should be assumed to be a value in meters.

observationPeriod.title: observationPeriod
observationPeriod.description: The length of time an Observation took place over. The format follows `P[0-9]*[Y|M|D|h|m|s]`. For example, P1Y is Period 1 Year, P3M is Period 3 Months, P3h is Period 3 hours.

usedToDiagnose.title: usedToDiagnose
usedToDiagnose.description: A condition the test is used to diagnose.

processorRequirements.title: processorRequirements
processorRequirements.description: Processor architecture required to run the application (e.g. IA64).

arrivalTerminal.title: arrivalTerminal
arrivalTerminal.description: Identifier of the flight's arrival terminal.

physicalRequirement.title: physicalRequirement
physicalRequirement.description: A description of the types of physical activity associated with the job. Defined terms such as those in O*net may be used, but note that there is no way to specify the level of ability as well as its nature when using a defined term.

featureList.title: featureList
featureList.description: Features or modules provided by this application (and possibly required by other applications).

potentialUse.title: potentialUse
potentialUse.description: Intended use of the BioChemEntity by humans.

termDuration.title: termDuration
termDuration.description: The amount of time in a term as defined by the institution. A term is a length of time where students take one or more classes. Semesters and quarters are common units for term.

carbohydrateContent.title: carbohydrateContent
carbohydrateContent.description: The number of grams of carbohydrates.

deliveryStatus.title: deliveryStatus
deliveryStatus.description: New entry added as the package passes through each leg of its journey (from shipment to final delivery).

appliesToPaymentMethod.title: appliesToPaymentMethod
appliesToPaymentMethod.description: The payment method(s) to which the payment charge specification applies.

paymentMethodType.title: paymentMethodType
paymentMethodType.description: The type of a payment method.

nutrition.title: nutrition
nutrition.description: Nutrition information about the recipe or menu item.

ratingCount.title: ratingCount
ratingCount.description: The count of total number of ratings.

hasCategoryCode.title: hasCategoryCode
hasCategoryCode.description: A Category code contained in this code set.

courseCode.title: courseCode
courseCode.description: The identifier for the [[Course]] used by the course [[provider]] (e.g. CS101 or 6.001).

agentInteractionStatistic.title: agentInteractionStatistic
agentInteractionStatistic.description: The number of completed interactions for this entity, in a particular role (the 'agent'), in a particular action (indicated in the statistic), and in a particular context (i.e. interactionService).

usNPI.title: usNPI
usNPI.description: A National Provider Identifier (NPI) is a unique 10-digit identification number issued to health care providers in the United States by the Centers for Medicare and Medicaid Services.

shippingLabel.title: shippingLabel
shippingLabel.description: Label to match an [[OfferShippingDetails]] with a [[ShippingRateSettings]] (within the context of a [[shippingSettingsLink]] cross-reference).

blogPost.title: blogPost
blogPost.description: A posting that is part of this blog.

blogPosts.title: blogPosts
blogPosts.description: Indicates a post that is part of a [[Blog]]. Note that historically, what we term a "Blog" was once known as a "weblog", and that what we term a "BlogPosting" is now often colloquially referred to as a "blog".

timeRequired.title: timeRequired
timeRequired.description: Approximate or typical time it usually takes to work with or through the content of this work for the typical or target audience.

targetUrl.title: targetUrl
targetUrl.description: The URL of a node in an established educational framework.

loanPaymentFrequency.title: loanPaymentFrequency
loanPaymentFrequency.description: Frequency of payments due, i.e. number of months between payments. This is defined as a frequency, i.e. the reciprocal of a period of time.

busName.title: busName
busName.description: The name of the bus (e.g. Bolt Express).

inStoreReturnsOffered.title: inStoreReturnsOffered
inStoreReturnsOffered.description: Are in-store returns offered? (For more advanced return methods use the [[returnMethod]] property.)

benefits.title: benefits
benefits.description: Description of benefits associated with the job.

financialAidEligible.title: financialAidEligible
financialAidEligible.description: A financial aid type or program which students may use to pay for tuition or fees associated with the program.

sha256.title: sha256
sha256.description: The [SHA-2](https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/SHA-2) SHA256 hash of the content of the item. For example, a zero-length input has value 'e3b0c44298fc1c149afbf4c8996fb92427ae41e4649b934ca495991b7852b855'.

valueAddedTaxIncluded.title: valueAddedTaxIncluded
valueAddedTaxIncluded.description: Specifies whether the applicable value-added tax (VAT) is included in the price specification or not.

relatedCondition.title: relatedCondition
relatedCondition.description: A medical condition associated with this anatomy.

latitude.title: latitude
latitude.description: The latitude of a location. For example ```37.42242``` ([WGS 84](https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/World_Geodetic_System)).

hiringOrganization.title: hiringOrganization
hiringOrganization.description: Organization or Person offering the job position.

videoFrameSize.title: videoFrameSize
videoFrameSize.description: The frame size of the video.

issueNumber.title: issueNumber
issueNumber.description: Identifies the issue of publication; for example, "iii" or "2".

bioChemInteraction.title: bioChemInteraction
bioChemInteraction.description: A BioChemEntity that is known to interact with this item.

offeredBy.title: offeredBy
offeredBy.description: A pointer to the organization or person making the offer.

numberOfAvailableAccommodationUnits.title: numberOfAvailableAccommodationUnits
numberOfAvailableAccommodationUnits.description: Indicates the number of available accommodation units in an [[ApartmentComplex]], or the number of accommodation units for a specific [[FloorPlan]] (within its specific [[ApartmentComplex]]). See also [[numberOfAccommodationUnits]].

estimatedFlightDuration.title: estimatedFlightDuration
estimatedFlightDuration.description: The estimated time the flight will take.

providesBroadcastService.title: providesBroadcastService
providesBroadcastService.description: The BroadcastService offered on this channel.

programmingModel.title: programmingModel
programmingModel.description: Indicates whether API is managed or unmanaged.

makesOffer.title: makesOffer
makesOffer.description: A pointer to products or services offered by the organization or person.

isLocatedInSubcellularLocation.title: isLocatedInSubcellularLocation
isLocatedInSubcellularLocation.description: Subcellular location where this BioChemEntity is located; please use PropertyValue if you want to include any evidence.

procedureType.title: procedureType
procedureType.description: The type of procedure, for example Surgical, Noninvasive, or Percutaneous.

earlyPrepaymentPenalty.title: earlyPrepaymentPenalty
earlyPrepaymentPenalty.description: The amount to be paid as a penalty in the event of early payment of the loan.

browserRequirements.title: browserRequirements
browserRequirements.description: Specifies browser requirements in human-readable text. For example, 'requires HTML5 support'.

prescribingInfo.title: prescribingInfo
prescribingInfo.description: Link to prescribing information for the drug.

isicV4.title: isicV4
isicV4.description: The International Standard of Industrial Classification of All Economic Activities (ISIC), Revision 4 code for a particular organization, business person, or place.

volumeNumber.title: volumeNumber
volumeNumber.description: Identifies the volume of publication or multi-part work; for example, "iii" or "2".

iso6523Code.title: iso6523Code
iso6523Code.description: An organization identifier as defined in [ISO 6523(-1)](https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/ISO/IEC_6523). The identifier should be in the `XXXX:YYYYYY:ZZZ` or `XXXX:YYYYYY`format. Where `XXXX` is a 4 digit _ICD_ (International Code Designator), `YYYYYY` is an _OID_ (Organization Identifier) with all formatting characters (dots, dashes, spaces) removed with a maximal length of 35 characters, and `ZZZ` is an optional OPI (Organization Part Identifier) with a maximum length of 35 characters. The various components (ICD, OID, OPI) are joined with a colon character (ASCII `0x3a`). Note that many existing organization identifiers defined as attributes like [leiCode](https://schema.org/leiCode) (`0199`), [duns](https://schema.org/duns) (`0060`) or [GLN](https://schema.org/globalLocationNumber) (`0088`) can be expressed using ISO-6523. If possible, ISO-6523 codes should be preferred to populating [vatID](https://schema.org/vatID) or [taxID](https://schema.org/taxID), as ISO identifiers are less ambiguous.

priceType.title: priceType
priceType.description: Defines the type of a price specified for an offered product, for example a list price, a (temporary) sale price or a manufacturer suggested retail price. If multiple prices are specified for an offer the [[priceType]] property can be used to identify the type of each such specified price. The value of priceType can be specified as a value from enumeration PriceTypeEnumeration or as a free form text string for price types that are not already predefined in PriceTypeEnumeration.

rangeIncludes.title: rangeIncludes
rangeIncludes.description: Relates a property to a class that constitutes (one of) the expected type(s) for values of the property.

commentCount.title: commentCount
commentCount.description: The number of comments this CreativeWork (e.g. Article, Question or Answer) has received. This is most applicable to works published in Web sites with commenting system; additional comments may exist elsewhere.

flightNumber.title: flightNumber
flightNumber.description: The unique identifier for a flight including the airline IATA code. For example, if describing United flight 110, where the IATA code for United is 'UA', the flightNumber is 'UA110'.

recordedIn.title: recordedIn
recordedIn.description: The CreativeWork that captured all or part of this Event.

issuedThrough.title: issuedThrough
issuedThrough.description: The service through which the permit was granted.

sourcedFrom.title: sourcedFrom
sourcedFrom.description: The neurological pathway that originates the neurons.

postOfficeBoxNumber.title: postOfficeBoxNumber
postOfficeBoxNumber.description: The post office box number for PO box addresses.

itemListOrder.title: itemListOrder
itemListOrder.description: Type of ordering (e.g. Ascending, Descending, Unordered).

salaryCurrency.title: salaryCurrency
salaryCurrency.description: The currency (coded using [ISO 4217](http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/ISO_4217)) used for the main salary information in this job posting or for this employee.

runsTo.title: runsTo
runsTo.description: The vasculature the lymphatic structure runs, or efferents, to.

digitalSourceType.title: digitalSourceType
digitalSourceType.description: Indicates an IPTCDigitalSourceEnumeration code indicating the nature of the digital source(s) for some [[CreativeWork]].

discountCurrency.title: discountCurrency
discountCurrency.description: The currency of the discount.\n\nUse standard formats: [ISO 4217 currency format](http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/ISO_4217), e.g. "USD"; [Ticker symbol](https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/List_of_cryptocurrencies) for cryptocurrencies, e.g. "BTC"; well known names for [Local Exchange Trading Systems](https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Local_exchange_trading_system) (LETS) and other currency types, e.g. "Ithaca HOUR".

alternativeHeadline.title: alternativeHeadline
alternativeHeadline.description: A secondary title of the CreativeWork.

industry.title: industry
industry.description: The industry associated with the job position.

servingSize.title: servingSize
servingSize.description: The serving size, in terms of the number of volume or mass.

minValue.title: minValue
minValue.description: The lower value of some characteristic or property.

isUnlabelledFallback.title: isUnlabelledFallback
isUnlabelledFallback.description: This can be marked 'true' to indicate that some published [[DeliveryTimeSettings]] or [[ShippingRateSettings]] are intended to apply to all [[OfferShippingDetails]] published by the same merchant, when referenced by a [[shippingSettingsLink]] in those settings. It is not meaningful to use a 'true' value for this property alongside a transitTimeLabel (for [[DeliveryTimeSettings]]) or shippingLabel (for [[ShippingRateSettings]]), since this property is for use with unlabelled settings.

creativeWorkStatus.title: creativeWorkStatus
creativeWorkStatus.description: The status of a creative work in terms of its stage in a lifecycle. Example terms include Incomplete, Draft, Published, Obsolete. Some organizations define a set of terms for the stages of their publication lifecycle.

requiredGender.title: requiredGender
requiredGender.description: Audiences defined by a person's gender.

attendee.title: attendee
attendee.description: A person or organization attending the event.

eligibleCustomerType.title: eligibleCustomerType
eligibleCustomerType.description: The type(s) of customers for which the given offer is valid.

primaryImageOfPage.title: primaryImageOfPage
primaryImageOfPage.description: Indicates the main image on the page.

issuedBy.title: issuedBy
issuedBy.description: The organization issuing the item, for example a [[Permit]], [[Ticket]], or [[Certification]].

broker.title: broker
broker.description: An entity that arranges for an exchange between a buyer and a seller.  In most cases a broker never acquires or releases ownership of a product or service involved in an exchange.  If it is not clear whether an entity is a broker, seller, or buyer, the latter two terms are preferred.

geoTouches.title: geoTouches
geoTouches.description: Represents spatial relations in which two geometries (or the places they represent) touch: "they have at least one boundary point in common, but no interior points." (A symmetric relationship, as defined in [DE-9IM](https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/DE-9IM).)

layoutImage.title: layoutImage
layoutImage.description: A schematic image showing the floorplan layout.

serviceAudience.title: serviceAudience
serviceAudience.description: The audience eligible for this service.

infectiousAgent.title: infectiousAgent
infectiousAgent.description: The actual infectious agent, such as a specific bacterium.

suggestedGender.title: suggestedGender
suggestedGender.description: The suggested gender of the intended person or audience, for example "male", "female", or "unisex".

locationCreated.title: locationCreated
locationCreated.description: The location where the CreativeWork was created, which may not be the same as the location depicted in the CreativeWork.

founders.title: founders
founders.description: A person who founded this organization.

typeOfBed.title: typeOfBed
typeOfBed.description: The type of bed to which the BedDetail refers, i.e. the type of bed available in the quantity indicated by quantity.

serviceUrl.title: serviceUrl
serviceUrl.description: The website to access the service.

departureTerminal.title: departureTerminal
departureTerminal.description: Identifier of the flight's departure terminal.

cvdNumVent.title: cvdNumVent
cvdNumVent.description: numvent - MECHANICAL VENTILATORS: Total number of ventilators available.

containedInPlace.title: containedInPlace
containedInPlace.description: The basic containment relation between a place and one that contains it.

significantLink.title: significantLink
significantLink.description: One of the more significant URLs on the page. Typically, these are the non-navigation links that are clicked on the most.

availableChannel.title: availableChannel
availableChannel.description: A means of accessing the service (e.g. a phone bank, a web site, a location, etc.).

maximumPhysicalAttendeeCapacity.title: maximumPhysicalAttendeeCapacity
maximumPhysicalAttendeeCapacity.description: The maximum physical attendee capacity of an [[Event]] whose [[eventAttendanceMode]] is [[OfflineEventAttendanceMode]] (or the offline aspects, in the case of a [[MixedEventAttendanceMode]]).

supersededBy.title: supersededBy
supersededBy.description: Relates a term (i.e. a property, class or enumeration) to one that supersedes it.

publicAccess.title: publicAccess
publicAccess.description: A flag to signal that the [[Place]] is open to public visitors.  If this property is omitted there is no assumed default boolean value.

programMembershipUsed.title: programMembershipUsed
programMembershipUsed.description: Any membership in a frequent flyer, hotel loyalty program, etc. being applied to the reservation.

previousItem.title: previousItem
previousItem.description: A link to the ListItem that precedes the current one.

applicationSubCategory.title: applicationSubCategory
applicationSubCategory.description: Subcategory of the application, e.g. 'Arcade Game'.

openingHoursSpecification.title: openingHoursSpecification
openingHoursSpecification.description: The opening hours of a certain place.

nonEqual.title: nonEqual
nonEqual.description: This ordering relation for qualitative values indicates that the subject is not equal to the object.

utterances.title: utterances
utterances.description: Text of an utterances (spoken words, lyrics etc.) that occurs at a certain section of a media object, represented as a [[HyperTocEntry]].

paymentAccepted.title: paymentAccepted
paymentAccepted.description: Cash, Credit Card, Cryptocurrency, Local Exchange Tradings System, etc.

totalJobOpenings.title: totalJobOpenings
totalJobOpenings.description: The number of positions open for this job posting. Use a positive integer. Do not use if the number of positions is unclear or not known.

line.title: line
line.description: A line is a point-to-point path consisting of two or more points. A line is expressed as a series of two or more point objects separated by space.

legislationLegalValue.title: legislationLegalValue
legislationLegalValue.description: The legal value of this legislation file. The same legislation can be written in multiple files with different legal values. Typically a digitally signed PDF have a "stronger" legal value than the HTML file of the same act.

reviewCount.title: reviewCount
reviewCount.description: The count of total number of reviews.

courseMode.title: courseMode
courseMode.description: The medium or means of delivery of the course instance or the mode of study, either as a text label (e.g. "online", "onsite" or "blended"; "synchronous" or "asynchronous"; "full-time" or "part-time") or as a URL reference to a term from a controlled vocabulary (e.g. https://ceds.ed.gov/element/001311#Asynchronous).

eligibleQuantity.title: eligibleQuantity
eligibleQuantity.description: The interval and unit of measurement of ordering quantities for which the offer or price specification is valid. This allows e.g. specifying that a certain freight charge is valid only for a certain quantity.

frequency.title: frequency
frequency.description: How often the dose is taken, e.g. 'daily'.

emissionsCO2.title: emissionsCO2
emissionsCO2.description: The CO2 emissions in g/km. When used in combination with a QuantitativeValue, put "g/km" into the unitText property of that value, since there is no UN/CEFACT Common Code for "g/km".

reviewedBy.title: reviewedBy
reviewedBy.description: People or organizations that have reviewed the content on this web page for accuracy and/or completeness.

alcoholWarning.title: alcoholWarning
alcoholWarning.description: Any precaution, guidance, contraindication, etc. related to consumption of alcohol while taking this drug.

appliesToDeliveryMethod.title: appliesToDeliveryMethod
appliesToDeliveryMethod.description: The delivery method(s) to which the delivery charge or payment charge specification applies.

mechanismOfAction.title: mechanismOfAction
mechanismOfAction.description: The specific biochemical interaction through which this drug or supplement produces its pharmacological effect.

legislationApplies.title: legislationApplies
legislationApplies.description: Indicates that this legislation (or part of a legislation) somehow transfers another legislation in a different legislative context. This is an informative link, and it has no legal value. For legally-binding links of transposition, use the legislationTransposes property. For example an informative consolidated law of a European Union's member state "applies" the consolidated version of the European Directive implemented in it.

unitText.title: unitText
unitText.description: A string or text indicating the unit of measurement. Useful if you cannot provide a standard unit code for unitCode.

restockingFee.title: restockingFee
restockingFee.description: Use [[MonetaryAmount]] to specify a fixed restocking fee for product returns, or use [[Number]] to specify a percentage of the product price paid by the customer.

performer.title: performer
performer.description: A performer at the event—for example, a presenter, musician, musical group or actor.

typicalAgeRange.title: typicalAgeRange
typicalAgeRange.description: The typical expected age range, e.g. '7-9', '11-'.

engineType.title: engineType
engineType.description: The type of engine or engines powering the vehicle.

globalLocationNumber.title: globalLocationNumber
globalLocationNumber.description: The [Global Location Number](http://www.gs1.org/gln) (GLN, sometimes also referred to as International Location Number or ILN) of the respective organization, person, or place. The GLN is a 13-digit number used to identify parties and physical locations.

encodingType.title: encodingType
encodingType.description: The supported encoding type(s) for an EntryPoint request.

quest.title: quest
quest.description: The task that a player-controlled character, or group of characters may complete in order to gain a reward.

menu.title: menu
menu.description: Either the actual menu as a structured representation, as text, or a URL of the menu.

bioChemSimilarity.title: bioChemSimilarity
bioChemSimilarity.description: A similar BioChemEntity, e.g., obtained by fingerprint similarity algorithms.

tracks.title: tracks
tracks.description: A music recording (track)—usually a single song.

isTierOf.title: isTierOf
isTierOf.description: The member program this tier is a part of.

followup.title: followup
followup.description: Typical or recommended followup care after the procedure is performed.

acceptedPaymentMethod.title: acceptedPaymentMethod
acceptedPaymentMethod.description: The payment method(s) that are accepted in general by an organization, or for some specific demand or offer.

contactPoint.title: contactPoint
contactPoint.description: A contact point for a person or organization.

fileSize.title: fileSize
fileSize.description: Size of the application / package (e.g. 18MB). In the absence of a unit (MB, KB etc.), KB will be assumed.

gtin14.title: gtin14
gtin14.description: The GTIN-14 code of the product, or the product to which the offer refers. See [GS1 GTIN Summary](http://www.gs1.org/barcodes/technical/idkeys/gtin) for more details.

offersPrescriptionByMail.title: offersPrescriptionByMail
offersPrescriptionByMail.description: Whether prescriptions can be delivered by mail.

recipeInstructions.title: recipeInstructions
recipeInstructions.description: A step in making the recipe, in the form of a single item (document, video, etc.) or an ordered list with HowToStep and/or HowToSection items.

slogan.title: slogan
slogan.description: A slogan or motto associated with the item.

postalCodeRange.title: postalCodeRange
postalCodeRange.description: A defined range of postal codes.

recipeYield.title: recipeYield
recipeYield.description: The quantity produced by the recipe (for example, number of people served, number of servings, etc).

language.title: language
language.description: A sub property of instrument. The language used on this action.

gamePlatform.title: gamePlatform
gamePlatform.description: The electronic systems used to play video games.

doseValue.title: doseValue
doseValue.description: The value of the dose, e.g. 500.

relatedTherapy.title: relatedTherapy
relatedTherapy.description: A medical therapy related to this anatomy.

monoisotopicMolecularWeight.title: monoisotopicMolecularWeight
monoisotopicMolecularWeight.description: The monoisotopic mass is the sum of the masses of the atoms in a molecule using the unbound, ground-state, rest mass of the principal (most abundant) isotope for each element instead of the isotopic average mass. Please include the units in the form '<Number> <unit>', for example '770.230488 g/mol' or as '<QuantitativeValue>.

guidelineDate.title: guidelineDate
guidelineDate.description: Date on which this guideline's recommendation was made.

departurePlatform.title: departurePlatform
departurePlatform.description: The platform from which the train departs.

contentRating.title: contentRating
contentRating.description: Official rating of a piece of content—for example, 'MPAA PG-13'.

performerIn.title: performerIn
performerIn.description: Event that this person is a performer or participant in.

maximumVirtualAttendeeCapacity.title: maximumVirtualAttendeeCapacity
maximumVirtualAttendeeCapacity.description: The maximum virtual attendee capacity of an [[Event]] whose [[eventAttendanceMode]] is [[OnlineEventAttendanceMode]] (or the online aspects, in the case of a [[MixedEventAttendanceMode]]).

interactionService.title: interactionService
interactionService.description: The WebSite or SoftwareApplication where the interactions took place.

deliveryLeadTime.title: deliveryLeadTime
deliveryLeadTime.description: The typical delay between the receipt of the order and the goods either leaving the warehouse or being prepared for pickup, in case the delivery method is on site pickup.

valuePattern.title: valuePattern
valuePattern.description: Specifies a regular expression for testing literal values according to the HTML spec.

isEncodedByBioChemEntity.title: isEncodedByBioChemEntity
isEncodedByBioChemEntity.description: Another BioChemEntity encoding by this one.

breastfeedingWarning.title: breastfeedingWarning
breastfeedingWarning.description: Any precaution, guidance, contraindication, etc. related to this drug's use by breastfeeding mothers.

coverageStartTime.title: coverageStartTime
coverageStartTime.description: The time when the live blog will begin covering the Event. Note that coverage may begin before the Event's start time. The LiveBlogPosting may also be created before coverage begins.

event.title: event
event.description: Upcoming or past event associated with this place, organization, or action.

suggestedMaxAge.title: suggestedMaxAge
suggestedMaxAge.description: Maximum recommended age in years for the audience or user.

sender.title: sender
sender.description: A sub property of participant. The participant who is at the sending end of the action.

speed.title: speed
speed.description:
The speed range of the vehicle. If the vehicle is powered by an engine, the upper limit of the speed range (indicated by [[maxValue]]) should be the maximum speed achievable under regular conditions.

Typical unit code(s): KMH for km/h, HM for mile per hour (0.447 04 m/s), KNT for knot

*Note 1: Use [[minValue]] and [[maxValue]] to indicate the range. Typically, the minimal value is zero.
* Note 2: There are many different ways of measuring the speed range. You can link to information about how the given value has been determined using the [[valueReference]] property.

healthPlanCopayOption.title: healthPlanCopayOption
healthPlanCopayOption.description: Whether the copay is before or after deductible, etc. TODO: Is this a closed set?

byMonthDay.title: byMonthDay
byMonthDay.description: Defines the day(s) of the month on which a recurring [[Event]] takes place. Specified as an [[Integer]] between 1-31.

accessibilityHazard.title: accessibilityHazard
accessibilityHazard.description: A characteristic of the described resource that is physiologically dangerous to some users. Related to WCAG 2.0 guideline 2.3. Values should be drawn from the [approved vocabulary](https://www.w3.org/2021/a11y-discov-vocab/latest/#accessibilityHazard-vocabulary).

dateVehicleFirstRegistered.title: dateVehicleFirstRegistered
dateVehicleFirstRegistered.description: The date of the first registration of the vehicle with the respective public authorities.

postalCodePrefix.title: postalCodePrefix
postalCodePrefix.description: A defined range of postal codes indicated by a common textual prefix. Used for non-numeric systems such as UK.

annualPercentageRate.title: annualPercentageRate
annualPercentageRate.description: The annual rate that is charged for borrowing (or made by investing), expressed as a single percentage number that represents the actual yearly cost of funds over the term of a loan. This includes any fees or additional costs associated with the transaction.

text.title: text
text.description: The textual content of this CreativeWork.

torque.title: torque
torque.description:
The torque (turning force) of the vehicle's engine.

Typical unit code(s): NU for newton metre (N m), F17 for pound-force per foot, or F48 for pound-force per inch
