* Note 1: You can link to information about how the given value has been determined (e.g. reference RPM) using the [[valueReference]] property.
* Note 2: You can use [[minValue]] and [[maxValue]] to indicate ranges.

serviceSmsNumber.title: serviceSmsNumber
serviceSmsNumber.description: The number to access the service by text message.

hasDriveThroughService.title: hasDriveThroughService
hasDriveThroughService.description: Indicates whether some facility (e.g. [[FoodEstablishment]], [[CovidTestingFacility]]) offers a service that can be used by driving through in a car. In the case of [[CovidTestingFacility]] such facilities could potentially help with social distancing from other potentially-infected users.

numberOfAccommodationUnits.title: numberOfAccommodationUnits
numberOfAccommodationUnits.description: Indicates the total (available plus unavailable) number of accommodation units in an [[ApartmentComplex]], or the number of accommodation units for a specific [[FloorPlan]] (within its specific [[ApartmentComplex]]). See also [[numberOfAvailableAccommodationUnits]].

vehicleInteriorColor.title: vehicleInteriorColor
vehicleInteriorColor.description: The color or color combination of the interior of the vehicle.

geoContains.title: geoContains
geoContains.description: Represents a relationship between two geometries (or the places they represent), relating a containing geometry to a contained geometry. "a contains b iff no points of b lie in the exterior of a, and at least one point of the interior of b lies in the interior of a". As defined in [DE-9IM](https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/DE-9IM).

inPlaylist.title: inPlaylist
inPlaylist.description: The playlist to which this recording belongs.

duringMedia.title: duringMedia
duringMedia.description: A media object representing the circumstances while performing this direction.

includedDataCatalog.title: includedDataCatalog
includedDataCatalog.description: A data catalog which contains this dataset (this property was previously 'catalog', preferred name is now 'includedInDataCatalog').

numberOfPlayers.title: numberOfPlayers
numberOfPlayers.description: Indicate how many people can play this game (minimum, maximum, or range).

actor.title: actor
actor.description: An actor, e.g. in TV, radio, movie, video games etc., or in an event. Actors can be associated with individual items or with a series, episode, clip.

hostingOrganization.title: hostingOrganization
hostingOrganization.description: The Organization (airline, travelers' club, retailer, etc.) the membership is made with or which offers the  MemberProgram.

serialNumber.title: serialNumber
serialNumber.description: The serial number or any alphanumeric identifier of a particular product. When attached to an offer, it is a shortcut for the serial number of the product included in the offer.

providerMobility.title: providerMobility
providerMobility.description: Indicates the mobility of a provided service (e.g. 'static', 'dynamic').

shippingDestination.title: shippingDestination
shippingDestination.description: indicates (possibly multiple) shipping destinations. These can be defined in several ways, e.g. postalCode ranges.

foodEstablishment.title: foodEstablishment
foodEstablishment.description: A sub property of location. The specific food establishment where the action occurred.

exerciseRelatedDiet.title: exerciseRelatedDiet
exerciseRelatedDiet.description: A sub property of instrument. The diet used in this action.

normalRange.title: normalRange
normalRange.description: Range of acceptable values for a typical patient, when applicable.

hasCourseInstance.title: hasCourseInstance
hasCourseInstance.description: An offering of the course at a specific time and place or through specific media or mode of study or to a specific section of students.

free.title: free
free.description: A flag to signal that the item, event, or place is accessible for free.

result.title: result
result.description: The result produced in the action. E.g. John wrote *a book*.

foodEvent.title: foodEvent
foodEvent.description: A sub property of location. The specific food event where the action occurred.

timeToComplete.title: timeToComplete
timeToComplete.description: The expected length of time to complete the program if attending full-time.

identifier.title: identifier
identifier.description: The identifier property represents any kind of identifier for any kind of [[Thing]], such as ISBNs, GTIN codes, UUIDs etc. Schema.org provides dedicated properties for representing many of these, either as textual strings or as URL (URI) links. See [background notes](/docs/datamodel.html#identifierBg) for more details.

publishingPrinciples.title: publishingPrinciples
publishingPrinciples.description:
The publishingPrinciples property indicates (typically via [[URL]]) a document describing the editorial principles of an [[Organization]] (or individual, e.g. a [[Person]] writing a blog) that relate to their activities as a publisher, e.g. ethics or diversity policies. When applied to a [[CreativeWork]] (e.g. [[NewsArticle]]) the principles are those of the party primarily responsible for the creation of the [[CreativeWork]].

While such policies are most typically expressed in natural language, sometimes related information (e.g. indicating a [[funder]]) can be expressed using schema.org terminology.

servicePostalAddress.title: servicePostalAddress
servicePostalAddress.description: The address for accessing the service by mail.

urlTemplate.title: urlTemplate
urlTemplate.description: An url template (RFC6570) that will be used to construct the target of the execution of the action.

billingPeriod.title: billingPeriod
billingPeriod.description: The time interval used to compute the invoice.

includedInHealthInsurancePlan.title: includedInHealthInsurancePlan
includedInHealthInsurancePlan.description: The insurance plans that cover this drug.

mainContentOfPage.title: mainContentOfPage
mainContentOfPage.description: Indicates if this web page element is the main subject of the page.

hasOfferCatalog.title: hasOfferCatalog
hasOfferCatalog.description: Indicates an OfferCatalog listing for this Organization, Person, or Service.

originatesFrom.title: originatesFrom
originatesFrom.description: The vasculature the lymphatic structure originates, or afferents, from.

educationalAlignment.title: educationalAlignment
educationalAlignment.description:
An alignment to an established educational framework.

This property should not be used where the nature of the alignment can be described using a simple property, for example to express that a resource [[teaches]] or [[assesses]] a competency.

postOp.title: postOp
postOp.description: A description of the postoperative procedures, care, and/or followups for this device.

holdingArchive.title: holdingArchive
holdingArchive.description: [[ArchiveOrganization]] that holds, keeps or maintains the [[ArchiveComponent]].

labelDetails.title: labelDetails
labelDetails.description: Link to the drug's label details.

albumProductionType.title: albumProductionType
albumProductionType.description: Classification of the album by its type of content: soundtrack, live album, studio album, etc.

cvdNumC19OverflowPats.title: cvdNumC19OverflowPats
cvdNumC19OverflowPats.description: numc19overflowpats - ED/OVERFLOW: Patients with suspected or confirmed COVID-19 who are in the ED or any overflow location awaiting an inpatient bed.

award.title: award
award.description: An award won by or for this item.

datasetTimeInterval.title: datasetTimeInterval
datasetTimeInterval.description: The range of temporal applicability of a dataset, e.g. for a 2011 census dataset, the year 2011 (in ISO 8601 time interval format).

monthlyMinimumRepaymentAmount.title: monthlyMinimumRepaymentAmount
monthlyMinimumRepaymentAmount.description: The minimum payment is the lowest amount of money that one is required to pay on a credit card statement each month.

variesBy.title: variesBy
variesBy.description: Indicates the property or properties by which the variants in a [[ProductGroup]] vary, e.g. their size, color etc. Schema.org properties can be referenced by their short name e.g. "color"; terms defined elsewhere can be referenced with their URIs.

mainEntityOfPage.title: mainEntityOfPage
mainEntityOfPage.description: Indicates a page (or other CreativeWork) for which this thing is the main entity being described. See [background notes](/docs/datamodel.html#mainEntityBackground) for details.

option.title: option
option.description: A sub property of object. The options subject to this action.

citation.title: citation
citation.description: A citation or reference to another creative work, such as another publication, web page, scholarly article, etc.

numAdults.title: numAdults
numAdults.description: The number of adults staying in the unit.

diversityStaffingReport.title: diversityStaffingReport
diversityStaffingReport.description: For an [[Organization]] (often but not necessarily a [[NewsMediaOrganization]]), a report on staffing diversity issues. In a news context this might be for example ASNE or RTDNA (US) reports, or self-reported.

passengerSequenceNumber.title: passengerSequenceNumber
passengerSequenceNumber.description: The passenger's sequence number as assigned by the airline.

healthcareReportingData.title: healthcareReportingData
healthcareReportingData.description: Indicates data describing a hospital, e.g. a CDC [[CDCPMDRecord]] or as some kind of [[Dataset]].

statType.title: statType
statType.description: Indicates the kind of statistic represented by a [[StatisticalVariable]], e.g. mean, count etc. The value of statType is a property, either from within Schema.org (e.g. [[median]], [[marginOfError]], [[maxValue]], [[minValue]]) or from other compatible (e.g. RDF) systems such as DataCommons.org or Wikidata.org.

xpath.title: xpath
xpath.description: An XPath, e.g. of a [[SpeakableSpecification]] or [[WebPageElement]]. In the latter case, multiple matches within a page can constitute a single conceptual "Web page element".

audienceType.title: audienceType
audienceType.description: The target group associated with a given audience (e.g. veterans, car owners, musicians, etc.).

numberOfFullBathrooms.title: numberOfFullBathrooms
numberOfFullBathrooms.description: Number of full bathrooms - The total number of full and ¾ bathrooms in an [[Accommodation]]. This corresponds to the [BathroomsFull field in RESO](https://ddwiki.reso.org/display/DDW17/BathroomsFull+Field).

potentialAction.title: potentialAction
potentialAction.description: Indicates a potential Action, which describes an idealized action in which this thing would play an 'object' role.

toRecipient.title: toRecipient
toRecipient.description: A sub property of recipient. The recipient who was directly sent the message.

guidelineSubject.title: guidelineSubject
guidelineSubject.description: The medical conditions, treatments, etc. that are the subject of the guideline.

coverageEndTime.title: coverageEndTime
coverageEndTime.description: The time when the live blog will stop covering the Event. Note that coverage may continue after the Event concludes.

providesService.title: providesService
providesService.description: The service provided by this channel.

possibleComplication.title: possibleComplication
possibleComplication.description: A possible unexpected and unfavorable evolution of a medical condition. Complications may include worsening of the signs or symptoms of the disease, extension of the condition to other organ systems, etc.

callSign.title: callSign
callSign.description: A [callsign](https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Call_sign), as used in broadcasting and radio communications to identify people, radio and TV stations, or vehicles.

sponsor.title: sponsor
sponsor.description: A person or organization that supports a thing through a pledge, promise, or financial contribution. E.g. a sponsor of a Medical Study or a corporate sponsor of an event.

tongueWeight.title: tongueWeight
tongueWeight.description:
The permitted vertical load (TWR) of a trailer attached to the vehicle. Also referred to as Tongue Load Rating (TLR) or Vertical Load Rating (VLR).

Typical unit code(s): KGM for kilogram, LBR for pound

* Note 1: You can indicate additional information in the [[name]] of the [[QuantitativeValue]] node.
* Note 2: You may also link to a [[QualitativeValue]] node that provides additional information using [[valueReference]].
* Note 3: Note that you can use [[minValue]] and [[maxValue]] to indicate ranges.

webFeed.title: webFeed
webFeed.description: The URL for a feed, e.g. associated with a podcast series, blog, or series of date-stamped updates. This is usually RSS or Atom.

geoCoveredBy.title: geoCoveredBy
geoCoveredBy.description: Represents a relationship between two geometries (or the places they represent), relating a geometry to another that covers it. As defined in [DE-9IM](https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/DE-9IM).

knows.title: knows
knows.description: The most generic bi-directional social/work relation.

geoMidpoint.title: geoMidpoint
geoMidpoint.description: Indicates the GeoCoordinates at the centre of a GeoShape, e.g. GeoCircle.

vehicleSeatingCapacity.title: vehicleSeatingCapacity
vehicleSeatingCapacity.description: The number of passengers that can be seated in the vehicle, both in terms of the physical space available, and in terms of limitations set by law.\n\nTypical unit code(s): C62 for persons.

lesser.title: lesser
lesser.description: This ordering relation for qualitative values indicates that the subject is lesser than the object.

runtime.title: runtime
runtime.description: Runtime platform or script interpreter dependencies (example: Java v1, Python 2.3, .NET Framework 3.0).

partOfSystem.title: partOfSystem
partOfSystem.description: The anatomical or organ system that this structure is part of.

workPresented.title: workPresented
workPresented.description: The movie presented during this event.

recourseLoan.title: recourseLoan
recourseLoan.description: The only way you get the money back in the event of default is the security. Recourse is where you still have the opportunity to go back to the borrower for the rest of the money.

contentReferenceTime.title: contentReferenceTime
contentReferenceTime.description: The specific time described by a creative work, for works (e.g. articles, video objects etc.) that emphasise a particular moment within an Event.

eventAttendanceMode.title: eventAttendanceMode
eventAttendanceMode.description: The eventAttendanceMode of an event indicates whether it occurs online, offline, or a mix.

billingAddress.title: billingAddress
billingAddress.description: The billing address for the order.

merchantReturnDays.title: merchantReturnDays
merchantReturnDays.description: Specifies either a fixed return date or the number of days (from the delivery date) that a product can be returned. Used when the [[returnPolicyCategory]] property is specified as [[MerchantReturnFiniteReturnWindow]].

lender.title: lender
lender.description: A sub property of participant. The person that lends the object being borrowed.

processingTime.title: processingTime
processingTime.description: Estimated processing time for the service using this channel.

ticketToken.title: ticketToken
ticketToken.description: Reference to an asset (e.g., Barcode, QR code image or PDF) usable for entrance.

scheduledPaymentDate.title: scheduledPaymentDate
scheduledPaymentDate.description: The date the invoice is scheduled to be paid.

shippingSettingsLink.title: shippingSettingsLink
shippingSettingsLink.description: Link to a page containing [[ShippingRateSettings]] and [[DeliveryTimeSettings]] details.

query.title: query
query.description: A sub property of instrument. The query used on this action.

afterMedia.title: afterMedia
afterMedia.description: A media object representing the circumstances after performing this direction.

variantCover.title: variantCover
variantCover.description:
A description of the variant cover
    	for the issue, if the issue is a variant printing. For example, "Bryan Hitch
    	Variant Cover" or "2nd Printing Variant".

bitrate.title: bitrate
bitrate.description: The bitrate of the media object.

numberOfPartialBathrooms.title: numberOfPartialBathrooms
numberOfPartialBathrooms.description: Number of partial bathrooms - The total number of half and ¼ bathrooms in an [[Accommodation]]. This corresponds to the [BathroomsPartial field in RESO](https://ddwiki.reso.org/display/DDW17/BathroomsPartial+Field).

sdLicense.title: sdLicense
sdLicense.description: A license document that applies to this structured data, typically indicated by URL.

encoding.title: encoding
encoding.description: A media object that encodes this CreativeWork. This property is a synonym for associatedMedia.

isLiveBroadcast.title: isLiveBroadcast
isLiveBroadcast.description: True if the broadcast is of a live event.

dataset.title: dataset
dataset.description: A dataset contained in this catalog.

estimatedCost.title: estimatedCost
estimatedCost.description: The estimated cost of the supply or supplies consumed when performing instructions.

validForMemberTier.title: validForMemberTier
validForMemberTier.description: The membership program tier an Offer (or a PriceSpecification, OfferShippingDetails, or MerchantReturnPolicy under an Offer) is valid for.

modifiedTime.title: modifiedTime
modifiedTime.description: The date and time the reservation was modified.

homeLocation.title: homeLocation
homeLocation.description: A contact location for a person's residence.

ownershipFundingInfo.title: ownershipFundingInfo
ownershipFundingInfo.description: For an [[Organization]] (often but not necessarily a [[NewsMediaOrganization]]), a description of organizational ownership structure; funding and grants. In a news/media setting, this is with particular reference to editorial independence.   Note that the [[funder]] is also available and can be used to make basic funder information machine-readable.

diet.title: diet
diet.description: A sub property of instrument. The diet used in this action.

albumReleaseType.title: albumReleaseType
albumReleaseType.description: The kind of release which this album is: single, EP or album.

gtin13.title: gtin13
gtin13.description: The GTIN-13 code of the product, or the product to which the offer refers. This is equivalent to 13-digit ISBN codes and EAN UCC-13. Former 12-digit UPC codes can be converted into a GTIN-13 code by simply adding a preceding zero. See [GS1 GTIN Summary](http://www.gs1.org/barcodes/technical/idkeys/gtin) for more details.

duns.title: duns
duns.description: The Dun & Bradstreet DUNS number for identifying an organization or business person.

archiveHeld.title: archiveHeld
archiveHeld.description: Collection, [fonds](https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Fonds), or item held, kept or maintained by an [[ArchiveOrganization]].

followee.title: followee
followee.description: A sub property of object. The person or organization being followed.

birthPlace.title: birthPlace
birthPlace.description: The place where the person was born.

publishedOn.title: publishedOn
publishedOn.description: A broadcast service associated with the publication event.

salaryUponCompletion.title: salaryUponCompletion
salaryUponCompletion.description: The expected salary upon completing the training.

hasDeliveryMethod.title: hasDeliveryMethod
hasDeliveryMethod.description: Method used for delivery or shipping.

productGroupID.title: productGroupID
productGroupID.description: Indicates a textual identifier for a ProductGroup.

hasBioChemEntityPart.title: hasBioChemEntityPart
hasBioChemEntityPart.description: Indicates a BioChemEntity that (in some sense) has this BioChemEntity as a part.

inProductGroupWithID.title: inProductGroupWithID
inProductGroupWithID.description: Indicates the [[productGroupID]] for a [[ProductGroup]] that this product [[isVariantOf]].

dissolutionDate.title: dissolutionDate
dissolutionDate.description: The date that this organization was dissolved.

measurementMethod.title: measurementMethod
measurementMethod.description: A subproperty of [[measurementTechnique]] that can be used for specifying specific methods, in particular via [[MeasurementMethodEnum]].

course.title: course
course.description: A sub property of location. The course where this action was taken.

disambiguatingDescription.title: disambiguatingDescription
disambiguatingDescription.description: A sub property of description. A short description of the item used to disambiguate from other, similar items. Information from other properties (in particular, name) may be necessary for the description to be useful for disambiguation.

location.title: location
location.description: The location of, for example, where an event is happening, where an organization is located, or where an action takes place.

circle.title: circle
circle.description: A circle is the circular region of a specified radius centered at a specified latitude and longitude. A circle is expressed as a pair followed by a radius in meters.

associatedClaimReview.title: associatedClaimReview
associatedClaimReview.description: An associated [[ClaimReview]], related by specific common content, topic or claim. The expectation is that this property would be most typically used in cases where a single activity is conducting both claim reviews and media reviews, in which case [[relatedMediaReview]] would commonly be used on a [[ClaimReview]], while [[relatedClaimReview]] would be used on [[MediaReview]].

thumbnail.title: thumbnail
thumbnail.description: Thumbnail image for an image or video.

broadcastChannelId.title: broadcastChannelId
broadcastChannelId.description: The unique address by which the BroadcastService can be identified in a provider lineup. In US, this is typically a number.

eduQuestionType.title: eduQuestionType
eduQuestionType.description: For questions that are part of learning resources (e.g. Quiz), eduQuestionType indicates the format of question being given. Example: "Multiple choice", "Open ended", "Flashcard".

size.title: size
size.description: A standardized size of a product or creative work, specified either through a simple textual string (for example 'XL', '32Wx34L'), a  QuantitativeValue with a unitCode, or a comprehensive and structured [[SizeSpecification]]; in other cases, the [[width]], [[height]], [[depth]] and [[weight]] properties may be more applicable.

legislationType.title: legislationType
legislationType.description: The type of the legislation. Examples of values are "law", "act", "directive", "decree", "regulation", "statutory instrument", "loi organique", "règlement grand-ducal", etc., depending on the country.

isProprietary.title: isProprietary
isProprietary.description: True if this item's name is a proprietary/brand name (vs. generic name).

gtin12.title: gtin12
gtin12.description: The GTIN-12 code of the product, or the product to which the offer refers. The GTIN-12 is the 12-digit GS1 Identification Key composed of a U.P.C. Company Prefix, Item Reference, and Check Digit used to identify trade items. See [GS1 GTIN Summary](http://www.gs1.org/barcodes/technical/idkeys/gtin) for more details.

model.title: model
model.description: The model of the product. Use with the URL of a ProductModel or a textual representation of the model identifier. The URL of the ProductModel can be from an external source. It is recommended to additionally provide strong product identifiers via the gtin8/gtin13/gtin14 and mpn properties.

includedComposition.title: includedComposition
includedComposition.description: Smaller compositions included in this work (e.g. a movement in a symphony).

areaServed.title: areaServed
areaServed.description: The geographic area where a service or offered item is provided.

transcript.title: transcript
transcript.description: If this MediaObject is an AudioObject or VideoObject, the transcript of that object.

applicableCountry.title: applicableCountry
applicableCountry.description: A country where a particular merchant return policy applies to, for example the two-letter ISO 3166-1 alpha-2 country code.

box.title: box
box.description: A box is the area enclosed by the rectangle formed by two points. The first point is the lower corner, the second point is the upper corner. A box is expressed as two points separated by a space character.

legislationConsolidates.title: legislationConsolidates
legislationConsolidates.description: Indicates another legislation taken into account in this consolidated legislation (which is usually the product of an editorial process that revises the legislation). This property should be used multiple times to refer to both the original version or the previous consolidated version, and to the legislations making the change.

trackingUrl.title: trackingUrl
trackingUrl.description: Tracking url for the parcel delivery.

additionalType.title: additionalType
additionalType.description: An additional type for the item, typically used for adding more specific types from external vocabularies in microdata syntax. This is a relationship between something and a class that the thing is in. Typically the value is a URI-identified RDF class, and in this case corresponds to the use of rdf:type in RDF. Text values can be used sparingly, for cases where useful information can be added without their being an appropriate schema to reference. In the case of text values, the class label should follow the schema.org style guide.

duplicateTherapy.title: duplicateTherapy
duplicateTherapy.description: A therapy that duplicates or overlaps this one.

roofLoad.title: roofLoad
roofLoad.description:
The permitted total weight of cargo and installations (e.g. a roof rack) on top of the vehicle.

Typical unit code(s): KGM for kilogram, LBR for pound

* Note 1: You can indicate additional information in the [[name]] of the [[QuantitativeValue]] node.
* Note 2: You may also link to a [[QualitativeValue]] node that provides additional information using [[valueReference]]
* Note 3: Note that you can use [[minValue]] and [[maxValue]] to indicate ranges.

arterialBranch.title: arterialBranch
arterialBranch.description: The branches that comprise the arterial structure.

materialExtent.title: materialExtent
materialExtent.description: The quantity of the materials being described or an expression of the physical space they occupy.

worstRating.title: worstRating
worstRating.description: The lowest value allowed in this rating system.

reservationFor.title: reservationFor
reservationFor.description: The thing -- flight, event, restaurant, etc. being reserved.

realEstateAgent.title: realEstateAgent
realEstateAgent.description: A sub property of participant. The real estate agent involved in the action.

warrantyScope.title: warrantyScope
warrantyScope.description: The scope of the warranty promise.

releaseDate.title: releaseDate
releaseDate.description: The release date of a product or product model. This can be used to distinguish the exact variant of a product.

startOffset.title: startOffset
startOffset.description: The start time of the clip expressed as the number of seconds from the beginning of the work.

isAcceptingNewPatients.title: isAcceptingNewPatients
isAcceptingNewPatients.description: Whether the provider is accepting new patients.

priceComponentType.title: priceComponentType
priceComponentType.description: Identifies a price component (for example, a line item on an invoice), part of the total price for an offer.

mathExpression.title: mathExpression
mathExpression.description: A mathematical expression (e.g. 'x^2-3x=0') that may be solved for a specific variable, simplified, or transformed. This can take many formats, e.g. LaTeX, Ascii-Math, or math as you would write with a keyboard.

numberOfAxles.title: numberOfAxles
numberOfAxles.description: The number of axles.\n\nTypical unit code(s): C62.

paymentUrl.title: paymentUrl
paymentUrl.description: The URL for sending a payment.

primaryPrevention.title: primaryPrevention
primaryPrevention.description: A preventative therapy used to prevent an initial occurrence of the medical condition, such as vaccination.

isConsumableFor.title: isConsumableFor
isConsumableFor.description: A pointer to another product (or multiple products) for which this product is a consumable.

prepTime.title: prepTime
prepTime.description: The length of time it takes to prepare the items to be used in instructions or a direction, in [ISO 8601 duration format](http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/ISO_8601).

targetCollection.title: targetCollection
targetCollection.description: A sub property of object. The collection target of the action.

signOrSymptom.title: signOrSymptom
signOrSymptom.description: A sign or symptom of this condition. Signs are objective or physically observable manifestations of the medical condition while symptoms are the subjective experience of the medical condition.

warrantyPromise.title: warrantyPromise
warrantyPromise.description: The warranty promise(s) included in the offer.

weightTotal.title: weightTotal
weightTotal.description:
The permitted total weight of the loaded vehicle, including passengers and cargo and the weight of the empty vehicle.

Typical unit code(s): KGM for kilogram, LBR for pound

* Note 1: You can indicate additional information in the [[name]] of the [[QuantitativeValue]] node.
* Note 2: You may also link to a [[QualitativeValue]] node that provides additional information using [[valueReference]].
* Note 3: Note that you can use [[minValue]] and [[maxValue]] to indicate ranges.

valueMaxLength.title: valueMaxLength
valueMaxLength.description: Specifies the allowed range for number of characters in a literal value.

awards.title: awards
awards.description: Awards won by or for this item.

recipe.title: recipe
recipe.description: A sub property of instrument. The recipe/instructions used to perform the action.

suitableForDiet.title: suitableForDiet
suitableForDiet.description: Indicates a dietary restriction or guideline for which this recipe or menu item is suitable, e.g. diabetic, halal etc.

preOp.title: preOp
preOp.description: A description of the workup, testing, and other preparations required before implanting this device.

upvoteCount.title: upvoteCount
upvoteCount.description: The number of upvotes this question, answer or comment has received from the community.

grantee.title: grantee
grantee.description: The person, organization, contact point, or audience that has been granted this permission.

workLocation.title: workLocation
workLocation.description: A contact location for a person's place of work.

device.title: device
device.description: Device required to run the application. Used in cases where a specific make/model is required to run the application.

competitor.title: competitor
competitor.description: A competitor in a sports event.

produces.title: produces
produces.description: The tangible thing generated by the service, e.g. a passport, permit, etc.

healthPlanCoinsuranceRate.title: healthPlanCoinsuranceRate
healthPlanCoinsuranceRate.description: The rate of coinsurance expressed as a number between 0.0 and 1.0.

confirmationNumber.title: confirmationNumber
confirmationNumber.description: A number that confirms the given order or payment has been received.

membershipNumber.title: membershipNumber
membershipNumber.description: A unique identifier for the membership.

readonlyValue.title: readonlyValue
readonlyValue.description: Whether or not a property is mutable.  Default is false. Specifying this for a property that also has a value makes it act similar to a "hidden" input in an HTML form.

originalMediaLink.title: originalMediaLink
originalMediaLink.description: Link to the page containing an original version of the content, or directly to an online copy of the original [[MediaObject]] content, e.g. video file.

certificationStatus.title: certificationStatus
certificationStatus.description: Indicates the current status of a certification: active or inactive. See also  [gs1:certificationStatus](https://www.gs1.org/voc/certificationStatus).

numTracks.title: numTracks
numTracks.description: The number of tracks in this album or playlist.

successorOf.title: successorOf
successorOf.description: A pointer from a newer variant of a product  to its previous, often discontinued predecessor.

noBylinesPolicy.title: noBylinesPolicy
noBylinesPolicy.description: For a [[NewsMediaOrganization]] or other news-related [[Organization]], a statement explaining when authors of articles are not named in bylines.

missionCoveragePrioritiesPolicy.title: missionCoveragePrioritiesPolicy
missionCoveragePrioritiesPolicy.description: For a [[NewsMediaOrganization]], a statement on coverage priorities, including any public agenda or stance on issues.

requiredMinAge.title: requiredMinAge
requiredMinAge.description: Audiences defined by a person's minimum age.

instructor.title: instructor
instructor.description: A person assigned to instruct or provide instructional assistance for the [[CourseInstance]].

characterName.title: characterName
characterName.description: The name of a character played in some acting or performing role, i.e. in a PerformanceRole.

answerCount.title: answerCount
answerCount.description: The number of answers this question has received.

character.title: character
character.description: Fictional person connected with a creative work.

loanTerm.title: loanTerm
loanTerm.description: The duration of the loan or credit agreement.

partOfInvoice.title: partOfInvoice
partOfInvoice.description: The order is being paid as part of the referenced Invoice.

checkinTime.title: checkinTime
checkinTime.description: The earliest someone may check into a lodging establishment.

founder.title: founder
founder.description: A person or organization who founded this organization.

freeShippingThreshold.title: freeShippingThreshold
freeShippingThreshold.description: A monetary value above (or at) which the shipping rate becomes free. Intended to be used via an [[OfferShippingDetails]] with [[shippingSettingsLink]] matching this [[ShippingRateSettings]].

parentTaxon.title: parentTaxon
parentTaxon.description: Closest parent taxon of the taxon in question.

iupacName.title: iupacName
iupacName.description: Systematic method of naming chemical compounds as recommended by the International Union of Pure and Applied Chemistry (IUPAC).

surface.title: surface
surface.description: A material used as a surface in some artwork, e.g. Canvas, Paper, Wood, Board, etc.

episodeNumber.title: episodeNumber
episodeNumber.description: Position of the episode within an ordered group of episodes.

partOfSeries.title: partOfSeries
partOfSeries.description: The series to which this episode or season belongs.

ticketedSeat.title: ticketedSeat
ticketedSeat.description: The seat associated with the ticket.

reviewAspect.title: reviewAspect
reviewAspect.description: This Review or Rating is relevant to this part or facet of the itemReviewed.

increasesRiskOf.title: increasesRiskOf
increasesRiskOf.description: The condition, complication, etc. influenced by this factor.

workHours.title: workHours
workHours.description: The typical working hours for this job (e.g. 1st shift, night shift, 8am-5pm).

performTime.title: performTime
performTime.description: The length of time it takes to perform instructions or a direction (not including time to prepare the supplies), in [ISO 8601 duration format](http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/ISO_8601).

beneficiaryBank.title: beneficiaryBank
beneficiaryBank.description: A bank or bank’s branch, financial institution or international financial institution operating the beneficiary’s bank account or releasing funds for the beneficiary.

customerRemorseReturnShippingFeesAmount.title: customerRemorseReturnShippingFeesAmount
customerRemorseReturnShippingFeesAmount.description: The amount of shipping costs if a product is returned due to customer remorse. Applicable when property [[customerRemorseReturnFees]] equals [[ReturnShippingFees]].

screenshot.title: screenshot
screenshot.description: A link to a screenshot image of the app.

toLocation.title: toLocation
toLocation.description: A sub property of location. The final location of the object or the agent after the action.

productID.title: productID
productID.description: The product identifier, such as ISBN. For example: ``` meta itemprop="productID" content="isbn:123-456-789" ```.

translationOfWork.title: translationOfWork
translationOfWork.description: The work that this work has been translated from. E.g. 物种起源 is a translationOf “On the Origin of Species”.

modelDate.title: modelDate
modelDate.description: The release date of a vehicle model (often used to differentiate versions of the same make and model).

isPartOfBioChemEntity.title: isPartOfBioChemEntity
isPartOfBioChemEntity.description: Indicates a BioChemEntity that is (in some sense) a part of this BioChemEntity.

publisherImprint.title: publisherImprint
publisherImprint.description: The publishing division which published the comic.

observationAbout.title: observationAbout
observationAbout.description: The [[observationAbout]] property identifies an entity, often a [[Place]], associated with an [[Observation]].

cargoVolume.title: cargoVolume
cargoVolume.description:
The available volume for cargo or luggage. For automobiles, this is usually the trunk volume.

Typical unit code(s): LTR for liters, FTQ for cubic foot/feet

Note: You can use [[minValue]] and [[maxValue]] to indicate ranges.

partySize.title: partySize
partySize.description: Number of people the reservation should accommodate.

typicalTest.title: typicalTest
typicalTest.description: A medical test typically performed given this condition.

dosageForm.title: dosageForm
dosageForm.description: A dosage form in which this drug/supplement is available, e.g. 'tablet', 'suspension', 'injection'.

accessModeSufficient.title: accessModeSufficient
accessModeSufficient.description: A list of single or combined accessModes that are sufficient to understand all the intellectual content of a resource. Values should be drawn from the [approved vocabulary](https://www.w3.org/2021/a11y-discov-vocab/latest/#accessModeSufficient-vocabulary).

occupationLocation.title: occupationLocation
occupationLocation.description: The region/country for which this occupational description is appropriate. Note that educational requirements and qualifications can vary between jurisdictions.

specialCommitments.title: specialCommitments
specialCommitments.description: Any special commitments associated with this job posting. Valid entries include VeteranCommit, MilitarySpouseCommit, etc.

ratingExplanation.title: ratingExplanation
ratingExplanation.description: A short explanation (e.g. one to two sentences) providing background context and other information that led to the conclusion expressed in the rating. This is particularly applicable to ratings associated with "fact check" markup using [[ClaimReview]].

diseaseSpreadStatistics.title: diseaseSpreadStatistics
diseaseSpreadStatistics.description:
Statistical information about the spread of a disease, either as [[WebContent]], or
  described directly as a [[Dataset]], or the specific [[Observation]]s in the dataset. When a [[WebContent]] URL is
  provided, the page indicated might also contain more such markup.

author.title: author
author.description: The author of this content or rating. Please note that author is special in that HTML 5 provides a special mechanism for indicating authorship via the rel tag. That is equivalent to this and may be used interchangeably.

floorLevel.title: floorLevel
floorLevel.description:
The floor level for an [[Accommodation]] in a multi-storey building. Since counting
  systems [vary internationally](https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Storey#Consecutive_number_floor_designations), the local system should be used where possible.

valueRequired.title: valueRequired
valueRequired.description: Whether the property must be filled in to complete the action.  Default is false.

cvdNumC19MechVentPats.title: cvdNumC19MechVentPats
cvdNumC19MechVentPats.description: numc19mechventpats - HOSPITALIZED and VENTILATED: Patients hospitalized in an NHSN inpatient care location who have suspected or confirmed COVID-19 and are on a mechanical ventilator.

acquireLicensePage.title: acquireLicensePage
acquireLicensePage.description: Indicates a page documenting how licenses can be purchased or otherwise acquired, for the current item.

partOfTVSeries.title: partOfTVSeries
partOfTVSeries.description: The TV series to which this episode or season belongs.

correctionsPolicy.title: correctionsPolicy
correctionsPolicy.description: For an [[Organization]] (e.g. [[NewsMediaOrganization]]), a statement describing (in news media, the newsroom’s) disclosure and correction policy for errors.

smiles.title: smiles
smiles.description: A specification in form of a line notation for describing the structure of chemical species using short ASCII strings.  Double bond stereochemistry \ indicators may need to be escaped in the string in formats where the backslash is an escape character.

minimumPaymentDue.title: minimumPaymentDue
minimumPaymentDue.description: The minimum payment required at this time.

accessCode.title: accessCode
accessCode.description: Password, PIN, or access code needed for delivery (e.g. from a locker).

colorist.title: colorist
colorist.description: The individual who adds color to inked drawings.

sportsTeam.title: sportsTeam
sportsTeam.description: A sub property of participant. The sports team that participated on this action.

diagram.title: diagram
diagram.description: An image containing a diagram that illustrates the structure and/or its component substructures and/or connections with other structures.

sensoryUnit.title: sensoryUnit
sensoryUnit.description: The neurological pathway extension that inputs and sends information to the brain or spinal cord.

distinguishingSign.title: distinguishingSign
distinguishingSign.description: One of a set of signs and symptoms that can be used to distinguish this diagnosis from others in the differential diagnosis.

penciler.title: penciler
penciler.description: The individual who draws the primary narrative artwork.

position.title: position
position.description: The position of an item in a series or sequence of items.

healthPlanDrugTier.title: healthPlanDrugTier
healthPlanDrugTier.description: The tier(s) of drugs offered by this formulary or insurance plan.

playersOnline.title: playersOnline
playersOnline.description: Number of players on the server.

bodyLocation.title: bodyLocation
bodyLocation.description: Location in the body of the anatomical structure.

broadcastAffiliateOf.title: broadcastAffiliateOf
broadcastAffiliateOf.description: The media network(s) whose content is broadcast on this station.

asin.title: asin
asin.description:
An Amazon Standard Identification Number (ASIN) is a 10-character alphanumeric unique identifier assigned by Amazon.com and its partners for product identification within the Amazon organization (summary from [Wikipedia](https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Amazon_Standard_Identification_Number)'s article).

Note also that this is a definition for how to include ASINs in Schema.org data, and not a definition of ASINs in general - see documentation from Amazon for authoritative details.
ASINs are most commonly encoded as text strings, but the [asin] property supports URL/URI as potential values too.

loanType.title: loanType
loanType.description: The type of a loan or credit.

incentiveCompensation.title: incentiveCompensation
incentiveCompensation.description: Description of bonus and commission compensation aspects of the job.

superEvent.title: superEvent
superEvent.description: An event that this event is a part of. For example, a collection of individual music performances might each have a music festival as their superEvent.

productionDate.title: productionDate
productionDate.description: The date of production of the item, e.g. vehicle.

arrivalBusStop.title: arrivalBusStop
arrivalBusStop.description: The stop or station from which the bus arrives.

price.title: price
price.description:
The offer price of a product, or of a price component when attached to PriceSpecification and its subtypes.

Usage guidelines:

* Use the [[priceCurrency]] property (with standard formats: [ISO 4217 currency format](http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/ISO_4217), e.g. "USD"; [Ticker symbol](https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/List_of_cryptocurrencies) for cryptocurrencies, e.g. "BTC"; well known names for [Local Exchange Trading Systems](https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Local_exchange_trading_system) (LETS) and other currency types, e.g. "Ithaca HOUR") instead of including [ambiguous symbols](http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Dollar_sign#Currencies_that_use_the_dollar_or_peso_sign) such as '$' in the value.
* Use '.' (Unicode 'FULL STOP' (U+002E)) rather than ',' to indicate a decimal point. Avoid using these symbols as a readability separator.
* Note that both [RDFa](http://www.w3.org/TR/xhtml-rdfa-primer/#using-the-content-attribute) and Microdata syntax allow the use of a "content=" attribute for publishing simple machine-readable values alongside more human-friendly formatting.
* Use values from 0123456789 (Unicode 'DIGIT ZERO' (U+0030) to 'DIGIT NINE' (U+0039)) rather than superficially similar Unicode symbols.

amenityFeature.title: amenityFeature
amenityFeature.description: An amenity feature (e.g. a characteristic or service) of the Accommodation. This generic property does not make a statement about whether the feature is included in an offer for the main accommodation or available at extra costs.

vehicleEngine.title: vehicleEngine
vehicleEngine.description: Information about the engine or engines of the vehicle.

legislationChanges.title: legislationChanges
legislationChanges.description: Another legislation that this legislation changes. This encompasses the notions of amendment, replacement, correction, repeal, or other types of change. This may be a direct change (textual or non-textual amendment) or a consequential or indirect change. The property is to be used to express the existence of a change relationship between two acts rather than the existence of a consolidated version of the text that shows the result of the change. For consolidation relationships, use the legislationConsolidates property.

lesserOrEqual.title: lesserOrEqual
lesserOrEqual.description: This ordering relation for qualitative values indicates that the subject is lesser than or equal to the object.

medicalSpecialty.title: medicalSpecialty
medicalSpecialty.description: A medical specialty of the provider.

validThrough.title: validThrough
validThrough.description: The date after when the item is not valid. For example the end of an offer, salary period, or a period of opening hours.

hasMemberProgram.title: hasMemberProgram
hasMemberProgram.description: MemberProgram offered by an Organization, for example an eCommerce merchant or an airline.

thumbnailUrl.title: thumbnailUrl
thumbnailUrl.description: A thumbnail image relevant to the Thing.

characterAttribute.title: characterAttribute
characterAttribute.description: A piece of data that represents a particular aspect of a fictional character (skill, power, character points, advantage, disadvantage).

returnFees.title: returnFees
returnFees.description: The type of return fees for purchased products (for any return reason).

employmentUnit.title: employmentUnit
employmentUnit.description: Indicates the department, unit and/or facility where the employee reports and/or in which the job is to be performed.

procedure.title: procedure
procedure.description: A description of the procedure involved in setting up, using, and/or installing the device.

tripOrigin.title: tripOrigin
tripOrigin.description: The location of origin of the trip, prior to any destination(s).

pagination.title: pagination
pagination.description: Any description of pages that is not separated into pageStart and pageEnd; for example, "1-6, 9, 55" or "10-12, 46-49".

inAlbum.title: inAlbum
inAlbum.description: The album to which this recording belongs.

saturatedFatContent.title: saturatedFatContent
saturatedFatContent.description: The number of grams of saturated fat.

studySubject.title: studySubject
studySubject.description: A subject of the study, i.e. one of the medical conditions, therapies, devices, drugs, etc. investigated by the study.

geo.title: geo
geo.description: The geo coordinates of the place.

merchantReturnLink.title: merchantReturnLink
merchantReturnLink.description: Specifies a Web page or service by URL, for product returns.

costCurrency.title: costCurrency
costCurrency.description: The currency (in 3-letter) of the drug cost. See: http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/ISO_4217.

availabilityEnds.title: availabilityEnds
availabilityEnds.description: The end of the availability of the product or service included in the offer.

acrissCode.title: acrissCode
acrissCode.description: The ACRISS Car Classification Code is a code used by many car rental companies, for classifying vehicles. ACRISS stands for Association of Car Rental Industry Systems and Standards.

naics.title: naics
naics.description: The North American Industry Classification System (NAICS) code for a particular organization or business person.

priceRange.title: priceRange
priceRange.description: The price range of the business, for example ```$$$```.

interestRate.title: interestRate
interestRate.description: The interest rate, charged or paid, applicable to the financial product. Note: This is different from the calculated annualPercentageRate.

game.title: game
game.description: Video game which is played on this server.

usesDevice.title: usesDevice
usesDevice.description: Device used to perform the test.

measuredProperty.title: measuredProperty
measuredProperty.description: The measuredProperty of an [[Observation]], typically via its [[StatisticalVariable]]. There are various kinds of applicable [[Property]]: a schema.org property, a property from other RDF-compatible systems, e.g. W3C RDF Data Cube, Data Commons, Wikidata, or schema.org extensions such as [GS1's](https://www.gs1.org/voc/?show=properties).

diversityPolicy.title: diversityPolicy
diversityPolicy.description: Statement on diversity policy by an [[Organization]] e.g. a [[NewsMediaOrganization]]. For a [[NewsMediaOrganization]], a statement describing the newsroom’s diversity policy on both staffing and sources, typically providing staffing data.

hasPart.title: hasPart
hasPart.description: Indicates an item or CreativeWork that is part of this item, or CreativeWork (in some sense).

gender.title: gender
gender.description: Gender of something, typically a [[Person]], but possibly also fictional characters, animals, etc. While https://schema.org/Male and https://schema.org/Female may be used, text strings are also acceptable for people who do not identify as a binary gender. The [[gender]] property can also be used in an extended sense to cover e.g. the gender of sports teams. As with the gender of individuals, we do not try to enumerate all possibilities. A mixed-gender [[SportsTeam]] can be indicated with a text value of "Mixed".

accountablePerson.title: accountablePerson
accountablePerson.description: Specifies the Person that is legally accountable for the CreativeWork.

trainingSalary.title: trainingSalary
trainingSalary.description: The estimated salary earned while in the program.

parentService.title: parentService
parentService.description: A broadcast service to which the broadcast service may belong to such as regional variations of a national channel.

hasRepresentation.title: hasRepresentation
hasRepresentation.description: A common representation such as a protein sequence or chemical structure for this entity. For images use schema.org/image.

clipNumber.title: clipNumber
clipNumber.description: Position of the clip within an ordered group of clips.

returnShippingFeesAmount.title: returnShippingFeesAmount
returnShippingFeesAmount.description: Amount of shipping costs for product returns (for any reason). Applicable when property [[returnFees]] equals [[ReturnShippingFees]].

additionalProperty.title: additionalProperty
additionalProperty.description: A property-value pair representing an additional characteristic of the entity, e.g. a product feature or another characteristic for which there is no matching property in schema.org.\n\nNote: Publishers should be aware that applications designed to use specific schema.org properties (e.g. https://schema.org/width, https://schema.org/color, https://schema.org/gtin13, ...) will typically expect such data to be provided using those properties, rather than using the generic property/value mechanism.

eventSchedule.title: eventSchedule
eventSchedule.description:
Associates an [[Event]] with a [[Schedule]]. There are circumstances where it is preferable to share a schedule for a series of
      repeating events rather than data on the individual events themselves. For example, a website or application might prefer to publish a schedule for a weekly
      gym class rather than provide data on every event. A schedule could be processed by applications to add forthcoming events to a calendar. An [[Event]] that
      is associated with a [[Schedule]] using this property should not have [[startDate]] or [[endDate]] properties. These are instead defined within the associated
      [[Schedule]], this avoids any ambiguity for clients using the data. The property might have repeated values to specify different schedules, e.g. for different months
      or seasons.

qualifications.title: qualifications
qualifications.description: Specific qualifications required for this role or Occupation.

multipleValues.title: multipleValues
multipleValues.description: Whether multiple values are allowed for the property.  Default is false.

prescriptionStatus.title: prescriptionStatus
prescriptionStatus.description: Indicates the status of drug prescription, e.g. local catalogs classifications or whether the drug is available by prescription or over-the-counter, etc.

availableDeliveryMethod.title: availableDeliveryMethod
availableDeliveryMethod.description: The delivery method(s) available for this offer.

ticketNumber.title: ticketNumber
ticketNumber.description: The unique identifier for the ticket.

geoRadius.title: geoRadius
geoRadius.description: Indicates the approximate radius of a GeoCircle (metres unless indicated otherwise via Distance notation).

courseWorkload.title: courseWorkload
courseWorkload.description: The amount of work expected of students taking the course, often provided as a figure per week or per month, and may be broken down by type. For example, "2 hours of lectures, 1 hour of lab work and 3 hours of independent study per week".

courseSchedule.title: courseSchedule
courseSchedule.description: Represents the length and pace of a course, expressed as a [[Schedule]].

typeOfGood.title: typeOfGood
typeOfGood.description: The product that this structured value is referring to.

hasPOS.title: hasPOS
hasPOS.description: Points-of-Sales operated by the organization or person.

instrument.title: instrument
instrument.description: The object that helped the agent perform the action. E.g. John wrote a book with *a pen*.

department.title: department
department.description: A relationship between an organization and a department of that organization, also described as an organization (allowing different urls, logos, opening hours). For example: a store with a pharmacy, or a bakery with a cafe.

geoIntersects.title: geoIntersects
geoIntersects.description: Represents spatial relations in which two geometries (or the places they represent) have at least one point in common. As defined in [DE-9IM](https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/DE-9IM).

actionApplication.title: actionApplication
actionApplication.description: An application that can complete the request.

competencyRequired.title: competencyRequired
competencyRequired.description: Knowledge, skill, ability or personal attribute that must be demonstrated by a person or other entity in order to do something such as earn an Educational Occupational Credential or understand a LearningResource.

documentation.title: documentation
documentation.description: Further documentation describing the Web API in more detail.

stepValue.title: stepValue
stepValue.description: The stepValue attribute indicates the granularity that is expected (and required) of the value in a PropertyValueSpecification.

expectedArrivalFrom.title: expectedArrivalFrom
expectedArrivalFrom.description: The earliest date the package may arrive.

artMedium.title: artMedium
artMedium.description: The material used. (E.g. Oil, Watercolour, Acrylic, Linoprint, Marble, Cyanotype, Digital, Lithograph, DryPoint, Intaglio, Pastel, Woodcut, Pencil, Mixed Media, etc.)

vehicleTransmission.title: vehicleTransmission
vehicleTransmission.description: The type of component used for transmitting the power from a rotating power source to the wheels or other relevant component(s) ("gearbox" for cars).

geoEquals.title: geoEquals
geoEquals.description: Represents spatial relations in which two geometries (or the places they represent) are topologically equal, as defined in [DE-9IM](https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/DE-9IM). "Two geometries are topologically equal if their interiors intersect and no part of the interior or boundary of one geometry intersects the exterior of the other" (a symmetric relationship).

administrationRoute.title: administrationRoute
administrationRoute.description: A route by which this drug may be administered, e.g. 'oral'.

appearance.title: appearance
appearance.description: Indicates an occurrence of a [[Claim]] in some [[CreativeWork]].

candidate.title: candidate
candidate.description: A sub property of object. The candidate subject of this action.

contributor.title: contributor
contributor.description: A secondary contributor to the CreativeWork or Event.

fuelEfficiency.title: fuelEfficiency
fuelEfficiency.description:
The distance traveled per unit of fuel used; most commonly miles per gallon (mpg) or kilometers per liter (km/L).

* Note 1: There are unfortunately no standard unit codes for miles per gallon or kilometers per liter. Use [[unitText]] to indicate the unit of measurement, e.g. mpg or km/L.
* Note 2: There are two ways of indicating the fuel consumption, [[fuelConsumption]] (e.g. 8 liters per 100 km) and [[fuelEfficiency]] (e.g. 30 miles per gallon). They are reciprocal.
* Note 3: Often, the absolute value is useful only when related to driving speed ("at 80 km/h") or usage pattern ("city traffic"). You can use [[valueReference]] to link the value for the fuel economy to another value.

applicationDeadline.title: applicationDeadline
applicationDeadline.description: The date at which the program stops collecting applications for the next enrollment cycle.

priceSpecification.title: priceSpecification
priceSpecification.description: One or more detailed price specifications, indicating the unit price and delivery or payment charges.

fromLocation.title: fromLocation
fromLocation.description: A sub property of location. The original location of the object or the agent before the action.

countryOfAssembly.title: countryOfAssembly
countryOfAssembly.description: The place where the product was assembled.

deliveryTime.title: deliveryTime
deliveryTime.description: The total delay between the receipt of the order and the goods reaching the final customer.

payload.title: payload
payload.description:
The permitted weight of passengers and cargo, EXCLUDING the weight of the empty vehicle.

Typical unit code(s): KGM for kilogram, LBR for pound

* Note 1: Many databases specify the permitted TOTAL weight instead, which is the sum of [[weight]] and [[payload]]
* Note 2: You can indicate additional information in the [[name]] of the [[QuantitativeValue]] node.
* Note 3: You may also link to a [[QualitativeValue]] node that provides additional information using [[valueReference]].
* Note 4: Note that you can use [[minValue]] and [[maxValue]] to indicate ranges.

healthPlanPharmacyCategory.title: healthPlanPharmacyCategory
healthPlanPharmacyCategory.description: The category or type of pharmacy associated with this cost sharing.

orderStatus.title: orderStatus
orderStatus.description: The current status of the order.

iswcCode.title: iswcCode
iswcCode.description: The International Standard Musical Work Code for the composition.

arrivalBoatTerminal.title: arrivalBoatTerminal
arrivalBoatTerminal.description: The terminal or port from which the boat arrives.

replacee.title: replacee
replacee.description: A sub property of object. The object that is being replaced.

checkoutPageURLTemplate.title: checkoutPageURLTemplate
checkoutPageURLTemplate.description: A URL template (RFC 6570) for a checkout page for an offer. This approach allows merchants to specify a URL for online checkout of the offered product, by interpolating parameters such as the logged in user ID, product ID, quantity, discount code etc. Parameter naming and standardization are not specified here.

license.title: license
license.description: A license document that applies to this content, typically indicated by URL.

track.title: track
track.description: A music recording (track)—usually a single song. If an ItemList is given, the list should contain items of type MusicRecording.

childTaxon.title: childTaxon
childTaxon.description: Closest child taxa of the taxon in question.

iataCode.title: iataCode
iataCode.description: IATA identifier for an airline or airport.

exampleOfWork.title: exampleOfWork
exampleOfWork.description: A creative work that this work is an example/instance/realization/derivation of.

permitAudience.title: permitAudience
permitAudience.description: The target audience for this permit.

availableIn.title: availableIn
availableIn.description: The location in which the strength is available.

provider.title: provider
provider.description: The service provider, service operator, or service performer; the goods producer. Another party (a seller) may offer those services or goods on behalf of the provider. A provider may also serve as the seller.

embedUrl.title: embedUrl
embedUrl.description: A URL pointing to a player for a specific video. In general, this is the information in the ```src``` element of an ```embed``` tag and should not be the same as the content of the ```loc``` tag.

vehicleModelDate.title: vehicleModelDate
vehicleModelDate.description: The release date of a vehicle model (often used to differentiate versions of the same make and model).

workFeatured.title: workFeatured
workFeatured.description:
A work featured in some event, e.g. exhibited in an ExhibitionEvent.
       Specific subproperties are available for workPerformed (e.g. a play), or a workPresented (a Movie at a ScreeningEvent).

pickupLocation.title: pickupLocation
pickupLocation.description: Where a taxi will pick up a passenger or a rental car can be picked up.

leaseLength.title: leaseLength
leaseLength.description: Length of the lease for some [[Accommodation]], either particular to some [[Offer]] or in some cases intrinsic to the property.

sdDatePublished.title: sdDatePublished
sdDatePublished.description: Indicates the date on which the current structured data was generated / published. Typically used alongside [[sdPublisher]].

buyer.title: buyer
buyer.description: A sub property of participant. The participant/person/organization that bought the object.

permissions.title: permissions
permissions.description: Permission(s) required to run the app (for example, a mobile app may require full internet access or may run only on wifi).

requirements.title: requirements
requirements.description: Component dependency requirements for application. This includes runtime environments and shared libraries that are not included in the application distribution package, but required to run the application (examples: DirectX, Java or .NET runtime).

numberOfForwardGears.title: numberOfForwardGears
numberOfForwardGears.description: The total number of forward gears available for the transmission system of the vehicle.\n\nTypical unit code(s): C62.

relevantSpecialty.title: relevantSpecialty
relevantSpecialty.description: If applicable, a medical specialty in which this entity is relevant.

steps.title: steps
steps.description: A single step item (as HowToStep, text, document, video, etc.) or a HowToSection (originally misnamed 'steps'; 'step' is preferred).

possibleTreatment.title: possibleTreatment
possibleTreatment.description: A possible treatment to address this condition, sign or symptom.

titleEIDR.title: titleEIDR
titleEIDR.description:
An [EIDR](https://eidr.org/) (Entertainment Identifier Registry) [[identifier]] representing at the most general/abstract level, a work of film or television.

For example, the motion picture known as "Ghostbusters" has a titleEIDR of  "10.5240/7EC7-228A-510A-053E-CBB8-J". This title (or work) may have several variants, which EIDR calls "edits". See [[editEIDR]].

Since schema.org types like [[Movie]], [[TVEpisode]], [[TVSeason]], and [[TVSeries]] can be used for both works and their multiple expressions, it is possible to use [[titleEIDR]] alone (for a general description), or alongside [[editEIDR]] for a more edit-specific description.

bestRating.title: bestRating
bestRating.description: The highest value allowed in this rating system.

vehicleInteriorType.title: vehicleInteriorType
vehicleInteriorType.description: The type or material of the interior of the vehicle (e.g. synthetic fabric, leather, wood, etc.). While most interior types are characterized by the material used, an interior type can also be based on vehicle usage or target audience.

printEdition.title: printEdition
printEdition.description: The edition of the print product in which the NewsArticle appears.

assesses.title: assesses
assesses.description: The item being described is intended to assess the competency or learning outcome defined by the referenced term.

postalCodeBegin.title: postalCodeBegin
postalCodeBegin.description: First postal code in a range (included).

teaches.title: teaches
teaches.description: The item being described is intended to help a person learn the competency or learning outcome defined by the referenced term.

customerRemorseReturnFees.title: customerRemorseReturnFees
customerRemorseReturnFees.description: The type of return fees if the product is returned due to customer remorse.

mediaAuthenticityCategory.title: mediaAuthenticityCategory
mediaAuthenticityCategory.description: Indicates a MediaManipulationRatingEnumeration classification of a media object (in the context of how it was published or shared).

numberOfRooms.title: numberOfRooms
numberOfRooms.description:
The number of rooms (excluding bathrooms and closets) of the accommodation or lodging business.
Typical unit code(s): ROM for room or C62 for no unit. The type of room can be put in the unitText property of the QuantitativeValue.

bed.title: bed
bed.description:
The type of bed or beds included in the accommodation. For the single case of just one bed of a certain type, you use bed directly with a text.
      If you want to indicate the quantity of a certain kind of bed, use an instance of BedDetails. For more detailed information, use the amenityFeature property.

itemDefectReturnLabelSource.title: itemDefectReturnLabelSource
itemDefectReturnLabelSource.description: The method (from an enumeration) by which the customer obtains a return shipping label for a defect product.

lyricist.title: lyricist
lyricist.description: The person who wrote the words.

proteinContent.title: proteinContent
proteinContent.description: The number of grams of protein.

domainIncludes.title: domainIncludes
domainIncludes.description: Relates a property to a class that is (one of) the type(s) the property is expected to be used on.

accountMinimumInflow.title: accountMinimumInflow
accountMinimumInflow.description: A minimum amount that has to be paid in every month.

correction.title: correction
correction.description: Indicates a correction to a [[CreativeWork]], either via a [[CorrectionComment]], textually or in another document.

servicePhone.title: servicePhone
servicePhone.description: The phone number to use to access the service.

yearBuilt.title: yearBuilt
yearBuilt.description: The year an [[Accommodation]] was constructed. This corresponds to the [YearBuilt field in RESO](https://ddwiki.reso.org/display/DDW17/YearBuilt+Field).

sportsEvent.title: sportsEvent
sportsEvent.description: A sub property of location. The sports event where this action occurred.

itemDefectReturnFees.title: itemDefectReturnFees
itemDefectReturnFees.description: The type of return fees for returns of defect products.

installUrl.title: installUrl
installUrl.description: URL at which the app may be installed, if different from the URL of the item.

expectsAcceptanceOf.title: expectsAcceptanceOf
expectsAcceptanceOf.description: An Offer which must be accepted before the user can perform the Action. For example, the user may need to buy a movie before being able to watch it.

validFor.title: validFor
validFor.description: The duration of validity of a permit or similar thing.

cvdNumBedsOcc.title: cvdNumBedsOcc
cvdNumBedsOcc.description: numbedsocc - HOSPITAL INPATIENT BED OCCUPANCY: Total number of staffed inpatient beds that are occupied.

countriesSupported.title: countriesSupported
countriesSupported.description: Countries for which the application is supported. You can also provide the two-letter ISO 3166-1 alpha-2 country code.

availabilityStarts.title: availabilityStarts
availabilityStarts.description: The beginning of the availability of the product or service included in the offer.

dateCreated.title: dateCreated
dateCreated.description: The date on which the CreativeWork was created or the item was added to a DataFeed.

fuelType.title: fuelType
fuelType.description: The type of fuel suitable for the engine or engines of the vehicle. If the vehicle has only one engine, this property can be attached directly to the vehicle.

cutoffTime.title: cutoffTime
cutoffTime.description: Order cutoff time allows merchants to describe the time after which they will no longer process orders received on that day. For orders processed after cutoff time, one day gets added to the delivery time estimate. This property is expected to be most typically used via the [[ShippingRateSettings]] publication pattern. The time is indicated using the ISO-8601 Time format, e.g. "23:30:00-05:00" would represent 6:30 pm Eastern Standard Time (EST) which is 5 hours behind Coordinated Universal Time (UTC).

hasCourse.title: hasCourse
hasCourse.description: A course or class that is one of the learning opportunities that constitute an educational / occupational program. No information is implied about whether the course is mandatory or optional; no guarantee is implied about whether the course will be available to everyone on the program.

newsUpdatesAndGuidelines.title: newsUpdatesAndGuidelines
newsUpdatesAndGuidelines.description: Indicates a page with news updates and guidelines. This could often be (but is not required to be) the main page containing [[SpecialAnnouncement]] markup on a site.

programType.title: programType
programType.description: The type of educational or occupational program. For example, classroom, internship, alternance, etc.

cssSelector.title: cssSelector
cssSelector.description: A CSS selector, e.g. of a [[SpeakableSpecification]] or [[WebPageElement]]. In the latter case, multiple matches within a page can constitute a single conceptual "Web page element".

previousStartDate.title: previousStartDate
previousStartDate.description: Used in conjunction with eventStatus for rescheduled or cancelled events. This property contains the previously scheduled start date. For rescheduled events, the startDate property should be used for the newly scheduled start date. In the (rare) case of an event that has been postponed and rescheduled multiple times, this field may be repeated.

itemDefectReturnShippingFeesAmount.title: itemDefectReturnShippingFeesAmount
itemDefectReturnShippingFeesAmount.description: Amount of shipping costs for defect product returns. Applicable when property [[itemDefectReturnFees]] equals [[ReturnShippingFees]].

expires.title: expires
expires.description: Date the content expires and is no longer useful or available. For example a [[VideoObject]] or [[NewsArticle]] whose availability or relevance is time-limited, a [[ClaimReview]] fact check whose publisher wants to indicate that it may no longer be relevant (or helpful to highlight) after some date, or a [[Certification]] the validity has expired.

hasTierRequirement.title: hasTierRequirement
hasTierRequirement.description: A requirement for a user to join a membership tier, for example: a CreditCard if the tier requires sign up for a credit card, A UnitPriceSpecification if the user is required to pay a (periodic) fee, or a MonetaryAmount if the user needs to spend a minimum amount to join the tier. If a tier is free to join then this property does not need to be specified.

distance.title: distance
distance.description: The distance travelled, e.g. exercising or travelling.

lowPrice.title: lowPrice
lowPrice.description:
The lowest price of all offers available.

Usage guidelines:

* Use values from 0123456789 (Unicode 'DIGIT ZERO' (U+0030) to 'DIGIT NINE' (U+0039)) rather than superficially similar Unicode symbols.
* Use '.' (Unicode 'FULL STOP' (U+002E)) rather than ',' to indicate a decimal point. Avoid using these symbols as a readability separator.

accessibilityAPI.title: accessibilityAPI
accessibilityAPI.description: Indicates that the resource is compatible with the referenced accessibility API. Values should be drawn from the [approved vocabulary](https://www.w3.org/2021/a11y-discov-vocab/latest/#accessibilityAPI-vocabulary).

awayTeam.title: awayTeam
awayTeam.description: The away team in a sports event.

shippingDetails.title: shippingDetails
shippingDetails.description: Indicates information about the shipping policies and options associated with an [[Offer]].

vehicleConfiguration.title: vehicleConfiguration
vehicleConfiguration.description: A short text indicating the configuration of the vehicle, e.g. '5dr hatchback ST 2.5 MT 225 hp' or 'limited edition'.

suggestedAge.title: suggestedAge
suggestedAge.description: The age or age range for the intended audience or person, for example 3-12 months for infants, 1-5 years for toddlers.

eventStatus.title: eventStatus
eventStatus.description: An eventStatus of an event represents its status; particularly useful when an event is cancelled or rescheduled.

occupationalCredentialAwarded.title: occupationalCredentialAwarded
occupationalCredentialAwarded.description: A description of the qualification, award, certificate, diploma or other occupational credential awarded as a consequence of successful completion of this course or program.

boardingGroup.title: boardingGroup
boardingGroup.description: The airline-specific indicator of boarding order / preference.

offers.title: offers
offers.description: An offer to provide this item—for example, an offer to sell a product, rent the DVD of a movie, perform a service, or give away tickets to an event. Use [[businessFunction]] to indicate the kind of transaction offered, i.e. sell, lease, etc. This property can also be used to describe a [[Demand]]. While this property is listed as expected on a number of common types, it can be used in others. In that case, using a second type, such as Product or a subtype of Product, can clarify the nature of the offer.

healthPlanNetworkId.title: healthPlanNetworkId
healthPlanNetworkId.description: Name or unique ID of network. (Networks are often reused across different insurance plans.)

targetPopulation.title: targetPopulation
targetPopulation.description: Characteristics of the population for which this is intended, or which typically uses it, e.g. 'adults'.

overdosage.title: overdosage
overdosage.description: Any information related to overdose on a drug, including signs or symptoms, treatments, contact information for emergency response.

postalCodeEnd.title: postalCodeEnd
postalCodeEnd.description: Last postal code in the range (included). Needs to be after [[postalCodeBegin]].

additionalVariable.title: additionalVariable
additionalVariable.description: Any additional component of the exercise prescription that may need to be articulated to the patient. This may include the order of exercises, the number of repetitions of movement, quantitative distance, progressions over time, etc.

itemOffered.title: itemOffered
itemOffered.description: An item being offered (or demanded). The transactional nature of the offer or demand is documented using [[businessFunction]], e.g. sell, lease etc. While several common expected types are listed explicitly in this definition, others can be used. Using a second type, such as Product or a subtype of Product, can clarify the nature of the offer.

bloodSupply.title: bloodSupply
bloodSupply.description: The blood vessel that carries blood from the heart to the muscle.

infectiousAgentClass.title: infectiousAgentClass
infectiousAgentClass.description: The class of infectious agent (bacteria, prion, etc.) that causes the disease.

alternativeOf.title: alternativeOf
alternativeOf.description: Another gene which is a variation of this one.

dateModified.title: dateModified
dateModified.description: The date on which the CreativeWork was most recently modified or when the item's entry was modified within a DataFeed.

cvdCollectionDate.title: cvdCollectionDate
cvdCollectionDate.description: collectiondate - Date for which patient counts are reported.

tourBookingPage.title: tourBookingPage
tourBookingPage.description: A page providing information on how to book a tour of some [[Place]], such as an [[Accommodation]] or [[ApartmentComplex]] in a real estate setting, as well as other kinds of tours as appropriate.

antagonist.title: antagonist
antagonist.description: The muscle whose action counteracts the specified muscle.

nextItem.title: nextItem
nextItem.description: A link to the ListItem that follows the current one.

honorificSuffix.title: honorificSuffix
honorificSuffix.description: An honorific suffix following a Person's name such as M.D./PhD/MSCSW.

editEIDR.title: editEIDR
editEIDR.description:
An [EIDR](https://eidr.org/) (Entertainment Identifier Registry) [[identifier]] representing a specific edit / edition for a work of film or television.

For example, the motion picture known as "Ghostbusters" whose [[titleEIDR]] is "10.5240/7EC7-228A-510A-053E-CBB8-J" has several edits, e.g. "10.5240/1F2A-E1C5-680A-14C6-E76B-I" and "10.5240/8A35-3BEE-6497-5D12-9E4F-3".

Since schema.org types like [[Movie]] and [[TVEpisode]] can be used for both works and their multiple expressions, it is possible to use [[titleEIDR]] alone (for a general description), or alongside [[editEIDR]] for a more edit-specific description.

sameAs.title: sameAs
sameAs.description: URL of a reference Web page that unambiguously indicates the item's identity. E.g. the URL of the item's Wikipedia page, Wikidata entry, or official website.

identifyingTest.title: identifyingTest
identifyingTest.description: A diagnostic test that can identify this sign.

connectedTo.title: connectedTo
