connectedTo.description: Other anatomical structures to which this structure is connected.

timeOfDay.title: timeOfDay
timeOfDay.description: The time of day the program normally runs. For example, "evenings".

numberOfPreviousOwners.title: numberOfPreviousOwners
numberOfPreviousOwners.description: The number of owners of the vehicle, including the current one.\n\nTypical unit code(s): C62.

requiresSubscription.title: requiresSubscription
requiresSubscription.description: Indicates if use of the media require a subscription  (either paid or free). Allowed values are ```true``` or ```false``` (note that an earlier version had 'yes', 'no').

branchOf.title: branchOf
branchOf.description: The larger organization that this local business is a branch of, if any. Not to be confused with (anatomical) [[branch]].

addressRegion.title: addressRegion
addressRegion.description: The region in which the locality is, and which is in the country. For example, California or another appropriate first-level [Administrative division](https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/List_of_administrative_divisions_by_country).

renegotiableLoan.title: renegotiableLoan
renegotiableLoan.description: Whether the terms for payment of interest can be renegotiated during the life of the loan.

abstract.title: abstract
abstract.description: An abstract is a short description that summarizes a [[CreativeWork]].

operatingSystem.title: operatingSystem
operatingSystem.description: Operating systems supported (Windows 7, OS X 10.6, Android 1.6).

transitTime.title: transitTime
transitTime.description: The typical delay the order has been sent for delivery and the goods reach the final customer. Typical properties: minValue, maxValue, unitCode (d for DAY).

termCode.title: termCode
termCode.description: A code that identifies this [[DefinedTerm]] within a [[DefinedTermSet]].

driveWheelConfiguration.title: driveWheelConfiguration
driveWheelConfiguration.description: The drive wheel configuration, i.e. which roadwheels will receive torque from the vehicle's engine via the drivetrain.

usageInfo.title: usageInfo
usageInfo.description:
The schema.org [[usageInfo]] property indicates further information about a [[CreativeWork]]. This property is applicable both to works that are freely available and to those that require payment or other transactions. It can reference additional information, e.g. community expectations on preferred linking and citation conventions, as well as purchasing details. For something that can be commercially licensed, usageInfo can provide detailed, resource-specific information about licensing options.

This property can be used alongside the license property which indicates license(s) applicable to some piece of content. The usageInfo property can provide information about other licensing options, e.g. acquiring commercial usage rights for an image that is also available under non-commercial creative commons licenses.

interactingDrug.title: interactingDrug
interactingDrug.description: Another drug that is known to interact with this drug in a way that impacts the effect of this drug or causes a risk to the patient. Note: disease interactions are typically captured as contraindications.

isBasedOn.title: isBasedOn
isBasedOn.description: A resource from which this work is derived or from which it is a modification or adaptation.

physiologicalBenefits.title: physiologicalBenefits
physiologicalBenefits.description: Specific physiologic benefits associated to the plan.

encodesBioChemEntity.title: encodesBioChemEntity
encodesBioChemEntity.description: Another BioChemEntity encoded by this one.

replyToUrl.title: replyToUrl
replyToUrl.description: The URL at which a reply may be posted to the specified UserComment.

shippingOrigin.title: shippingOrigin
shippingOrigin.description: Indicates the origin of a shipment, i.e. where it should be coming from.

hasMap.title: hasMap
hasMap.description: A URL to a map of the place.

creditText.title: creditText
creditText.description: Text that can be used to credit person(s) and/or organization(s) associated with a published Creative Work.

serviceOperator.title: serviceOperator
serviceOperator.description: The operating organization, if different from the provider.  This enables the representation of services that are provided by an organization, but operated by another organization like a subcontractor.

recipeCuisine.title: recipeCuisine
recipeCuisine.description: The cuisine of the recipe (for example, French or Ethiopian).

dateDeleted.title: dateDeleted
dateDeleted.description: The datetime the item was removed from the DataFeed.

pageEnd.title: pageEnd
pageEnd.description: The page on which the work ends; for example "138" or "xvi".

alignmentType.title: alignmentType
alignmentType.description: A category of alignment between the learning resource and the framework node. Recommended values include: 'requires', 'textComplexity', 'readingLevel', and 'educationalSubject'.

webCheckinTime.title: webCheckinTime
webCheckinTime.description: The time when a passenger can check into the flight online.

dropoffTime.title: dropoffTime
dropoffTime.description: When a rental car can be dropped off.

suggestedMeasurement.title: suggestedMeasurement
suggestedMeasurement.description: A suggested range of body measurements for the intended audience or person, for example inseam between 32 and 34 inches or height between 170 and 190 cm. Typically found on a size chart for wearable products.

funding.title: funding
funding.description: A [[Grant]] that directly or indirectly provide funding or sponsorship for this item. See also [[ownershipFundingInfo]].

subtitleLanguage.title: subtitleLanguage
subtitleLanguage.description: Languages in which subtitles/captions are available, in [IETF BCP 47 standard format](http://tools.ietf.org/html/bcp47).

printPage.title: printPage
printPage.description: If this NewsArticle appears in print, this field indicates the name of the page on which the article is found. Please note that this field is intended for the exact page name (e.g. A5, B18).

advanceBookingRequirement.title: advanceBookingRequirement
advanceBookingRequirement.description: The amount of time that is required between accepting the offer and the actual usage of the resource or service.

legislationDateVersion.title: legislationDateVersion
legislationDateVersion.description: The point-in-time at which the provided description of the legislation is valid (e.g.: when looking at the law on the 2016-04-07 (= dateVersion), I get the consolidation of 2015-04-12 of the "National Insurance Contributions Act 2015")

specialOpeningHoursSpecification.title: specialOpeningHoursSpecification
specialOpeningHoursSpecification.description: The special opening hours of a certain place.\n\nUse this to explicitly override general opening hours brought in scope by [[openingHoursSpecification]] or [[openingHours]].

repeatFrequency.title: repeatFrequency
repeatFrequency.description:
Defines the frequency at which [[Event]]s will occur according to a schedule [[Schedule]]. The intervals between
      events should be defined as a [[Duration]] of time.

requiredMaxAge.title: requiredMaxAge
requiredMaxAge.description: Audiences defined by a person's maximum age.

suggestedMinAge.title: suggestedMinAge
suggestedMinAge.description: Minimum recommended age in years for the audience or user.

numberOfBathroomsTotal.title: numberOfBathroomsTotal
numberOfBathroomsTotal.description: The total integer number of bathrooms in some [[Accommodation]], following real estate conventions as [documented in RESO](https://ddwiki.reso.org/display/DDW17/BathroomsTotalInteger+Field): "The simple sum of the number of bathrooms. For example for a property with two Full Bathrooms and one Half Bathroom, the Bathrooms Total Integer will be 3.". See also [[numberOfRooms]].

includedInDataCatalog.title: includedInDataCatalog
includedInDataCatalog.description: A data catalog which contains this dataset.

trainNumber.title: trainNumber
trainNumber.description: The unique identifier for the train.

referencesOrder.title: referencesOrder
referencesOrder.description: The Order(s) related to this Invoice. One or more Orders may be combined into a single Invoice.

encodesCreativeWork.title: encodesCreativeWork
encodesCreativeWork.description: The CreativeWork encoded by this media object.

downvoteCount.title: downvoteCount
downvoteCount.description: The number of downvotes this question, answer or comment has received from the community.

smokingAllowed.title: smokingAllowed
smokingAllowed.description: Indicates whether it is allowed to smoke in the place, e.g. in the restaurant, hotel or hotel room.

reservationId.title: reservationId
reservationId.description: A unique identifier for the reservation.

colorSwatch.title: colorSwatch
colorSwatch.description: A color swatch image, visualizing the color of a [[Product]]. Should match the textual description specified in the [[color]] property. This can be a URL or a fully described ImageObject.

isBasedOnUrl.title: isBasedOnUrl
isBasedOnUrl.description: A resource that was used in the creation of this resource. This term can be repeated for multiple sources. For example, http://example.com/great-multiplication-intro.html.

cookingMethod.title: cookingMethod
cookingMethod.description: The method of cooking, such as Frying, Steaming, ...

seasons.title: seasons
seasons.description: A season in a media series.

seatingCapacity.title: seatingCapacity
seatingCapacity.description: The number of persons that can be seated (e.g. in a vehicle), both in terms of the physical space available, and in terms of limitations set by law.\n\nTypical unit code(s): C62 for persons.

reviewRating.title: reviewRating
reviewRating.description: The rating given in this review. Note that reviews can themselves be rated. The ```reviewRating``` applies to rating given by the review. The [[aggregateRating]] property applies to the review itself, as a creative work.

ratingValue.title: ratingValue
ratingValue.description:
The rating for the content.

Usage guidelines:

* Use values from 0123456789 (Unicode 'DIGIT ZERO' (U+0030) to 'DIGIT NINE' (U+0039)) rather than superficially similar Unicode symbols.
* Use '.' (Unicode 'FULL STOP' (U+002E)) rather than ',' to indicate a decimal point. Avoid using these symbols as a readability separator.

adverseOutcome.title: adverseOutcome
adverseOutcome.description: A possible complication and/or side effect of this therapy. If it is known that an adverse outcome is serious (resulting in death, disability, or permanent damage; requiring hospitalization; or otherwise life-threatening or requiring immediate medical attention), tag it as a seriousAdverseOutcome instead.

answerExplanation.title: answerExplanation
answerExplanation.description: A step-by-step or full explanation about Answer. Can outline how this Answer was achieved or contain more broad clarification or statement about it.

orderQuantity.title: orderQuantity
orderQuantity.description: The number of the item ordered. If the property is not set, assume the quantity is one.

numberedPosition.title: numberedPosition
numberedPosition.description: A number associated with a role in an organization, for example, the number on an athlete's jersey.

inCodeSet.title: inCodeSet
inCodeSet.description: A [[CategoryCodeSet]] that contains this category code.

domiciledMortgage.title: domiciledMortgage
domiciledMortgage.description: Whether borrower is a resident of the jurisdiction where the property is located.

menuAddOn.title: menuAddOn
menuAddOn.description: Additional menu item(s) such as a side dish of salad or side order of fries that can be added to this menu item. Additionally it can be a menu section containing allowed add-on menu items for this menu item.

baseSalary.title: baseSalary
baseSalary.description: The base salary of the job or of an employee in an EmployeeRole.

actionableFeedbackPolicy.title: actionableFeedbackPolicy
actionableFeedbackPolicy.description: For a [[NewsMediaOrganization]] or other news-related [[Organization]], a statement about public engagement activities (for news media, the newsroom’s), including involving the public - digitally or otherwise -- in coverage decisions, reporting and activities after publication.

bodyType.title: bodyType
bodyType.description: Indicates the design and body style of the vehicle (e.g. station wagon, hatchback, etc.).

startDate.title: startDate
startDate.description: The start date and time of the item (in [ISO 8601 date format](http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/ISO_8601)).

mileageFromOdometer.title: mileageFromOdometer
mileageFromOdometer.description: The total distance travelled by the particular vehicle since its initial production, as read from its odometer.\n\nTypical unit code(s): KMT for kilometers, SMI for statute miles.

numConstraints.title: numConstraints
numConstraints.description: Indicates the number of constraints property values defined for a particular [[ConstraintNode]] such as [[StatisticalVariable]]. This helps applications understand if they have access to a sufficiently complete description of a [[StatisticalVariable]] or other construct that is defined using properties on template-style nodes.

itemReviewed.title: itemReviewed
itemReviewed.description: The item that is being reviewed/rated.

hasBioPolymerSequence.title: hasBioPolymerSequence
hasBioPolymerSequence.description: A symbolic representation of a BioChemEntity. For example, a nucleotide sequence of a Gene or an amino acid sequence of a Protein.

totalHistoricalEnrollment.title: totalHistoricalEnrollment
totalHistoricalEnrollment.description: The total number of students that have enrolled in the history of the course.

requiredCollateral.title: requiredCollateral
requiredCollateral.description: Assets required to secure loan or credit repayments. It may take form of third party pledge, goods, financial instruments (cash, securities, etc.)

trainName.title: trainName
trainName.description: The name of the train (e.g. The Orient Express).

legislationTransposes.title: legislationTransposes
legislationTransposes.description: Indicates that this legislation (or part of legislation) fulfills the objectives set by another legislation, by passing appropriate implementation measures. Typically, some legislations of European Union's member states or regions transpose European Directives. This indicates a legally binding link between the 2 legislations.

numberOfDoors.title: numberOfDoors
numberOfDoors.description: The number of doors.\n\nTypical unit code(s): C62.

articleBody.title: articleBody
articleBody.description: The actual body of the article.

evidenceLevel.title: evidenceLevel
evidenceLevel.description: Strength of evidence of the data used to formulate the guideline (enumerated).

mpn.title: mpn
mpn.description: The Manufacturer Part Number (MPN) of the product, or the product to which the offer refers.

returnMethod.title: returnMethod
returnMethod.description: The type of return method offered, specified from an enumeration.

jobImmediateStart.title: jobImmediateStart
jobImmediateStart.description: An indicator as to whether a position is available for an immediate start.

interactionType.title: interactionType
interactionType.description: The Action representing the type of interaction. For up votes, +1s, etc. use [[LikeAction]]. For down votes use [[DislikeAction]]. Otherwise, use the most specific Action.

availableOnDevice.title: availableOnDevice
availableOnDevice.description: Device required to run the application. Used in cases where a specific make/model is required to run the application.

regionsAllowed.title: regionsAllowed
regionsAllowed.description: The regions where the media is allowed. If not specified, then it's assumed to be allowed everywhere. Specify the countries in [ISO 3166 format](http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/ISO_3166).

recordedAt.title: recordedAt
recordedAt.description: The Event where the CreativeWork was recorded. The CreativeWork may capture all or part of the event.

supplyTo.title: supplyTo
supplyTo.description: The area to which the artery supplies blood.

parentOrganization.title: parentOrganization
parentOrganization.description: The larger organization that this organization is a [[subOrganization]] of, if any.

returnPolicyCategory.title: returnPolicyCategory
returnPolicyCategory.description: Specifies an applicable return policy (from an enumeration).

ineligibleRegion.title: ineligibleRegion
ineligibleRegion.description: The ISO 3166-1 (ISO 3166-1 alpha-2) or ISO 3166-2 code, the place, or the GeoShape for the geo-political region(s) for which the offer or delivery charge specification is not valid, e.g. a region where the transaction is not allowed.\n\nSee also [[eligibleRegion]].

chemicalComposition.title: chemicalComposition
chemicalComposition.description: The chemical composition describes the identity and relative ratio of the chemical elements that make up the substance.

foodWarning.title: foodWarning
foodWarning.description: Any precaution, guidance, contraindication, etc. related to consumption of specific foods while taking this drug.

additionalName.title: additionalName
additionalName.description: An additional name for a Person, can be used for a middle name.

backstory.title: backstory
backstory.description: For an [[Article]], typically a [[NewsArticle]], the backstory property provides a textual summary giving a brief explanation of why and how an article was created. In a journalistic setting this could include information about reporting process, methods, interviews, data sources, etc.

credentialCategory.title: credentialCategory
credentialCategory.description: The category or type of credential being described, for example "degree”, “certificate”, “badge”, or more specific term.

acceptedAnswer.title: acceptedAnswer
acceptedAnswer.description: The answer(s) that has been accepted as best, typically on a Question/Answer site. Sites vary in their selection mechanisms, e.g. drawing on community opinion and/or the view of the Question author.

fileFormat.title: fileFormat
fileFormat.description: Media type, typically MIME format (see [IANA site](http://www.iana.org/assignments/media-types/media-types.xhtml)) of the content, e.g. application/zip of a SoftwareApplication binary. In cases where a CreativeWork has several media type representations, 'encoding' can be used to indicate each MediaObject alongside particular fileFormat information. Unregistered or niche file formats can be indicated instead via the most appropriate URL, e.g. defining Web page or a Wikipedia entry.

expectedArrivalUntil.title: expectedArrivalUntil
expectedArrivalUntil.description: The latest date the package may arrive.

cookTime.title: cookTime
cookTime.description: The time it takes to actually cook the dish, in [ISO 8601 duration format](http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/ISO_8601).

carrier.title: carrier
carrier.description: 'carrier' is an out-dated term indicating the 'provider' for parcel delivery and flights.

drug.title: drug
drug.description: Specifying a drug or medicine used in a medication procedure.

inSupportOf.title: inSupportOf
inSupportOf.description: Qualification, candidature, degree, application that Thesis supports.

speechToTextMarkup.title: speechToTextMarkup
speechToTextMarkup.description: Form of markup used. eg. [SSML](https://www.w3.org/TR/speech-synthesis11) or [IPA](https://www.wikidata.org/wiki/Property:P898).

sdPublisher.title: sdPublisher
sdPublisher.description:
Indicates the party responsible for generating and publishing the current structured data markup, typically in cases where the structured data is derived automatically from existing published content but published on a different site. For example, student projects and open data initiatives often re-publish existing content with more explicitly structured metadata. The
[[sdPublisher]] property helps make such practices more explicit.

customer.title: customer
customer.description: Party placing the order or paying the invoice.

subStructure.title: subStructure
subStructure.description: Component (sub-)structure(s) that comprise this anatomical structure.

transitTimeLabel.title: transitTimeLabel
transitTimeLabel.description: Label to match an [[OfferShippingDetails]] with a [[DeliveryTimeSettings]] (within the context of a [[shippingSettingsLink]] cross-reference).

educationalCredentialAwarded.title: educationalCredentialAwarded
educationalCredentialAwarded.description: A description of the qualification, award, certificate, diploma or other educational credential awarded as a consequence of successful completion of this course or program.

partOfTrip.title: partOfTrip
partOfTrip.description: Identifies that this [[Trip]] is a subTrip of another Trip.  For example Day 1, Day 2, etc. of a multi-day trip.

hasDigitalDocumentPermission.title: hasDigitalDocumentPermission
hasDigitalDocumentPermission.description: A permission related to the access to this document (e.g. permission to read or write an electronic document). For a public document, specify a grantee with an Audience with audienceType equal to "public".

codeSampleType.title: codeSampleType
codeSampleType.description: What type of code sample: full (compile ready) solution, code snippet, inline code, scripts, template.

arrivalAirport.title: arrivalAirport
arrivalAirport.description: The airport where the flight terminates.

tool.title: tool
tool.description: A sub property of instrument. An object used (but not consumed) when performing instructions or a direction.

expertConsiderations.title: expertConsiderations
expertConsiderations.description: Medical expert advice related to the plan.

copyrightHolder.title: copyrightHolder
copyrightHolder.description: The party holding the legal copyright to the CreativeWork.

returnLabelSource.title: returnLabelSource
returnLabelSource.description: The method (from an enumeration) by which the customer obtains a return shipping label for a product returned for any reason.

availableFrom.title: availableFrom
availableFrom.description: When the item is available for pickup from the store, locker, etc.

applicationStartDate.title: applicationStartDate
applicationStartDate.description: The date at which the program begins collecting applications for the next enrollment cycle.

availableAtOrFrom.title: availableAtOrFrom
availableAtOrFrom.description: The place(s) from which the offer can be obtained (e.g. store locations).

publishedBy.title: publishedBy
publishedBy.description: An agent associated with the publication event.

expressedIn.title: expressedIn
expressedIn.description: Tissue, organ, biological sample, etc in which activity of this gene has been observed experimentally. For example brain, digestive system.

arrivalGate.title: arrivalGate
arrivalGate.description: Identifier of the flight's arrival gate.

subjectOf.title: subjectOf
subjectOf.description: A CreativeWork or Event about this Thing.

functionalClass.title: functionalClass
functionalClass.description: The degree of mobility the joint allows.

discussionUrl.title: discussionUrl
discussionUrl.description: A link to the page containing the comments of the CreativeWork.

isRelatedTo.title: isRelatedTo
isRelatedTo.description: A pointer to another, somehow related product (or multiple products).

governmentBenefitsInfo.title: governmentBenefitsInfo
governmentBenefitsInfo.description: governmentBenefitsInfo provides information about government benefits associated with a SpecialAnnouncement.

seasonNumber.title: seasonNumber
seasonNumber.description: Position of the season within an ordered group of seasons.

events.title: events
events.description: Upcoming or past events associated with this place or organization.

carrierRequirements.title: carrierRequirements
carrierRequirements.description: Specifies specific carrier(s) requirements for the application (e.g. an application may only work on a specific carrier network).

schemaVersion.title: schemaVersion
schemaVersion.description:
Indicates (by URL or string) a particular version of a schema used in some CreativeWork. This property was created primarily to
    indicate the use of a specific schema.org release, e.g. ```10.0``` as a simple string, or more explicitly via URL, ```https://schema.org/docs/releases.html#v10.0```. There may be situations in which other schemas might usefully be referenced this way, e.g. ```http://dublincore.org/specifications/dublin-core/dces/1999-07-02/``` but this has not been carefully explored in the community.

collection.title: collection
collection.description: A sub property of object. The collection target of the action.

paymentMethodId.title: paymentMethodId
paymentMethodId.description: An identifier for the method of payment used (e.g. the last 4 digits of the credit card).

gameLocation.title: gameLocation
gameLocation.description: Real or fictional location of the game (or part of game).

countryOfLastProcessing.title: countryOfLastProcessing
countryOfLastProcessing.description: The place where the item (typically [[Product]]) was last processed and tested before importation.

closes.title: closes
closes.description: The closing hour of the place or service on the given day(s) of the week.

publisher.title: publisher
publisher.description: The publisher of the creative work.

ccRecipient.title: ccRecipient
ccRecipient.description: A sub property of recipient. The recipient copied on a message.
